65// This is used as a reference when computing the source variance for the
66// purpose of activity masking.
67// Eventually this should be replaced by custom no-reference routines,
68// which will be faster.

74 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128
75};

111unsigned int vp9_get_sby_variance(VP9_COMP *cpi, const struct buf_2d *ref,
112 BLOCK_SIZE bs) {
113 unsigned int sse;
114 const unsigned int var =
115 cpi->fn_ptr[bs].vf(ref->buf, ref->stride, VP9_VAR_OFFS, 0, &sse);
116 return var;
117}
118
119#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
120unsigned int vp9_high_get_sby_variance(VP9_COMP *cpi, const struct buf_2d *ref,
121 BLOCK_SIZE bs, int bd) {
122 unsigned int var, sse;
123 switch (bd) {
124 case 10:
125 var =
126 cpi->fn_ptr[bs].vf(ref->buf, ref->stride,
127 CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_10), 0, &sse);
128 break;
129 case 12:
130 var =
131 cpi->fn_ptr[bs].vf(ref->buf, ref->stride,
132 CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_12), 0, &sse);
133 break;
134 case 8:
135 default:
136 var =
137 cpi->fn_ptr[bs].vf(ref->buf, ref->stride,
138 CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_8), 0, &sse);
139 break;
140 }
141 return var;
142}
143#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
144
145unsigned int vp9_get_sby_perpixel_variance(VP9_COMP *cpi,
146 const struct buf_2d *ref,
147 BLOCK_SIZE bs) {
148 return ROUND_POWER_OF_TWO(vp9_get_sby_variance(cpi, ref, bs),
149 num_pels_log2_lookup[bs]);
150}
151
152#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
153unsigned int vp9_high_get_sby_perpixel_variance(VP9_COMP *cpi,
154 const struct buf_2d *ref,
155 BLOCK_SIZE bs, int bd) {
156 return (unsigned int)ROUND64_POWER_OF_TWO(
157 (int64_t)vp9_high_get_sby_variance(cpi, ref, bs, bd),
158 num_pels_log2_lookup[bs]);
159}
160#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
161
162#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
163static unsigned int get_sby_perpixel_diff_variance(VP9_COMP *cpi,
164 const struct buf_2d *ref,
165 int mi_row, int mi_col,
166 BLOCK_SIZE bs) {
167 unsigned int sse, var;
168 uint8_t *last_y;
169 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *last = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, LAST_FRAME);
170
171 assert(last != NULL);
172 last_y =
173 &last->y_buffer[mi_row * MI_SIZE * last->y_stride + mi_col * MI_SIZE];
174 var = cpi->fn_ptr[bs].vf(ref->buf, ref->stride, last_y, last->y_stride, &sse);
175 return ROUND_POWER_OF_TWO(var, num_pels_log2_lookup[bs]);
176}
177
178static BLOCK_SIZE get_rd_var_based_fixed_partition(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x,
179 int mi_row, int mi_col) {
180 unsigned int var = get_sby_perpixel_diff_variance(
181 cpi, &x->plane[0].src, mi_row, mi_col, BLOCK_64X64);
182 if (var < 8)
183 return BLOCK_64X64;
184 else if (var < 128)
185 return BLOCK_32X32;
186 else if (var < 2048)
187 return BLOCK_16X16;
188 else
189 return BLOCK_8X8;
190}
191#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
192
193static void set_segment_index(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x, int mi_row,
194 int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int segment_index) {
195 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
196 const struct segmentation *const seg = &cm->seg;
197 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
198 MODE_INFO *mi = xd->mi[0];
199
200 const AQ_MODE aq_mode = cpi->oxcf.aq_mode;
201 const uint8_t *const map =
202 seg->update_map ? cpi->segmentation_map : cm->last_frame_seg_map;
203
204 // Initialize the segmentation index as 0.
205 mi->segment_id = 0;
206
207 // Skip the rest if AQ mode is disabled.
208 if (!seg->enabled) return;
209
210 switch (aq_mode) {
211 case CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ:
212 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
213 break;
214#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
215 case VARIANCE_AQ:
216 if (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME || cpi->refresh_alt_ref_frame ||
217 cpi->force_update_segmentation ||
218 (cpi->refresh_golden_frame && !cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref)) {
219 int min_energy;
220 int max_energy;
221 // Get sub block energy range
222 if (bsize >= BLOCK_32X32) {
223 vp9_get_sub_block_energy(cpi, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, &min_energy,
224 &max_energy);
225 } else {
226 min_energy = bsize <= BLOCK_16X16 ? x->mb_energy
227 : vp9_block_energy(cpi, x, bsize);
228 }
229 mi->segment_id = vp9_vaq_segment_id(min_energy);
230 } else {
231 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
232 }
233 break;
234 case EQUATOR360_AQ:
235 if (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME || cpi->force_update_segmentation)
236 mi->segment_id = vp9_360aq_segment_id(mi_row, cm->mi_rows);
237 else
238 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
239 break;
240#endif
241 case LOOKAHEAD_AQ:
242 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
243 break;
244 case PSNR_AQ: mi->segment_id = segment_index; break;
245 case PERCEPTUAL_AQ: mi->segment_id = x->segment_id; break;
246 default:
247 // NO_AQ or PSNR_AQ
248 break;
249 }
250
251 // Set segment index from ROI map if it's enabled.
252 if (cpi->roi.enabled)
253 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
254
255 vp9_init_plane_quantizers(cpi, x);
256}
257
258// Lighter version of set_offsets that only sets the mode info
259// pointers.
260static INLINE void set_mode_info_offsets(VP9_COMMON *const cm,
261 MACROBLOCK *const x,
262 MACROBLOCKD *const xd, int mi_row,
263 int mi_col) {
264 const int idx_str = xd->mi_stride * mi_row + mi_col;
265 xd->mi = cm->mi_grid_visible + idx_str;
266 xd->mi[0] = cm->mi + idx_str;
267 x->mbmi_ext = x->mbmi_ext_base + (mi_row * cm->mi_cols + mi_col);
268}
269
270static void set_ssim_rdmult(VP9_COMP *const cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
271 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize, const int mi_row,
272 const int mi_col, int *const rdmult) {
273 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
274
275 const int bsize_base = BLOCK_16X16;
276 const int num_8x8_w = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize_base];
277 const int num_8x8_h = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize_base];
278 const int num_cols = (cm->mi_cols + num_8x8_w - 1) / num_8x8_w;
279 const int num_rows = (cm->mi_rows + num_8x8_h - 1) / num_8x8_h;
280 const int num_bcols =
281 (num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] + num_8x8_w - 1) / num_8x8_w;
282 const int num_brows =
283 (num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize] + num_8x8_h - 1) / num_8x8_h;
284 int row, col;
285 double num_of_mi = 0.0;
286 double geom_mean_of_scale = 0.0;
287
288 assert(cpi->oxcf.tuning == VP8_TUNE_SSIM);
289
290 for (row = mi_row / num_8x8_w;
291 row < num_rows && row < mi_row / num_8x8_w + num_brows; ++row) {
292 for (col = mi_col / num_8x8_h;
293 col < num_cols && col < mi_col / num_8x8_h + num_bcols; ++col) {
294 const int index = row * num_cols + col;
295 geom_mean_of_scale += log(cpi->mi_ssim_rdmult_scaling_factors[index]);
296 num_of_mi += 1.0;
297 }
298 }
299 geom_mean_of_scale = exp(geom_mean_of_scale / num_of_mi);
300
301 *rdmult = (int)((double)(*rdmult) * geom_mean_of_scale);
302 *rdmult = VPXMAX(*rdmult, 0);
303 set_error_per_bit(x, *rdmult);
304 vpx_clear_system_state();
305}
306
307static void set_offsets(VP9_COMP *cpi, const TileInfo *const tile,
308 MACROBLOCK *const x, int mi_row, int mi_col,
309 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
310 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
311 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
312 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
313 const int mi_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
314 const int mi_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
315 MvLimits *const mv_limits = &x->mv_limits;
316
317 set_skip_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col);
318
319 set_mode_info_offsets(cm, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col);
320
321 // Set up destination pointers.
322 vp9_setup_dst_planes(xd->plane, get_frame_new_buffer(cm), mi_row, mi_col);
323
324 // Set up limit values for MV components.
325 // Mv beyond the range do not produce new/different prediction block.
326 mv_limits->row_min = -(((mi_row + mi_height) * MI_SIZE) + VP9_INTERP_EXTEND);
327 mv_limits->col_min = -(((mi_col + mi_width) * MI_SIZE) + VP9_INTERP_EXTEND);
328 mv_limits->row_max = (cm->mi_rows - mi_row) * MI_SIZE + VP9_INTERP_EXTEND;
329 mv_limits->col_max = (cm->mi_cols - mi_col) * MI_SIZE + VP9_INTERP_EXTEND;
330
331 // Set up distance of MB to edge of frame in 1/8th pel units.
332 assert(!(mi_col & (mi_width - 1)) && !(mi_row & (mi_height - 1)));
333 set_mi_row_col(xd, tile, mi_row, mi_height, mi_col, mi_width, cm->mi_rows,
334 cm->mi_cols);
335
336 // Set up source buffers.
337 vp9_setup_src_planes(x, cpi->Source, mi_row, mi_col);
338
339 // R/D setup.
340 x->rddiv = cpi->rd.RDDIV;
341 x->rdmult = cpi->rd.RDMULT;
342 if (oxcf->tuning == VP8_TUNE_SSIM) {
343 set_ssim_rdmult(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, &x->rdmult);
344 }
345
346 // required by vp9_append_sub8x8_mvs_for_idx() and vp9_find_best_ref_mvs()
347 xd->tile = *tile;
348}
349
350static void duplicate_mode_info_in_sb(VP9_COMMON *cm, MACROBLOCKD *xd,
351 int mi_row, int mi_col,
352 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
353 const int block_width =
354 VPXMIN(num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize], cm->mi_cols - mi_col);
355 const int block_height =
356 VPXMIN(num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize], cm->mi_rows - mi_row);
357 const int mi_stride = xd->mi_stride;
358 MODE_INFO *const src_mi = xd->mi[0];
359 int i, j;
360
361 for (j = 0; j < block_height; ++j)
362 for (i = 0; i < block_width; ++i) xd->mi[j * mi_stride + i] = src_mi;
363}
364
365static void set_block_size(VP9_COMP *const cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
366 MACROBLOCKD *const xd, int mi_row, int mi_col,
367 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
368 if (cpi->common.mi_cols > mi_col && cpi->common.mi_rows > mi_row) {
369 set_mode_info_offsets(&cpi->common, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col);
370 xd->mi[0]->sb_type = bsize;
371 }
372}
373
374typedef struct {
375 // This struct is used for computing variance in choose_partitioning(), where
376 // the max number of samples within a superblock is 16x16 (with 4x4 avg). Even
377 // in high bitdepth, uint32_t is enough for sum_square_error (2^12 * 2^12 * 16
378 // * 16 = 2^32).
379 uint32_t sum_square_error;
380 int32_t sum_error;
381 int log2_count;
382 int variance;
383} var;
384
385typedef struct {
386 var none;
387 var horz[2];
388 var vert[2];
389} partition_variance;
390
391typedef struct {
392 partition_variance part_variances;
393 var split[4];
394} v4x4;
395
396typedef struct {
397 partition_variance part_variances;
398 v4x4 split[4];
399} v8x8;
400
401typedef struct {
402 partition_variance part_variances;
403 v8x8 split[4];
404} v16x16;
405
406typedef struct {
407 partition_variance part_variances;
408 v16x16 split[4];
409} v32x32;
410
411typedef struct {
412 partition_variance part_variances;
413 v32x32 split[4];
414} v64x64;
415
416typedef struct {
417 partition_variance *part_variances;
418 var *split[4];
419} variance_node;
420
421typedef enum {
422 V16X16,
423 V32X32,
424 V64X64,
425} TREE_LEVEL;
426
427static void tree_to_node(void *data, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, variance_node *node) {
428 int i;
429 node->part_variances = NULL;
430 switch (bsize) {
431 case BLOCK_64X64: {
432 v64x64 *vt = (v64x64 *)data;
433 node->part_variances = &vt->part_variances;
434 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
435 node->split[i] = &vt->split[i].part_variances.none;
436 break;
437 }
438 case BLOCK_32X32: {
439 v32x32 *vt = (v32x32 *)data;
440 node->part_variances = &vt->part_variances;
441 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
442 node->split[i] = &vt->split[i].part_variances.none;
443 break;
444 }
445 case BLOCK_16X16: {
446 v16x16 *vt = (v16x16 *)data;
447 node->part_variances = &vt->part_variances;
448 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
449 node->split[i] = &vt->split[i].part_variances.none;
450 break;
451 }
452 case BLOCK_8X8: {
453 v8x8 *vt = (v8x8 *)data;
454 node->part_variances = &vt->part_variances;
455 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
456 node->split[i] = &vt->split[i].part_variances.none;
457 break;
458 }
459 default: {
460 v4x4 *vt = (v4x4 *)data;
461 assert(bsize == BLOCK_4X4);
462 node->part_variances = &vt->part_variances;
463 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) node->split[i] = &vt->split[i];
464 break;
465 }
466 }
467}
468
469// Set variance values given sum square error, sum error, count.
470static void fill_variance(uint32_t s2, int32_t s, int c, var *v) {
471 v->sum_square_error = s2;
472 v->sum_error = s;
473 v->log2_count = c;
474}
475
476static void get_variance(var *v) {
477 v->variance =
478 (int)(256 * (v->sum_square_error -
479 (uint32_t)(((int64_t)v->sum_error * v->sum_error) >>
480 v->log2_count)) >>
481 v->log2_count);
482}
483
484static void sum_2_variances(const var *a, const var *b, var *r) {
485 assert(a->log2_count == b->log2_count);
486 fill_variance(a->sum_square_error + b->sum_square_error,
487 a->sum_error + b->sum_error, a->log2_count + 1, r);
488}
489
490static void fill_variance_tree(void *data, BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
491 variance_node node;
492 memset(&node, 0, sizeof(node));
493 tree_to_node(data, bsize, &node);
494 sum_2_variances(node.split[0], node.split[1], &node.part_variances->horz[0]);
495 sum_2_variances(node.split[2], node.split[3], &node.part_variances->horz[1]);
496 sum_2_variances(node.split[0], node.split[2], &node.part_variances->vert[0]);
497 sum_2_variances(node.split[1], node.split[3], &node.part_variances->vert[1]);
498 sum_2_variances(&node.part_variances->vert[0], &node.part_variances->vert[1],
499 &node.part_variances->none);
500}
501
502static int set_vt_partitioning(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
503 MACROBLOCKD *const xd, void *data,
504 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row, int mi_col,
505 int64_t threshold, BLOCK_SIZE bsize_min,
506 int force_split) {
507 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
508 variance_node vt;
509 const int block_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
510 const int block_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
511
512 assert(block_height == block_width);
513 tree_to_node(data, bsize, &vt);
514
515 if (force_split == 1) return 0;
516
517 // For bsize=bsize_min (16x16/8x8 for 8x8/4x4 downsampling), select if
518 // variance is below threshold, otherwise split will be selected.
519 // No check for vert/horiz split as too few samples for variance.
520 if (bsize == bsize_min) {
521 // Variance already computed to set the force_split.
522 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm)) get_variance(&vt.part_variances->none);
523 if (mi_col + block_width / 2 < cm->mi_cols &&
524 mi_row + block_height / 2 < cm->mi_rows &&
525 vt.part_variances->none.variance < threshold) {
526 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
527 return 1;
528 }
529 return 0;
530 } else if (bsize > bsize_min) {
531 // Variance already computed to set the force_split.
532 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm)) get_variance(&vt.part_variances->none);
533 // For key frame: take split for bsize above 32X32 or very high variance.
534 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm) &&
535 (bsize > BLOCK_32X32 ||
536 vt.part_variances->none.variance > (threshold << 4))) {
537 return 0;
538 }
539 // If variance is low, take the bsize (no split).
540 if (mi_col + block_width / 2 < cm->mi_cols &&
541 mi_row + block_height / 2 < cm->mi_rows &&
542 vt.part_variances->none.variance < threshold) {
543 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
544 return 1;
545 }
546
547 // Check vertical split.
548 if (mi_row + block_height / 2 < cm->mi_rows) {
549 BLOCK_SIZE subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_VERT);
550 get_variance(&vt.part_variances->vert[0]);
551 get_variance(&vt.part_variances->vert[1]);
552 if (vt.part_variances->vert[0].variance < threshold &&
553 vt.part_variances->vert[1].variance < threshold &&
554 get_plane_block_size(subsize, &xd->plane[1]) < BLOCK_INVALID) {
555 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize);
556 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col + block_width / 2, subsize);
557 return 1;
558 }
559 }
560 // Check horizontal split.
561 if (mi_col + block_width / 2 < cm->mi_cols) {
562 BLOCK_SIZE subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_HORZ);
563 get_variance(&vt.part_variances->horz[0]);
564 get_variance(&vt.part_variances->horz[1]);
565 if (vt.part_variances->horz[0].variance < threshold &&
566 vt.part_variances->horz[1].variance < threshold &&
567 get_plane_block_size(subsize, &xd->plane[1]) < BLOCK_INVALID) {
568 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize);
569 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row + block_height / 2, mi_col, subsize);
570 return 1;
571 }
572 }
573
574 return 0;
575 }
576 return 0;
577}
578
579static int64_t scale_part_thresh_sumdiff(int64_t threshold_base, int speed,
580 int width, int height,
581 int content_state) {
582 if (speed >= 8) {
583 if (width <= 640 && height <= 480)
584 return (5 * threshold_base) >> 2;
585 else if ((content_state == kLowSadLowSumdiff) ||
586 (content_state == kHighSadLowSumdiff) ||
587 (content_state == kLowVarHighSumdiff))
588 return (5 * threshold_base) >> 2;
589 } else if (speed == 7) {
590 if ((content_state == kLowSadLowSumdiff) ||
591 (content_state == kHighSadLowSumdiff) ||
592 (content_state == kLowVarHighSumdiff)) {
593 return (5 * threshold_base) >> 2;
594 }
595 }
596 return threshold_base;
597}
598
599// Set the variance split thresholds for following the block sizes:
600// 0 - threshold_64x64, 1 - threshold_32x32, 2 - threshold_16x16,
601// 3 - vbp_threshold_8x8. vbp_threshold_8x8 (to split to 4x4 partition) is
602// currently only used on key frame.
603static void set_vbp_thresholds(VP9_COMP *cpi, int64_t thresholds[], int q,
604 int content_state) {
605 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
606 const int is_key_frame = frame_is_intra_only(cm);
607 const int threshold_multiplier =
608 is_key_frame ? 20 : cpi->sf.variance_part_thresh_mult;
609 int64_t threshold_base =
610 (int64_t)(threshold_multiplier * cpi->y_dequant[q][1]);
611
612 if (is_key_frame) {
613 thresholds[0] = threshold_base;
614 thresholds[1] = threshold_base >> 2;
615 thresholds[2] = threshold_base >> 2;
616 thresholds[3] = threshold_base << 2;
617 } else {
618 // Increase base variance threshold based on estimated noise level.
619 if (cpi->noise_estimate.enabled && cm->width >= 640 && cm->height >= 480) {
620 NOISE_LEVEL noise_level =
621 vp9_noise_estimate_extract_level(&cpi->noise_estimate);
622 if (noise_level == kHigh)
623 threshold_base = 3 * threshold_base;
624 else if (noise_level == kMedium)
625 threshold_base = threshold_base << 1;
626 else if (noise_level < kLow)
627 threshold_base = (7 * threshold_base) >> 3;
628 }
629#if CONFIG_VP9_TEMPORAL_DENOISING
630 if (cpi->oxcf.noise_sensitivity > 0 && denoise_svc(cpi) &&
631 cpi->oxcf.speed > 5 && cpi->denoiser.denoising_level >= kDenLow)
632 threshold_base =
633 vp9_scale_part_thresh(threshold_base, cpi->denoiser.denoising_level,
634 content_state, cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id);
635 else
636 threshold_base =
637 scale_part_thresh_sumdiff(threshold_base, cpi->oxcf.speed, cm->width,
638 cm->height, content_state);
639#else
640 // Increase base variance threshold based on content_state/sum_diff level.
641 threshold_base = scale_part_thresh_sumdiff(
642 threshold_base, cpi->oxcf.speed, cm->width, cm->height, content_state);
643#endif
644 thresholds[0] = threshold_base;
645 thresholds[2] = threshold_base << cpi->oxcf.speed;
646 if (cm->width >= 1280 && cm->height >= 720 && cpi->oxcf.speed < 7)
647 thresholds[2] = thresholds[2] << 1;
648 if (cm->width <= 352 && cm->height <= 288) {
649 thresholds[0] = threshold_base >> 3;
650 thresholds[1] = threshold_base >> 1;
651 thresholds[2] = threshold_base << 3;
652 if (cpi->rc.avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] > 220)
653 thresholds[2] = thresholds[2] << 2;
654 else if (cpi->rc.avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] > 200)
655 thresholds[2] = thresholds[2] << 1;
656 } else if (cm->width < 1280 && cm->height < 720) {
657 thresholds[1] = (5 * threshold_base) >> 2;
658 } else if (cm->width < 1920 && cm->height < 1080) {
659 thresholds[1] = threshold_base << 1;
660 } else {
661 thresholds[1] = (5 * threshold_base) >> 1;
662 }
663 if (cpi->sf.disable_16x16part_nonkey) thresholds[2] = INT64_MAX;
664 }
665}
666
667void vp9_set_variance_partition_thresholds(VP9_COMP *cpi, int q,
668 int content_state) {
669 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
670 SPEED_FEATURES *const sf = &cpi->sf;
671 const int is_key_frame = frame_is_intra_only(cm);
672 if (sf->partition_search_type != VAR_BASED_PARTITION &&
673 sf->partition_search_type != REFERENCE_PARTITION) {
674 return;
675 } else {
676 set_vbp_thresholds(cpi, cpi->vbp_thresholds, q, content_state);
677 // The thresholds below are not changed locally.
678 if (is_key_frame) {
679 cpi->vbp_threshold_sad = 0;
680 cpi->vbp_threshold_copy = 0;
681 cpi->vbp_bsize_min = BLOCK_8X8;
682 } else {
683 if (cm->width <= 352 && cm->height <= 288)
684 cpi->vbp_threshold_sad = 10;
685 else
686 cpi->vbp_threshold_sad = (cpi->y_dequant[q][1] << 1) > 1000
687 ? (cpi->y_dequant[q][1] << 1)
688 : 1000;
689 cpi->vbp_bsize_min = BLOCK_16X16;
690 if (cm->width <= 352 && cm->height <= 288)
691 cpi->vbp_threshold_copy = 4000;
692 else if (cm->width <= 640 && cm->height <= 360)
693 cpi->vbp_threshold_copy = 8000;
694 else
695 cpi->vbp_threshold_copy = (cpi->y_dequant[q][1] << 3) > 8000
696 ? (cpi->y_dequant[q][1] << 3)
697 : 8000;
698 if (cpi->rc.high_source_sad ||
699 (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.high_source_sad_superframe)) {
700 cpi->vbp_threshold_sad = 0;
701 cpi->vbp_threshold_copy = 0;
702 }
703 }
704 cpi->vbp_threshold_minmax = 15 + (q >> 3);
705 }
706}
707
708// Compute the minmax over the 8x8 subblocks.
709static int compute_minmax_8x8(const uint8_t *s, int sp, const uint8_t *d,
710 int dp, int x16_idx, int y16_idx,
711#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
712 int highbd_flag,
713#endif
714 int pixels_wide, int pixels_high) {
715 int k;
716 int minmax_max = 0;
717 int minmax_min = 255;
718 // Loop over the 4 8x8 subblocks.
719 for (k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
720 int x8_idx = x16_idx + ((k & 1) << 3);
721 int y8_idx = y16_idx + ((k >> 1) << 3);
722 int min = 0;
723 int max = 0;
724 if (x8_idx < pixels_wide && y8_idx < pixels_high) {
725#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
726 if (highbd_flag & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
727 vpx_highbd_minmax_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp,
728 d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx, dp, &min, &max);
729 } else {
730 vpx_minmax_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp, d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx,
731 dp, &min, &max);
732 }
733#else
734 vpx_minmax_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp, d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx, dp,
735 &min, &max);
736#endif
737 if ((max - min) > minmax_max) minmax_max = (max - min);
738 if ((max - min) < minmax_min) minmax_min = (max - min);
739 }
740 }
741 return (minmax_max - minmax_min);
742}
743
744static void fill_variance_4x4avg(const uint8_t *s, int sp, const uint8_t *d,
745 int dp, int x8_idx, int y8_idx, v8x8 *vst,
746#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
747 int highbd_flag,
748#endif
749 int pixels_wide, int pixels_high,
750 int is_key_frame) {
751 int k;
752 for (k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
753 int x4_idx = x8_idx + ((k & 1) << 2);
754 int y4_idx = y8_idx + ((k >> 1) << 2);
755 unsigned int sse = 0;
756 int sum = 0;
757 if (x4_idx < pixels_wide && y4_idx < pixels_high) {
758 int s_avg;
759 int d_avg = 128;
760#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
761 if (highbd_flag & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
762 s_avg = vpx_highbd_avg_4x4(s + y4_idx * sp + x4_idx, sp);
763 if (!is_key_frame)
764 d_avg = vpx_highbd_avg_4x4(d + y4_idx * dp + x4_idx, dp);
765 } else {
766 s_avg = vpx_avg_4x4(s + y4_idx * sp + x4_idx, sp);
767 if (!is_key_frame) d_avg = vpx_avg_4x4(d + y4_idx * dp + x4_idx, dp);
768 }
769#else
770 s_avg = vpx_avg_4x4(s + y4_idx * sp + x4_idx, sp);
771 if (!is_key_frame) d_avg = vpx_avg_4x4(d + y4_idx * dp + x4_idx, dp);
772#endif
773 sum = s_avg - d_avg;
774 sse = sum * sum;
775 }
776 fill_variance(sse, sum, 0, &vst->split[k].part_variances.none);
777 }
778}
779
780static void fill_variance_8x8avg(const uint8_t *s, int sp, const uint8_t *d,
781 int dp, int x16_idx, int y16_idx, v16x16 *vst,
782#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
783 int highbd_flag,
784#endif
785 int pixels_wide, int pixels_high,
786 int is_key_frame) {
787 int k;
788 for (k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
789 int x8_idx = x16_idx + ((k & 1) << 3);
790 int y8_idx = y16_idx + ((k >> 1) << 3);
791 unsigned int sse = 0;
792 int sum = 0;
793 if (x8_idx < pixels_wide && y8_idx < pixels_high) {
794 int s_avg;
795 int d_avg = 128;
796#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
797 if (highbd_flag & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
798 s_avg = vpx_highbd_avg_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp);
799 if (!is_key_frame)
800 d_avg = vpx_highbd_avg_8x8(d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx, dp);
801 } else {
802 s_avg = vpx_avg_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp);
803 if (!is_key_frame) d_avg = vpx_avg_8x8(d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx, dp);
804 }
805#else
806 s_avg = vpx_avg_8x8(s + y8_idx * sp + x8_idx, sp);
807 if (!is_key_frame) d_avg = vpx_avg_8x8(d + y8_idx * dp + x8_idx, dp);
808#endif
809 sum = s_avg - d_avg;
810 sse = sum * sum;
811 }
812 fill_variance(sse, sum, 0, &vst->split[k].part_variances.none);
813 }
814}
815
816// Check if most of the superblock is skin content, and if so, force split to
817// 32x32, and set x->sb_is_skin for use in mode selection.
818static int skin_sb_split(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, const int low_res,
819 int mi_row, int mi_col, int *force_split) {
820 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
821#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
822 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) return 0;
823#endif
824 // Avoid checking superblocks on/near boundary and avoid low resolutions.
825 // Note superblock may still pick 64X64 if y_sad is very small
826 // (i.e., y_sad < cpi->vbp_threshold_sad) below. For now leave this as is.
827 if (!low_res && (mi_col >= 8 && mi_col + 8 < cm->mi_cols && mi_row >= 8 &&
828 mi_row + 8 < cm->mi_rows)) {
829 int num_16x16_skin = 0;
830 int num_16x16_nonskin = 0;
831 uint8_t *ysignal = x->plane[0].src.buf;
832 uint8_t *usignal = x->plane[1].src.buf;
833 uint8_t *vsignal = x->plane[2].src.buf;
834 int sp = x->plane[0].src.stride;
835 int spuv = x->plane[1].src.stride;
836 const int block_index = mi_row * cm->mi_cols + mi_col;
837 const int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[BLOCK_64X64];
838 const int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[BLOCK_64X64];
839 const int xmis = VPXMIN(cm->mi_cols - mi_col, bw);
840 const int ymis = VPXMIN(cm->mi_rows - mi_row, bh);
841 // Loop through the 16x16 sub-blocks.
842 int i, j;
843 for (i = 0; i < ymis; i += 2) {
844 for (j = 0; j < xmis; j += 2) {
845 int bl_index = block_index + i * cm->mi_cols + j;
846 int is_skin = cpi->skin_map[bl_index];
847 num_16x16_skin += is_skin;
848 num_16x16_nonskin += (1 - is_skin);
849 if (num_16x16_nonskin > 3) {
850 // Exit loop if at least 4 of the 16x16 blocks are not skin.
851 i = ymis;
852 break;
853 }
854 ysignal += 16;
855 usignal += 8;
856 vsignal += 8;
857 }
858 ysignal += (sp << 4) - 64;
859 usignal += (spuv << 3) - 32;
860 vsignal += (spuv << 3) - 32;
861 }
862 if (num_16x16_skin > 12) {
863 *force_split = 1;
864 return 1;
865 }
866 }
867 return 0;
868}
869
870static void set_low_temp_var_flag(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, MACROBLOCKD *xd,
871 v64x64 *vt, int64_t thresholds[],
872 MV_REFERENCE_FRAME ref_frame_partition,
873 int mi_col, int mi_row) {
874 int i, j;
875 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
876 const int mv_thr = cm->width > 640 ? 8 : 4;
877 // Check temporal variance for bsize >= 16x16, if LAST_FRAME was selected and
878 // int_pro mv is small. If the temporal variance is small set the flag
879 // variance_low for the block. The variance threshold can be adjusted, the
880 // higher the more aggressive.
881 if (ref_frame_partition == LAST_FRAME &&
882 (cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var == 1 ||
883 (xd->mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv.col < mv_thr &&
884 xd->mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv.col > -mv_thr &&
885 xd->mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv.row < mv_thr &&
886 xd->mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv.row > -mv_thr))) {
887 if (xd->mi[0]->sb_type == BLOCK_64X64) {
888 if ((vt->part_variances).none.variance < (thresholds[0] >> 1))
889 x->variance_low[0] = 1;
890 } else if (xd->mi[0]->sb_type == BLOCK_64X32) {
891 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
892 if (vt->part_variances.horz[i].variance < (thresholds[0] >> 2))
893 x->variance_low[i + 1] = 1;
894 }
895 } else if (xd->mi[0]->sb_type == BLOCK_32X64) {
896 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
897 if (vt->part_variances.vert[i].variance < (thresholds[0] >> 2))
898 x->variance_low[i + 3] = 1;
899 }
900 } else {
901 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
902 const int idx[4][2] = { { 0, 0 }, { 0, 4 }, { 4, 0 }, { 4, 4 } };
903 const int idx_str =
904 cm->mi_stride * (mi_row + idx[i][0]) + mi_col + idx[i][1];
905 MODE_INFO **this_mi = cm->mi_grid_visible + idx_str;
906
907 if (cm->mi_cols <= mi_col + idx[i][1] ||
908 cm->mi_rows <= mi_row + idx[i][0])
909 continue;
910
911 if ((*this_mi)->sb_type == BLOCK_32X32) {
912 int64_t threshold_32x32 = (cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var == 1 ||
913 cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var == 3)
914 ? ((5 * thresholds[1]) >> 3)
915 : (thresholds[1] >> 1);
916 if (vt->split[i].part_variances.none.variance < threshold_32x32)
917 x->variance_low[i + 5] = 1;
918 } else if (cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var >= 2) {
919 // For 32x16 and 16x32 blocks, the flag is set on each 16x16 block
920 // inside.
921 if ((*this_mi)->sb_type == BLOCK_16X16 ||
922 (*this_mi)->sb_type == BLOCK_32X16 ||
923 (*this_mi)->sb_type == BLOCK_16X32) {
924 for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
925 if (vt->split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance <
926 (thresholds[2] >> 8))
927 x->variance_low[(i << 2) + j + 9] = 1;
928 }
929 }
930 }
931 }
932 }
933 }
934}
935
936static void copy_partitioning_helper(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x,
937 MACROBLOCKD *xd, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
938 int mi_row, int mi_col) {
939 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
940 BLOCK_SIZE *prev_part = cpi->prev_partition;
941 int start_pos = mi_row * cm->mi_stride + mi_col;
942
943 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
944 const int bs = (1 << bsl) >> 2;
945 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
946 PARTITION_TYPE partition;
947
948 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
949
950 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][prev_part[start_pos]];
951 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, partition);
952
953 if (subsize < BLOCK_8X8) {
954 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
955 } else {
956 switch (partition) {
957 case PARTITION_NONE:
958 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
959 break;
960 case PARTITION_HORZ:
961 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize);
962 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row + bs, mi_col, subsize);
963 break;
964 case PARTITION_VERT:
965 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize);
966 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col + bs, subsize);
967 break;
968 default:
969 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
970 copy_partitioning_helper(cpi, x, xd, subsize, mi_row, mi_col);
971 copy_partitioning_helper(cpi, x, xd, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col);
972 copy_partitioning_helper(cpi, x, xd, subsize, mi_row, mi_col + bs);
973 copy_partitioning_helper(cpi, x, xd, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col + bs);
974 break;
975 }
976 }
977}
978
979static int copy_partitioning(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, MACROBLOCKD *xd,
980 int mi_row, int mi_col, int segment_id,
981 int sb_offset) {
982 int svc_copy_allowed = 1;
983 int frames_since_key_thresh = 1;
984 if (cpi->use_svc) {
985 // For SVC, don't allow copy if base spatial layer is key frame, or if
986 // frame is not a temporal enhancement layer frame.
987 int layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(0, cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id,
988 cpi->svc.number_temporal_layers);
989 const LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &cpi->svc.layer_context[layer];
990 if (lc->is_key_frame || !cpi->svc.non_reference_frame) svc_copy_allowed = 0;
991 frames_since_key_thresh = cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers << 1;
992 }
993 if (cpi->rc.frames_since_key > frames_since_key_thresh && svc_copy_allowed &&
994 !cpi->resize_pending && segment_id == CR_SEGMENT_ID_BASE &&
995 cpi->prev_segment_id[sb_offset] == CR_SEGMENT_ID_BASE &&
996 cpi->copied_frame_cnt[sb_offset] < cpi->max_copied_frame) {
997 if (cpi->prev_partition != NULL) {
998 copy_partitioning_helper(cpi, x, xd, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
999 cpi->copied_frame_cnt[sb_offset] += 1;
1000 memcpy(x->variance_low, &(cpi->prev_variance_low[sb_offset * 25]),
1001 sizeof(x->variance_low));
1002 return 1;
1003 }
1004 }
1005
1006 return 0;
1007}
1008
1009static int scale_partitioning_svc(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, MACROBLOCKD *xd,
1010 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row, int mi_col,
1011 int mi_row_high, int mi_col_high) {
1012 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1013 SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
1014 BLOCK_SIZE *prev_part = svc->prev_partition_svc;
1015 // Variables with _high are for higher resolution.
1016 int bsize_high = 0;
1017 int subsize_high = 0;
1018 const int bsl_high = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
1019 const int bs_high = (1 << bsl_high) >> 2;
1020 const int has_rows = (mi_row_high + bs_high) < cm->mi_rows;
1021 const int has_cols = (mi_col_high + bs_high) < cm->mi_cols;
1022
1023 const int row_boundary_block_scale_factor[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 13, 13, 13, 1, 0,
1024 1, 1, 0, 1, 1,
1025 0, 1, 0 };
1026 const int col_boundary_block_scale_factor[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 13, 13, 13, 2, 2,
1027 0, 2, 2, 0, 2,
1028 2, 0, 0 };
1029 int start_pos;
1030 BLOCK_SIZE bsize_low;
1031 PARTITION_TYPE partition_high;
1032
1033 if (mi_row_high >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col_high >= cm->mi_cols) return 0;
1034 if (mi_row >= svc->mi_rows[svc->spatial_layer_id - 1] ||
1035 mi_col >= svc->mi_cols[svc->spatial_layer_id - 1])
1036 return 0;
1037
1038 // Find corresponding (mi_col/mi_row) block down-scaled by 2x2.
1039 start_pos = mi_row * (svc->mi_stride[svc->spatial_layer_id - 1]) + mi_col;
1040 bsize_low = prev_part[start_pos];
1041 // The block size is too big for boundaries. Do variance based partitioning.
1042 if ((!has_rows || !has_cols) && bsize_low > BLOCK_16X16) return 1;
1043
1044 // For reference frames: return 1 (do variance-based partitioning) if the
1045 // superblock is not low source sad and lower-resoln bsize is below 32x32.
1046 if (!cpi->svc.non_reference_frame && !x->skip_low_source_sad &&
1047 bsize_low < BLOCK_32X32)
1048 return 1;
1049
1050 // Scale up block size by 2x2. Force 64x64 for size larger than 32x32.
1051 if (bsize_low < BLOCK_32X32) {
1052 bsize_high = bsize_low + 3;
1053 } else if (bsize_low >= BLOCK_32X32) {
1054 bsize_high = BLOCK_64X64;
1055 }
1056 // Scale up blocks on boundary.
1057 if (!has_cols && has_rows) {
1058 bsize_high = bsize_low + row_boundary_block_scale_factor[bsize_low];
1059 } else if (has_cols && !has_rows) {
1060 bsize_high = bsize_low + col_boundary_block_scale_factor[bsize_low];
1061 } else if (!has_cols && !has_rows) {
1062 bsize_high = bsize_low;
1063 }
1064
1065 partition_high = partition_lookup[bsl_high][bsize_high];
1066 subsize_high = get_subsize(bsize, partition_high);
1067
1068 if (subsize_high < BLOCK_8X8) {
1069 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high, mi_col_high, bsize_high);
1070 } else {
1071 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
1072 const int bs = (1 << bsl) >> 2;
1073 switch (partition_high) {
1074 case PARTITION_NONE:
1075 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high, mi_col_high, bsize_high);
1076 break;
1077 case PARTITION_HORZ:
1078 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high, mi_col_high, subsize_high);
1079 if (subsize_high < BLOCK_64X64)
1080 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high + bs_high, mi_col_high,
1081 subsize_high);
1082 break;
1083 case PARTITION_VERT:
1084 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high, mi_col_high, subsize_high);
1085 if (subsize_high < BLOCK_64X64)
1086 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row_high, mi_col_high + bs_high,
1087 subsize_high);
1088 break;
1089 default:
1090 assert(partition_high == PARTITION_SPLIT);
1091 if (scale_partitioning_svc(cpi, x, xd, subsize_high, mi_row, mi_col,
1092 mi_row_high, mi_col_high))
1093 return 1;
1094 if (scale_partitioning_svc(cpi, x, xd, subsize_high, mi_row + (bs >> 1),
1095 mi_col, mi_row_high + bs_high, mi_col_high))
1096 return 1;
1097 if (scale_partitioning_svc(cpi, x, xd, subsize_high, mi_row,
1098 mi_col + (bs >> 1), mi_row_high,
1099 mi_col_high + bs_high))
1100 return 1;
1101 if (scale_partitioning_svc(cpi, x, xd, subsize_high, mi_row + (bs >> 1),
1102 mi_col + (bs >> 1), mi_row_high + bs_high,
1103 mi_col_high + bs_high))
1104 return 1;
1105 break;
1106 }
1107 }
1108
1109 return 0;
1110}
1111
1112static void update_partition_svc(VP9_COMP *cpi, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row,
1113 int mi_col) {
1114 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1115 BLOCK_SIZE *prev_part = cpi->svc.prev_partition_svc;
1116 int start_pos = mi_row * cm->mi_stride + mi_col;
1117 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
1118 const int bs = (1 << bsl) >> 2;
1119 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
1120 PARTITION_TYPE partition;
1121 const MODE_INFO *mi = NULL;
1122 int xx, yy;
1123
1124 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
1125
1126 mi = cm->mi_grid_visible[start_pos];
1127 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][mi->sb_type];
1128 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, partition);
1129 if (subsize < BLOCK_8X8) {
1130 prev_part[start_pos] = bsize;
1131 } else {
1132 switch (partition) {
1133 case PARTITION_NONE:
1134 prev_part[start_pos] = bsize;
1135 if (bsize == BLOCK_64X64) {
1136 for (xx = 0; xx < 8; xx += 4)
1137 for (yy = 0; yy < 8; yy += 4) {
1138 if ((mi_row + xx < cm->mi_rows) && (mi_col + yy < cm->mi_cols))
1139 prev_part[start_pos + xx * cm->mi_stride + yy] = bsize;
1140 }
1141 }
1142 break;
1143 case PARTITION_HORZ:
1144 prev_part[start_pos] = subsize;
1145 if (mi_row + bs < cm->mi_rows)
1146 prev_part[start_pos + bs * cm->mi_stride] = subsize;
1147 break;
1148 case PARTITION_VERT:
1149 prev_part[start_pos] = subsize;
1150 if (mi_col + bs < cm->mi_cols) prev_part[start_pos + bs] = subsize;
1151 break;
1152 default:
1153 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
1154 update_partition_svc(cpi, subsize, mi_row, mi_col);
1155 update_partition_svc(cpi, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col);
1156 update_partition_svc(cpi, subsize, mi_row, mi_col + bs);
1157 update_partition_svc(cpi, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col + bs);
1158 break;
1159 }
1160 }
1161}
1162
1163static void update_prev_partition_helper(VP9_COMP *cpi, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
1164 int mi_row, int mi_col) {
1165 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1166 BLOCK_SIZE *prev_part = cpi->prev_partition;
1167 int start_pos = mi_row * cm->mi_stride + mi_col;
1168 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
1169 const int bs = (1 << bsl) >> 2;
1170 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
1171 PARTITION_TYPE partition;
1172 const MODE_INFO *mi = NULL;
1173
1174 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
1175
1176 mi = cm->mi_grid_visible[start_pos];
1177 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][mi->sb_type];
1178 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, partition);
1179 if (subsize < BLOCK_8X8) {
1180 prev_part[start_pos] = bsize;
1181 } else {
1182 switch (partition) {
1183 case PARTITION_NONE: prev_part[start_pos] = bsize; break;
1184 case PARTITION_HORZ:
1185 prev_part[start_pos] = subsize;
1186 if (mi_row + bs < cm->mi_rows)
1187 prev_part[start_pos + bs * cm->mi_stride] = subsize;
1188 break;
1189 case PARTITION_VERT:
1190 prev_part[start_pos] = subsize;
1191 if (mi_col + bs < cm->mi_cols) prev_part[start_pos + bs] = subsize;
1192 break;
1193 default:
1194 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
1195 update_prev_partition_helper(cpi, subsize, mi_row, mi_col);
1196 update_prev_partition_helper(cpi, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col);
1197 update_prev_partition_helper(cpi, subsize, mi_row, mi_col + bs);
1198 update_prev_partition_helper(cpi, subsize, mi_row + bs, mi_col + bs);
1199 break;
1200 }
1201 }
1202}
1203
1204static void update_prev_partition(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, int segment_id,
1205 int mi_row, int mi_col, int sb_offset) {
1206 update_prev_partition_helper(cpi, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
1207 cpi->prev_segment_id[sb_offset] = segment_id;
1208 memcpy(&(cpi->prev_variance_low[sb_offset * 25]), x->variance_low,
1209 sizeof(x->variance_low));
1210 // Reset the counter for copy partitioning
1211 cpi->copied_frame_cnt[sb_offset] = 0;
1212}
1213
1214static void chroma_check(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, int bsize,
1215 unsigned int y_sad, int is_key_frame,
1216 int scene_change_detected) {
1217 int i;
1218 MACROBLOCKD *xd = &x->e_mbd;
1219 int shift = 2;
1220
1221 if (is_key_frame) return;
1222
1223 // For speed > 8, avoid the chroma check if y_sad is above threshold.
1224 if (cpi->oxcf.speed > 8) {
1225 if (y_sad > cpi->vbp_thresholds[1] &&
1226 (!cpi->noise_estimate.enabled ||
1227 vp9_noise_estimate_extract_level(&cpi->noise_estimate) < kMedium))
1228 return;
1229 }
1230
1231 if (cpi->oxcf.content == VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN && scene_change_detected)
1232 shift = 5;
1233
1234 for (i = 1; i <= 2; ++i) {
1235 unsigned int uv_sad = UINT_MAX;
1236 struct macroblock_plane *p = &x->plane[i];
1237 struct macroblockd_plane *pd = &xd->plane[i];
1238 const BLOCK_SIZE bs = get_plane_block_size(bsize, pd);
1239
1240 if (bs != BLOCK_INVALID)
1241 uv_sad = cpi->fn_ptr[bs].sdf(p->src.buf, p->src.stride, pd->dst.buf,
1242 pd->dst.stride);
1243
1244 // TODO(marpan): Investigate if we should lower this threshold if
1245 // superblock is detected as skin.
1246 x->color_sensitivity[i - 1] = uv_sad > (y_sad >> shift);
1247 }
1248}
1249
1250static uint64_t avg_source_sad(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x, int shift,
1251 int sb_offset) {
1252 unsigned int tmp_sse;
1253 uint64_t tmp_sad;
1254 unsigned int tmp_variance;
1255 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = BLOCK_64X64;
1256 uint8_t *src_y = cpi->Source->y_buffer;
1257 int src_ystride = cpi->Source->y_stride;
1258 uint8_t *last_src_y = cpi->Last_Source->y_buffer;
1259 int last_src_ystride = cpi->Last_Source->y_stride;
1260 uint64_t avg_source_sad_threshold = 10000;
1261 uint64_t avg_source_sad_threshold2 = 12000;
1262#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1263 if (cpi->common.use_highbitdepth) return 0;
1264#endif
1265 src_y += shift;
1266 last_src_y += shift;
1267 tmp_sad =
1268 cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].sdf(src_y, src_ystride, last_src_y, last_src_ystride);
1269 tmp_variance = vpx_variance64x64(src_y, src_ystride, last_src_y,
1270 last_src_ystride, &tmp_sse);
1271 // Note: tmp_sse - tmp_variance = ((sum * sum) >> 12)
1272 if (tmp_sad < avg_source_sad_threshold)
1273 x->content_state_sb = ((tmp_sse - tmp_variance) < 25) ? kLowSadLowSumdiff
1274 : kLowSadHighSumdiff;
1275 else
1276 x->content_state_sb = ((tmp_sse - tmp_variance) < 25) ? kHighSadLowSumdiff
1277 : kHighSadHighSumdiff;
1278
1279 // Detect large lighting change.
1280 if (cpi->oxcf.content != VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN &&
1281 cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CBR && tmp_variance < (tmp_sse >> 3) &&
1282 (tmp_sse - tmp_variance) > 10000)
1283 x->content_state_sb = kLowVarHighSumdiff;
1284 else if (tmp_sad > (avg_source_sad_threshold << 1))
1285 x->content_state_sb = kVeryHighSad;
1286
1287 if (cpi->content_state_sb_fd != NULL) {
1288 if (tmp_sad < avg_source_sad_threshold2) {
1289 // Cap the increment to 255.
1290 if (cpi->content_state_sb_fd[sb_offset] < 255)
1291 cpi->content_state_sb_fd[sb_offset]++;
1292 } else {
1293 cpi->content_state_sb_fd[sb_offset] = 0;
1294 }
1295 }
1296 if (tmp_sad == 0) x->zero_temp_sad_source = 1;
1297 return tmp_sad;
1298}
1299
1300// This function chooses partitioning based on the variance between source and
1301// reconstructed last, where variance is computed for down-sampled inputs.
1302static int choose_partitioning(VP9_COMP *cpi, const TileInfo *const tile,
1303 MACROBLOCK *x, int mi_row, int mi_col) {
1304 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1305 MACROBLOCKD *xd = &x->e_mbd;
1306 int i, j, k, m;
1307 v64x64 vt;
1308 v16x16 *vt2 = NULL;
1309 int force_split[21];
1310 int avg_32x32;
1311 int max_var_32x32 = 0;
1312 int min_var_32x32 = INT_MAX;
1313 int var_32x32;
1314 int avg_16x16[4];
1315 int maxvar_16x16[4];
1316 int minvar_16x16[4];
1317 int64_t threshold_4x4avg;
1318 NOISE_LEVEL noise_level = kLow;
1319 int content_state = 0;
1320 uint8_t *s;
1321 const uint8_t *d;
1322 int sp;
1323 int dp;
1324 int compute_minmax_variance = 1;
1325 unsigned int y_sad = UINT_MAX;
1326 BLOCK_SIZE bsize = BLOCK_64X64;
1327 // Ref frame used in partitioning.
1328 MV_REFERENCE_FRAME ref_frame_partition = LAST_FRAME;
1329 int pixels_wide = 64, pixels_high = 64;
1330 int64_t thresholds[4] = { cpi->vbp_thresholds[0], cpi->vbp_thresholds[1],
1331 cpi->vbp_thresholds[2], cpi->vbp_thresholds[3] };
1332 int scene_change_detected =
1333 cpi->rc.high_source_sad ||
1334 (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.high_source_sad_superframe);
1335 int force_64_split = scene_change_detected ||
1336 (cpi->oxcf.content == VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN &&
1337 cpi->compute_source_sad_onepass &&
1338 cpi->sf.use_source_sad && !x->zero_temp_sad_source);
1339
1340 // For the variance computation under SVC mode, we treat the frame as key if
1341 // the reference (base layer frame) is key frame (i.e., is_key_frame == 1).
1342 int is_key_frame =
1343 (frame_is_intra_only(cm) ||
1344 (is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi) &&
1345 cpi->svc.layer_context[cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame));
1346 // Always use 4x4 partition for key frame.
1347 const int use_4x4_partition = frame_is_intra_only(cm);
1348 const int low_res = (cm->width <= 352 && cm->height <= 288);
1349 int variance4x4downsample[16];
1350 int segment_id;
1351 int sb_offset = (cm->mi_stride >> 3) * (mi_row >> 3) + (mi_col >> 3);
1352
1353 // For SVC: check if LAST frame is NULL or if the resolution of LAST is
1354 // different than the current frame resolution, and if so, treat this frame
1355 // as a key frame, for the purpose of the superblock partitioning.
1356 // LAST == NULL can happen in some cases where enhancement spatial layers are
1357 // enabled dyanmically in the stream and the only reference is the spatial
1358 // reference (GOLDEN).
1359 if (cpi->use_svc) {
1360 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const ref = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, LAST_FRAME);
1361 if (ref == NULL || ref->y_crop_height != cm->height ||
1362 ref->y_crop_width != cm->width)
1363 is_key_frame = 1;
1364 }
1365
1366 set_offsets(cpi, tile, x, mi_row, mi_col, BLOCK_64X64);
1367 set_segment_index(cpi, x, mi_row, mi_col, BLOCK_64X64, 0);
1368 segment_id = xd->mi[0]->segment_id;
1369
1370 if (cpi->oxcf.speed >= 8 || (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.non_reference_frame))
1371 compute_minmax_variance = 0;
1372
1373 memset(x->variance_low, 0, sizeof(x->variance_low));
1374
1375 if (cpi->sf.use_source_sad && !is_key_frame) {
1376 int sb_offset2 = ((cm->mi_cols + 7) >> 3) * (mi_row >> 3) + (mi_col >> 3);
1377 content_state = x->content_state_sb;
1378 x->skip_low_source_sad = (content_state == kLowSadLowSumdiff ||
1379 content_state == kLowSadHighSumdiff)
1380 ? 1
1381 : 0;
1382 x->lowvar_highsumdiff = (content_state == kLowVarHighSumdiff) ? 1 : 0;
1383 if (cpi->content_state_sb_fd != NULL)
1384 x->last_sb_high_content = cpi->content_state_sb_fd[sb_offset2];
1385
1386 // For SVC on top spatial layer: use/scale the partition from
1387 // the lower spatial resolution if svc_use_lowres_part is enabled.
1388 if (cpi->sf.svc_use_lowres_part &&
1389 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 1 &&
1390 cpi->svc.prev_partition_svc != NULL && content_state != kVeryHighSad) {
1391 if (!scale_partitioning_svc(cpi, x, xd, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row >> 1,
1392 mi_col >> 1, mi_row, mi_col)) {
1393 if (cpi->sf.copy_partition_flag) {
1394 update_prev_partition(cpi, x, segment_id, mi_row, mi_col, sb_offset);
1395 }
1396 return 0;
1397 }
1398 }
1399 // If source_sad is low copy the partition without computing the y_sad.
1400 if (x->skip_low_source_sad && cpi->sf.copy_partition_flag &&
1401 !force_64_split &&
1402 copy_partitioning(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, segment_id, sb_offset)) {
1403 x->sb_use_mv_part = 1;
1404 if (cpi->sf.svc_use_lowres_part &&
1405 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 2)
1406 update_partition_svc(cpi, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
1407 return 0;
1408 }
1409 }
1410
1411 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ && cm->seg.enabled &&
1412 cyclic_refresh_segment_id_boosted(segment_id)) {
1413 int q = vp9_get_qindex(&cm->seg, segment_id, cm->base_qindex);
1414 set_vbp_thresholds(cpi, thresholds, q, content_state);
1415 } else {
1416 set_vbp_thresholds(cpi, thresholds, cm->base_qindex, content_state);
1417 }
1418 // Decrease 32x32 split threshold for screen on base layer, for scene
1419 // change/high motion frames.
1420 if (cpi->oxcf.content == VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN &&
1421 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == 0 && force_64_split)
1422 thresholds[1] = 3 * thresholds[1] >> 2;
1423
1424 // For non keyframes, disable 4x4 average for low resolution when speed = 8
1425 threshold_4x4avg = (cpi->oxcf.speed < 8) ? thresholds[1] << 1 : INT64_MAX;
1426
1427 if (xd->mb_to_right_edge < 0) pixels_wide += (xd->mb_to_right_edge >> 3);
1428 if (xd->mb_to_bottom_edge < 0) pixels_high += (xd->mb_to_bottom_edge >> 3);
1429
1430 s = x->plane[0].src.buf;
1431 sp = x->plane[0].src.stride;
1432
1433 // Index for force_split: 0 for 64x64, 1-4 for 32x32 blocks,
1434 // 5-20 for the 16x16 blocks.
1435 force_split[0] = force_64_split;
1436
1437 if (!is_key_frame) {
1438 // In the case of spatial/temporal scalable coding, the assumption here is
1439 // that the temporal reference frame will always be of type LAST_FRAME.
1440 // TODO(marpan): If that assumption is broken, we need to revisit this code.
1441 MODE_INFO *mi = xd->mi[0];
1442 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, LAST_FRAME);
1443
1444 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *yv12_g = NULL;
1445 unsigned int y_sad_g, y_sad_thr, y_sad_last;
1446 bsize = BLOCK_32X32 + (mi_col + 4 < cm->mi_cols) * 2 +
1447 (mi_row + 4 < cm->mi_rows);
1448
1449 assert(yv12 != NULL);
1450
1451 if (!(is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi) && cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id) ||
1452 cpi->svc.use_gf_temporal_ref_current_layer) {
1453 // For now, GOLDEN will not be used for non-zero spatial layers, since
1454 // it may not be a temporal reference.
1455 yv12_g = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, GOLDEN_FRAME);
1456 }
1457
1458 // Only compute y_sad_g (sad for golden reference) for speed < 8.
1459 if (cpi->oxcf.speed < 8 && yv12_g && yv12_g != yv12 &&
1460 (cpi->ref_frame_flags & VP9_GOLD_FLAG)) {
1461 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, yv12_g, mi_row, mi_col,
1462 &cm->frame_refs[GOLDEN_FRAME - 1].sf);
1463 y_sad_g = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].sdf(
1464 x->plane[0].src.buf, x->plane[0].src.stride, xd->plane[0].pre[0].buf,
1465 xd->plane[0].pre[0].stride);
1466 } else {
1467 y_sad_g = UINT_MAX;
1468 }
1469
1470 if (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 0 && cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_VBR &&
1471 cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref) {
1472 yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, ALTREF_FRAME);
1473 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, yv12, mi_row, mi_col,
1474 &cm->frame_refs[ALTREF_FRAME - 1].sf);
1475 mi->ref_frame[0] = ALTREF_FRAME;
1476 y_sad_g = UINT_MAX;
1477 } else {
1478 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, yv12, mi_row, mi_col,
1479 &cm->frame_refs[LAST_FRAME - 1].sf);
1480 mi->ref_frame[0] = LAST_FRAME;
1481 }
1482 mi->ref_frame[1] = NONE;
1483 mi->sb_type = BLOCK_64X64;
1484 mi->mv[0].as_int = 0;
1485 mi->interp_filter = BILINEAR;
1486
1487 if (cpi->oxcf.speed >= 8 && !low_res &&
1488 x->content_state_sb != kVeryHighSad) {
1489 y_sad = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].sdf(
1490 x->plane[0].src.buf, x->plane[0].src.stride, xd->plane[0].pre[0].buf,
1491 xd->plane[0].pre[0].stride);
1492 } else {
1493 const MV dummy_mv = { 0, 0 };
1494 y_sad = vp9_int_pro_motion_estimation(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col,
1495 &dummy_mv);
1496 x->sb_use_mv_part = 1;
1497 x->sb_mvcol_part = mi->mv[0].as_mv.col;
1498 x->sb_mvrow_part = mi->mv[0].as_mv.row;
1499 if (cpi->oxcf.content == VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN &&
1500 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.first_spatial_layer_to_encode &&
1501 cpi->svc.high_num_blocks_with_motion && !x->zero_temp_sad_source &&
1502 cm->width > 640 && cm->height > 480) {
1503 // Disable split below 16x16 block size when scroll motion (horz or
1504 // vert) is detected.
1505 // TODO(marpan/jianj): Improve this condition: issue is that search
1506 // range is hard-coded/limited in vp9_int_pro_motion_estimation() so
1507 // scroll motion may not be detected here.
1508 if (((abs(x->sb_mvrow_part) >= 48 && abs(x->sb_mvcol_part) <= 8) ||
1509 (abs(x->sb_mvcol_part) >= 48 && abs(x->sb_mvrow_part) <= 8)) &&
1510 y_sad < 100000) {
1511 compute_minmax_variance = 0;
1512 thresholds[2] = INT64_MAX;
1513 }
1514 }
1515 }
1516
1517 y_sad_last = y_sad;
1518 // Pick ref frame for partitioning, bias last frame when y_sad_g and y_sad
1519 // are close if short_circuit_low_temp_var is on.
1520 y_sad_thr = cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var ? (y_sad * 7) >> 3 : y_sad;
1521 if (y_sad_g < y_sad_thr) {
1522 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, yv12_g, mi_row, mi_col,
1523 &cm->frame_refs[GOLDEN_FRAME - 1].sf);
1524 mi->ref_frame[0] = GOLDEN_FRAME;
1525 mi->mv[0].as_int = 0;
1526 y_sad = y_sad_g;
1527 ref_frame_partition = GOLDEN_FRAME;
1528 } else {
1529 x->pred_mv[LAST_FRAME] = mi->mv[0].as_mv;
1530 ref_frame_partition = LAST_FRAME;
1531 }
1532
1533 set_ref_ptrs(cm, xd, mi->ref_frame[0], mi->ref_frame[1]);
1534 vp9_build_inter_predictors_sb(xd, mi_row, mi_col, BLOCK_64X64);
1535
1536 if (cpi->use_skin_detection)
1537 x->sb_is_skin =
1538 skin_sb_split(cpi, x, low_res, mi_row, mi_col, force_split);
1539
1540 d = xd->plane[0].dst.buf;
1541 dp = xd->plane[0].dst.stride;
1542
1543 // If the y_sad is very small, take 64x64 as partition and exit.
1544 // Don't check on boosted segment for now, as 64x64 is suppressed there.
1545 if (segment_id == CR_SEGMENT_ID_BASE && y_sad < cpi->vbp_threshold_sad) {
1546 const int block_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[BLOCK_64X64];
1547 const int block_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[BLOCK_64X64];
1548 if (mi_col + block_width / 2 < cm->mi_cols &&
1549 mi_row + block_height / 2 < cm->mi_rows) {
1550 set_block_size(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, BLOCK_64X64);
1551 x->variance_low[0] = 1;
1552 chroma_check(cpi, x, bsize, y_sad, is_key_frame, scene_change_detected);
1553 if (cpi->sf.svc_use_lowres_part &&
1554 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 2)
1555 update_partition_svc(cpi, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
1556 if (cpi->sf.copy_partition_flag) {
1557 update_prev_partition(cpi, x, segment_id, mi_row, mi_col, sb_offset);
1558 }
1559 return 0;
1560 }
1561 }
1562
1563 // If the y_sad is small enough, copy the partition of the superblock in the
1564 // last frame to current frame only if the last frame is not a keyframe.
1565 // Stop the copy every cpi->max_copied_frame to refresh the partition.
1566 // TODO(jianj) : tune the threshold.
1567 if (cpi->sf.copy_partition_flag && y_sad_last < cpi->vbp_threshold_copy &&
1568 copy_partitioning(cpi, x, xd, mi_row, mi_col, segment_id, sb_offset)) {
1569 chroma_check(cpi, x, bsize, y_sad, is_key_frame, scene_change_detected);
1570 if (cpi->sf.svc_use_lowres_part &&
1571 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 2)
1572 update_partition_svc(cpi, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
1573 return 0;
1574 }
1575 } else {
1576 d = VP9_VAR_OFFS;
1577 dp = 0;
1578#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1579 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
1580 switch (xd->bd) {
1581 case 10: d = CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_10); break;
1582 case 12: d = CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_12); break;
1583 case 8:
1584 default: d = CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(VP9_HIGH_VAR_OFFS_8); break;
1585 }
1586 }
1587#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1588 }
1589
1590 if (low_res && threshold_4x4avg < INT64_MAX)
1591 CHECK_MEM_ERROR(cm, vt2, vpx_calloc(16, sizeof(*vt2)));
1592 // Fill in the entire tree of 8x8 (or 4x4 under some conditions) variances
1593 // for splits.
1594 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1595 const int x32_idx = ((i & 1) << 5);
1596 const int y32_idx = ((i >> 1) << 5);
1597 const int i2 = i << 2;
1598 force_split[i + 1] = 0;
1599 avg_16x16[i] = 0;
1600 maxvar_16x16[i] = 0;
1601 minvar_16x16[i] = INT_MAX;
1602 for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
1603 const int x16_idx = x32_idx + ((j & 1) << 4);
1604 const int y16_idx = y32_idx + ((j >> 1) << 4);
1605 const int split_index = 5 + i2 + j;
1606 v16x16 *vst = &vt.split[i].split[j];
1607 force_split[split_index] = 0;
1608 variance4x4downsample[i2 + j] = 0;
1609 if (!is_key_frame) {
1610 fill_variance_8x8avg(s, sp, d, dp, x16_idx, y16_idx, vst,
1611#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1612 xd->cur_buf->flags,
1613#endif
1614 pixels_wide, pixels_high, is_key_frame);
1615 fill_variance_tree(&vt.split[i].split[j], BLOCK_16X16);
1616 get_variance(&vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none);
1617 avg_16x16[i] += vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance;
1618 if (vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance < minvar_16x16[i])
1619 minvar_16x16[i] = vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance;
1620 if (vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance > maxvar_16x16[i])
1621 maxvar_16x16[i] = vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance;
1622 if (vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance > thresholds[2]) {
1623 // 16X16 variance is above threshold for split, so force split to 8x8
1624 // for this 16x16 block (this also forces splits for upper levels).
1625 force_split[split_index] = 1;
1626 force_split[i + 1] = 1;
1627 force_split[0] = 1;
1628 } else if (compute_minmax_variance &&
1629 vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance >
1630 thresholds[1] &&
1631 !cyclic_refresh_segment_id_boosted(segment_id)) {
1632 // We have some nominal amount of 16x16 variance (based on average),
1633 // compute the minmax over the 8x8 sub-blocks, and if above threshold,
1634 // force split to 8x8 block for this 16x16 block.
1635 int minmax = compute_minmax_8x8(s, sp, d, dp, x16_idx, y16_idx,
1636#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1637 xd->cur_buf->flags,
1638#endif
1639 pixels_wide, pixels_high);
1640 int thresh_minmax = (int)cpi->vbp_threshold_minmax;
1641 if (x->content_state_sb == kVeryHighSad)
1642 thresh_minmax = thresh_minmax << 1;
1643 if (minmax > thresh_minmax) {
1644 force_split[split_index] = 1;
1645 force_split[i + 1] = 1;
1646 force_split[0] = 1;
1647 }
1648 }
1649 }
1650 if (is_key_frame ||
1651 (low_res && vt.split[i].split[j].part_variances.none.variance >
1652 threshold_4x4avg)) {
1653 force_split[split_index] = 0;
1654 // Go down to 4x4 down-sampling for variance.
1655 variance4x4downsample[i2 + j] = 1;
1656 for (k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
1657 int x8_idx = x16_idx + ((k & 1) << 3);
1658 int y8_idx = y16_idx + ((k >> 1) << 3);
1659 v8x8 *vst2 = is_key_frame ? &vst->split[k] : &vt2[i2 + j].split[k];
1660 fill_variance_4x4avg(s, sp, d, dp, x8_idx, y8_idx, vst2,
1661#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1662 xd->cur_buf->flags,
1663#endif
1664 pixels_wide, pixels_high, is_key_frame);
1665 }
1666 }
1667 }
1668 }
1669 if (cpi->noise_estimate.enabled)
1670 noise_level = vp9_noise_estimate_extract_level(&cpi->noise_estimate);
1671 // Fill the rest of the variance tree by summing split partition values.
1672 avg_32x32 = 0;
1673 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1674 const int i2 = i << 2;
1675 for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
1676 if (variance4x4downsample[i2 + j] == 1) {
1677 v16x16 *vtemp = (!is_key_frame) ? &vt2[i2 + j] : &vt.split[i].split[j];
1678 for (m = 0; m < 4; m++) fill_variance_tree(&vtemp->split[m], BLOCK_8X8);
1679 fill_variance_tree(vtemp, BLOCK_16X16);
1680 // If variance of this 16x16 block is above the threshold, force block
1681 // to split. This also forces a split on the upper levels.
1682 get_variance(&vtemp->part_variances.none);
1683 if (vtemp->part_variances.none.variance > thresholds[2]) {
1684 force_split[5 + i2 + j] = 1;
1685 force_split[i + 1] = 1;
1686 force_split[0] = 1;
1687 }
1688 }
1689 }
1690 fill_variance_tree(&vt.split[i], BLOCK_32X32);
1691 // If variance of this 32x32 block is above the threshold, or if its above
1692 // (some threshold of) the average variance over the sub-16x16 blocks, then
1693 // force this block to split. This also forces a split on the upper
1694 // (64x64) level.
1695 if (!force_split[i + 1]) {
1696 get_variance(&vt.split[i].part_variances.none);
1697 var_32x32 = vt.split[i].part_variances.none.variance;
1698 max_var_32x32 = VPXMAX(var_32x32, max_var_32x32);
1699 min_var_32x32 = VPXMIN(var_32x32, min_var_32x32);
1700 if (vt.split[i].part_variances.none.variance > thresholds[1] ||
1701 (!is_key_frame &&
1702 vt.split[i].part_variances.none.variance > (thresholds[1] >> 1) &&
1703 vt.split[i].part_variances.none.variance > (avg_16x16[i] >> 1))) {
1704 force_split[i + 1] = 1;
1705 force_split[0] = 1;
1706 } else if (!is_key_frame && noise_level < kLow && cm->height <= 360 &&
1707 (maxvar_16x16[i] - minvar_16x16[i]) > (thresholds[1] >> 1) &&
1708 maxvar_16x16[i] > thresholds[1]) {
1709 force_split[i + 1] = 1;
1710 force_split[0] = 1;
1711 }
1712 avg_32x32 += var_32x32;
1713 }
1714 }
1715 if (!force_split[0]) {
1716 fill_variance_tree(&vt, BLOCK_64X64);
1717 get_variance(&vt.part_variances.none);
1718 // If variance of this 64x64 block is above (some threshold of) the average
1719 // variance over the sub-32x32 blocks, then force this block to split.
1720 // Only checking this for noise level >= medium for now.
1721 if (!is_key_frame && noise_level >= kMedium &&
1722 vt.part_variances.none.variance > (9 * avg_32x32) >> 5)
1723 force_split[0] = 1;
1724 // Else if the maximum 32x32 variance minus the miniumum 32x32 variance in
1725 // a 64x64 block is greater than threshold and the maximum 32x32 variance is
1726 // above a miniumum threshold, then force the split of a 64x64 block
1727 // Only check this for low noise.
1728 else if (!is_key_frame && noise_level < kMedium &&
1729 (max_var_32x32 - min_var_32x32) > 3 * (thresholds[0] >> 3) &&
1730 max_var_32x32 > thresholds[0] >> 1)
1731 force_split[0] = 1;
1732 }
1733
1734 // Now go through the entire structure, splitting every block size until
1735 // we get to one that's got a variance lower than our threshold.
1736 if (mi_col + 8 > cm->mi_cols || mi_row + 8 > cm->mi_rows ||
1737 !set_vt_partitioning(cpi, x, xd, &vt, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col,
1738 thresholds[0], BLOCK_16X16, force_split[0])) {
1739 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
1740 const int x32_idx = ((i & 1) << 2);
1741 const int y32_idx = ((i >> 1) << 2);
1742 const int i2 = i << 2;
1743 if (!set_vt_partitioning(cpi, x, xd, &vt.split[i], BLOCK_32X32,
1744 (mi_row + y32_idx), (mi_col + x32_idx),
1745 thresholds[1], BLOCK_16X16,
1746 force_split[i + 1])) {
1747 for (j = 0; j < 4; ++j) {
1748 const int x16_idx = ((j & 1) << 1);
1749 const int y16_idx = ((j >> 1) << 1);
1750 // For inter frames: if variance4x4downsample[] == 1 for this 16x16
1751 // block, then the variance is based on 4x4 down-sampling, so use vt2
1752 // in set_vt_partioning(), otherwise use vt.
1753 v16x16 *vtemp = (!is_key_frame && variance4x4downsample[i2 + j] == 1)
1754 ? &vt2[i2 + j]
1755 : &vt.split[i].split[j];
1756 if (!set_vt_partitioning(
1757 cpi, x, xd, vtemp, BLOCK_16X16, mi_row + y32_idx + y16_idx,
1758 mi_col + x32_idx + x16_idx, thresholds[2], cpi->vbp_bsize_min,
1759 force_split[5 + i2 + j])) {
1760 for (k = 0; k < 4; ++k) {
1761 const int x8_idx = (k & 1);
1762 const int y8_idx = (k >> 1);
1763 if (use_4x4_partition) {
1764 if (!set_vt_partitioning(cpi, x, xd, &vtemp->split[k],
1765 BLOCK_8X8,
1766 mi_row + y32_idx + y16_idx + y8_idx,
1767 mi_col + x32_idx + x16_idx + x8_idx,
1768 thresholds[3], BLOCK_8X8, 0)) {
1769 set_block_size(
1770 cpi, x, xd, (mi_row + y32_idx + y16_idx + y8_idx),
1771 (mi_col + x32_idx + x16_idx + x8_idx), BLOCK_4X4);
1772 }
1773 } else {
1774 set_block_size(
1775 cpi, x, xd, (mi_row + y32_idx + y16_idx + y8_idx),
1776 (mi_col + x32_idx + x16_idx + x8_idx), BLOCK_8X8);
1777 }
1778 }
1779 }
1780 }
1781 }
1782 }
1783 }
1784
1785 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm) && cpi->sf.copy_partition_flag) {
1786 update_prev_partition(cpi, x, segment_id, mi_row, mi_col, sb_offset);
1787 }
1788
1789 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm) && cpi->sf.svc_use_lowres_part &&
1790 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 2)
1791 update_partition_svc(cpi, BLOCK_64X64, mi_row, mi_col);
1792
1793 if (cpi->sf.short_circuit_low_temp_var) {
1794 set_low_temp_var_flag(cpi, x, xd, &vt, thresholds, ref_frame_partition,
1795 mi_col, mi_row);
1796 }
1797
1798 chroma_check(cpi, x, bsize, y_sad, is_key_frame, scene_change_detected);
1799 if (vt2) vpx_free(vt2);
1800 return 0;
1801}
1802
1803#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1804static void update_state(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td, PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx,
1805 int mi_row, int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
1806 int output_enabled) {
1807 int i, x_idx, y;
1808 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1809 RD_COUNTS *const rdc = &td->rd_counts;
1810 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
1811 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
1812 struct macroblock_plane *const p = x->plane;
1813 struct macroblockd_plane *const pd = xd->plane;
1814 MODE_INFO *mi = &ctx->mic;
1815 MODE_INFO *const xdmi = xd->mi[0];
1816 MODE_INFO *mi_addr = xd->mi[0];
1817 const struct segmentation *const seg = &cm->seg;
1818 const int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[mi->sb_type];
1819 const int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[mi->sb_type];
1820 const int x_mis = VPXMIN(bw, cm->mi_cols - mi_col);
1821 const int y_mis = VPXMIN(bh, cm->mi_rows - mi_row);
1822 MV_REF *const frame_mvs = cm->cur_frame->mvs + mi_row * cm->mi_cols + mi_col;
1823 int w, h;
1824
1825 const int mis = cm->mi_stride;
1826 const int mi_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
1827 const int mi_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
1828 int max_plane;
1829
1830 assert(mi->sb_type == bsize);
1831
1832 *mi_addr = *mi;
1833 *x->mbmi_ext = ctx->mbmi_ext;
1834
1835 // If segmentation in use
1836 if (seg->enabled) {
1837 // For in frame complexity AQ copy the segment id from the segment map.
1838 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == COMPLEXITY_AQ) {
1839 const uint8_t *const map =
1840 seg->update_map ? cpi->segmentation_map : cm->last_frame_seg_map;
1841 mi_addr->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
1842 }
1843 // Else for cyclic refresh mode update the segment map, set the segment id
1844 // and then update the quantizer.
1845 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ) {
1846 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_segment(cpi, xd->mi[0], mi_row, mi_col, bsize,
1847 ctx->rate, ctx->dist, x->skip, p);
1848 }
1849 }
1850
1851 max_plane = is_inter_block(xdmi) ? MAX_MB_PLANE : 1;
1852 for (i = 0; i < max_plane; ++i) {
1853 p[i].coeff = ctx->coeff_pbuf[i][1];
1854 p[i].qcoeff = ctx->qcoeff_pbuf[i][1];
1855 pd[i].dqcoeff = ctx->dqcoeff_pbuf[i][1];
1856 p[i].eobs = ctx->eobs_pbuf[i][1];
1857 }
1858
1859 for (i = max_plane; i < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++i) {
1860 p[i].coeff = ctx->coeff_pbuf[i][2];
1861 p[i].qcoeff = ctx->qcoeff_pbuf[i][2];
1862 pd[i].dqcoeff = ctx->dqcoeff_pbuf[i][2];
1863 p[i].eobs = ctx->eobs_pbuf[i][2];
1864 }
1865
1866 // Restore the coding context of the MB to that that was in place
1867 // when the mode was picked for it
1868 for (y = 0; y < mi_height; y++)
1869 for (x_idx = 0; x_idx < mi_width; x_idx++)
1870 if ((xd->mb_to_right_edge >> (3 + MI_SIZE_LOG2)) + mi_width > x_idx &&
1871 (xd->mb_to_bottom_edge >> (3 + MI_SIZE_LOG2)) + mi_height > y) {
1872 xd->mi[x_idx + y * mis] = mi_addr;
1873 }
1874
1875 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ) vp9_init_plane_quantizers(cpi, x);
1876
1877 if (is_inter_block(xdmi) && xdmi->sb_type < BLOCK_8X8) {
1878 xdmi->mv[0].as_int = mi->bmi[3].as_mv[0].as_int;
1879 xdmi->mv[1].as_int = mi->bmi[3].as_mv[1].as_int;
1880 }
1881
1882 x->skip = ctx->skip;
1883 memcpy(x->zcoeff_blk[xdmi->tx_size], ctx->zcoeff_blk,
1884 sizeof(ctx->zcoeff_blk[0]) * ctx->num_4x4_blk);
1885
1886 if (!output_enabled) return;
1887
1888#if CONFIG_INTERNAL_STATS
1889 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
1890 static const int kf_mode_index[] = {
1891 THR_DC /*DC_PRED*/, THR_V_PRED /*V_PRED*/,
1892 THR_H_PRED /*H_PRED*/, THR_D45_PRED /*D45_PRED*/,
1893 THR_D135_PRED /*D135_PRED*/, THR_D117_PRED /*D117_PRED*/,
1894 THR_D153_PRED /*D153_PRED*/, THR_D207_PRED /*D207_PRED*/,
1895 THR_D63_PRED /*D63_PRED*/, THR_TM /*TM_PRED*/,
1896 };
1897 ++cpi->mode_chosen_counts[kf_mode_index[xdmi->mode]];
1898 } else {
1899 // Note how often each mode chosen as best
1900 ++cpi->mode_chosen_counts[ctx->best_mode_index];
1901 }
1902#endif
1903 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
1904 if (is_inter_block(xdmi)) {
1905 vp9_update_mv_count(td);
1906
1907 if (cm->interp_filter == SWITCHABLE) {
1908 const int ctx = get_pred_context_switchable_interp(xd);
1909 ++td->counts->switchable_interp[ctx][xdmi->interp_filter];
1910 }
1911 }
1912
1913 rdc->comp_pred_diff[SINGLE_REFERENCE] += ctx->single_pred_diff;
1914 rdc->comp_pred_diff[COMPOUND_REFERENCE] += ctx->comp_pred_diff;
1915 rdc->comp_pred_diff[REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT] += ctx->hybrid_pred_diff;
1916
1917 for (i = 0; i < SWITCHABLE_FILTER_CONTEXTS; ++i)
1918 rdc->filter_diff[i] += ctx->best_filter_diff[i];
1919 }
1920
1921 for (h = 0; h < y_mis; ++h) {
1922 MV_REF *const frame_mv = frame_mvs + h * cm->mi_cols;
1923 for (w = 0; w < x_mis; ++w) {
1924 MV_REF *const mv = frame_mv + w;
1925 mv->ref_frame[0] = mi->ref_frame[0];
1926 mv->ref_frame[1] = mi->ref_frame[1];
1927 mv->mv[0].as_int = mi->mv[0].as_int;
1928 mv->mv[1].as_int = mi->mv[1].as_int;
1929 }
1930 }
1931}
1932#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1933
1934void vp9_setup_src_planes(MACROBLOCK *x, const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *src,
1935 int mi_row, int mi_col) {
1936 uint8_t *const buffers[3] = { src->y_buffer, src->u_buffer, src->v_buffer };
1937 const int strides[3] = { src->y_stride, src->uv_stride, src->uv_stride };
1938 int i;
1939
1940 // Set current frame pointer.
1941 x->e_mbd.cur_buf = src;
1942
1943 for (i = 0; i < MAX_MB_PLANE; i++)
1944 setup_pred_plane(&x->plane[i].src, buffers[i], strides[i], mi_row, mi_col,
1945 NULL, x->e_mbd.plane[i].subsampling_x,
1946 x->e_mbd.plane[i].subsampling_y);
1947}
1948
1949static void set_mode_info_seg_skip(MACROBLOCK *x, TX_MODE tx_mode,
1950 RD_COST *rd_cost, BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
1951 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
1952 MODE_INFO *const mi = xd->mi[0];
1953 INTERP_FILTER filter_ref;
1954
1955 filter_ref = get_pred_context_switchable_interp(xd);
1956 if (filter_ref == SWITCHABLE_FILTERS) filter_ref = EIGHTTAP;
1957
1958 mi->sb_type = bsize;
1959 mi->mode = ZEROMV;
1960 mi->tx_size =
1961 VPXMIN(max_txsize_lookup[bsize], tx_mode_to_biggest_tx_size[tx_mode]);
1962 mi->skip = 1;
1963 mi->uv_mode = DC_PRED;
1964 mi->ref_frame[0] = LAST_FRAME;
1965 mi->ref_frame[1] = NONE;
1966 mi->mv[0].as_int = 0;
1967 mi->interp_filter = filter_ref;
1968
1969 xd->mi[0]->bmi[0].as_mv[0].as_int = 0;
1970 x->skip = 1;
1971
1972 vp9_rd_cost_init(rd_cost);
1973}
1974
1975#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1976static void set_segment_rdmult(VP9_COMP *const cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
1977 int mi_row, int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
1978 AQ_MODE aq_mode) {
1979 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1980 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
1981 const uint8_t *const map =
1982 cm->seg.update_map ? cpi->segmentation_map : cm->last_frame_seg_map;
1983
1984 vp9_init_plane_quantizers(cpi, x);
1985 vpx_clear_system_state();
1986
1987 if (aq_mode == NO_AQ || aq_mode == PSNR_AQ) {
1988 if (cpi->sf.enable_tpl_model) x->rdmult = x->cb_rdmult;
1989 } else if (aq_mode == PERCEPTUAL_AQ) {
1990 x->rdmult = x->cb_rdmult;
1991 } else if (aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ) {
1992 // If segment is boosted, use rdmult for that segment.
1993 if (cyclic_refresh_segment_id_boosted(
1994 get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col)))
1995 x->rdmult = vp9_cyclic_refresh_get_rdmult(cpi->cyclic_refresh);
1996 } else {
1997 x->rdmult = vp9_compute_rd_mult(cpi, cm->base_qindex + cm->y_dc_delta_q);
1998 }
1999
2000 if (oxcf->tuning == VP8_TUNE_SSIM) {
2001 set_ssim_rdmult(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, &x->rdmult);
2002 }
2003}
2004
2005static void rd_pick_sb_modes(VP9_COMP *cpi, TileDataEnc *tile_data,
2006 MACROBLOCK *const x, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2007 RD_COST *rd_cost, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
2008 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx, int rate_in_best_rd,
2009 int64_t dist_in_best_rd) {
2010 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2011 TileInfo *const tile_info = &tile_data->tile_info;
2012 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2013 MODE_INFO *mi;
2014 struct macroblock_plane *const p = x->plane;
2015 struct macroblockd_plane *const pd = xd->plane;
2016 const AQ_MODE aq_mode = cpi->oxcf.aq_mode;
2017 int i, orig_rdmult;
2018 int64_t best_rd = INT64_MAX;
2019
2020 vpx_clear_system_state();
2021
2022 // Use the lower precision, but faster, 32x32 fdct for mode selection.
2023 x->use_lp32x32fdct = 1;
2024
2025 set_offsets(cpi, tile_info, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2026 mi = xd->mi[0];
2027 mi->sb_type = bsize;
2028
2029 for (i = 0; i < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++i) {
2030 p[i].coeff = ctx->coeff_pbuf[i][0];
2031 p[i].qcoeff = ctx->qcoeff_pbuf[i][0];
2032 pd[i].dqcoeff = ctx->dqcoeff_pbuf[i][0];
2033 p[i].eobs = ctx->eobs_pbuf[i][0];
2034 }
2035 ctx->is_coded = 0;
2036 ctx->skippable = 0;
2037 ctx->pred_pixel_ready = 0;
2038 x->skip_recode = 0;
2039
2040 // Set to zero to make sure we do not use the previous encoded frame stats
2041 mi->skip = 0;
2042
2043#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
2044 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
2045 x->source_variance = vp9_high_get_sby_perpixel_variance(
2046 cpi, &x->plane[0].src, bsize, xd->bd);
2047 } else {
2048 x->source_variance =
2049 vp9_get_sby_perpixel_variance(cpi, &x->plane[0].src, bsize);
2050 }
2051#else
2052 x->source_variance =
2053 vp9_get_sby_perpixel_variance(cpi, &x->plane[0].src, bsize);
2054#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
2055
2056 // Save rdmult before it might be changed, so it can be restored later.
2057 orig_rdmult = x->rdmult;
2058
2059 if ((cpi->sf.tx_domain_thresh > 0.0) || (cpi->sf.quant_opt_thresh > 0.0)) {
2060 double logvar = vp9_log_block_var(cpi, x, bsize);
2061 // Check block complexity as part of descision on using pixel or transform
2062 // domain distortion in rd tests.
2063 x->block_tx_domain = cpi->sf.allow_txfm_domain_distortion &&
2064 (logvar >= cpi->sf.tx_domain_thresh);
2065
2066 // Check block complexity as part of descision on using quantized
2067 // coefficient optimisation inside the rd loop.
2068 x->block_qcoeff_opt =
2069 cpi->sf.allow_quant_coeff_opt && (logvar <= cpi->sf.quant_opt_thresh);
2070 } else {
2071 x->block_tx_domain = cpi->sf.allow_txfm_domain_distortion;
2072 x->block_qcoeff_opt = cpi->sf.allow_quant_coeff_opt;
2073 }
2074
2075 set_segment_index(cpi, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, 0);
2076 set_segment_rdmult(cpi, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, aq_mode);
2077 if (rate_in_best_rd < INT_MAX && dist_in_best_rd < INT64_MAX) {
2078 best_rd = vp9_calculate_rd_cost(x->rdmult, x->rddiv, rate_in_best_rd,
2079 dist_in_best_rd);
2080 }
2081
2082 // Find best coding mode & reconstruct the MB so it is available
2083 // as a predictor for MBs that follow in the SB
2084 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
2085 vp9_rd_pick_intra_mode_sb(cpi, x, rd_cost, bsize, ctx, best_rd);
2086 } else {
2087 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) {
2088 if (segfeature_active(&cm->seg, mi->segment_id, SEG_LVL_SKIP))
2089 vp9_rd_pick_inter_mode_sb_seg_skip(cpi, tile_data, x, rd_cost, bsize,
2090 ctx, best_rd);
2091 else
2092 vp9_rd_pick_inter_mode_sb(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, rd_cost,
2093 bsize, ctx, best_rd);
2094 } else {
2095 vp9_rd_pick_inter_mode_sub8x8(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, rd_cost,
2096 bsize, ctx, best_rd);
2097 }
2098 }
2099
2100 // Examine the resulting rate and for AQ mode 2 make a segment choice.
2101 if ((rd_cost->rate != INT_MAX) && (aq_mode == COMPLEXITY_AQ) &&
2102 (bsize >= BLOCK_16X16) &&
2103 (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME || cpi->refresh_alt_ref_frame ||
2104 (cpi->refresh_golden_frame && !cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref))) {
2105 vp9_caq_select_segment(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, rd_cost->rate);
2106 }
2107
2108 // TODO(jingning) The rate-distortion optimization flow needs to be
2109 // refactored to provide proper exit/return handle.
2110 if (rd_cost->rate == INT_MAX || rd_cost->dist == INT64_MAX)
2111 rd_cost->rdcost = INT64_MAX;
2112 else
2113 rd_cost->rdcost = RDCOST(x->rdmult, x->rddiv, rd_cost->rate, rd_cost->dist);
2114
2115 x->rdmult = orig_rdmult;
2116
2117 ctx->rate = rd_cost->rate;
2118 ctx->dist = rd_cost->dist;
2119}
2120#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
2121
2122static void update_stats(VP9_COMMON *cm, ThreadData *td) {
2123 const MACROBLOCK *x = &td->mb;
2124 const MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2125 const MODE_INFO *const mi = xd->mi[0];
2126 const MB_MODE_INFO_EXT *const mbmi_ext = x->mbmi_ext;
2127 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = mi->sb_type;
2128
2129 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
2130 FRAME_COUNTS *const counts = td->counts;
2131 const int inter_block = is_inter_block(mi);
2132 const int seg_ref_active =
2133 segfeature_active(&cm->seg, mi->segment_id, SEG_LVL_REF_FRAME);
2134 if (!seg_ref_active) {
2135 counts->intra_inter[get_intra_inter_context(xd)][inter_block]++;
2136 // If the segment reference feature is enabled we have only a single
2137 // reference frame allowed for the segment so exclude it from
2138 // the reference frame counts used to work out probabilities.
2139 if (inter_block) {
2140 const MV_REFERENCE_FRAME ref0 = mi->ref_frame[0];
2141 if (cm->reference_mode == REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT)
2142 counts->comp_inter[vp9_get_reference_mode_context(cm, xd)]
2143 [has_second_ref(mi)]++;
2144
2145 if (has_second_ref(mi)) {
2146 const int idx = cm->ref_frame_sign_bias[cm->comp_fixed_ref];
2147 const int ctx = vp9_get_pred_context_comp_ref_p(cm, xd);
2148 const int bit = mi->ref_frame[!idx] == cm->comp_var_ref[1];
2149 counts->comp_ref[ctx][bit]++;
2150 } else {
2151 counts->single_ref[vp9_get_pred_context_single_ref_p1(xd)][0]
2152 [ref0 != LAST_FRAME]++;
2153 if (ref0 != LAST_FRAME)
2154 counts->single_ref[vp9_get_pred_context_single_ref_p2(xd)][1]
2155 [ref0 != GOLDEN_FRAME]++;
2156 }
2157 }
2158 }
2159 if (inter_block &&
2160 !segfeature_active(&cm->seg, mi->segment_id, SEG_LVL_SKIP)) {
2161 const int mode_ctx = mbmi_ext->mode_context[mi->ref_frame[0]];
2162 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) {
2163 const PREDICTION_MODE mode = mi->mode;
2164 ++counts->inter_mode[mode_ctx][INTER_OFFSET(mode)];
2165 } else {
2166 const int num_4x4_w = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2167 const int num_4x4_h = num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2168 int idx, idy;
2169 for (idy = 0; idy < 2; idy += num_4x4_h) {
2170 for (idx = 0; idx < 2; idx += num_4x4_w) {
2171 const int j = idy * 2 + idx;
2172 const PREDICTION_MODE b_mode = mi->bmi[j].as_mode;
2173 ++counts->inter_mode[mode_ctx][INTER_OFFSET(b_mode)];
2174 }
2175 }
2176 }
2177 }
2178 }
2179}
