2181#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
2182static void restore_context(MACROBLOCK *const x, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2183 ENTROPY_CONTEXT a[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE],
2184 ENTROPY_CONTEXT l[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE],
2185 PARTITION_CONTEXT sa[8], PARTITION_CONTEXT sl[8],
2186 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
2187 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2188 int p;
2189 const int num_4x4_blocks_wide = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2190 const int num_4x4_blocks_high = num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2191 int mi_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2192 int mi_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2193 for (p = 0; p < MAX_MB_PLANE; p++) {
2194 memcpy(xd->above_context[p] + ((mi_col * 2) >> xd->plane[p].subsampling_x),
2195 a + num_4x4_blocks_wide * p,
2196 (sizeof(ENTROPY_CONTEXT) * num_4x4_blocks_wide) >>
2197 xd->plane[p].subsampling_x);
2198 memcpy(xd->left_context[p] +
2199 ((mi_row & MI_MASK) * 2 >> xd->plane[p].subsampling_y),
2200 l + num_4x4_blocks_high * p,
2201 (sizeof(ENTROPY_CONTEXT) * num_4x4_blocks_high) >>
2202 xd->plane[p].subsampling_y);
2203 }
2204 memcpy(xd->above_seg_context + mi_col, sa,
2205 sizeof(*xd->above_seg_context) * mi_width);
2206 memcpy(xd->left_seg_context + (mi_row & MI_MASK), sl,
2207 sizeof(xd->left_seg_context[0]) * mi_height);
2208}
2209
2210static void save_context(MACROBLOCK *const x, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2211 ENTROPY_CONTEXT a[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE],
2212 ENTROPY_CONTEXT l[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE],
2213 PARTITION_CONTEXT sa[8], PARTITION_CONTEXT sl[8],
2214 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
2215 const MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2216 int p;
2217 const int num_4x4_blocks_wide = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2218 const int num_4x4_blocks_high = num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2219 int mi_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2220 int mi_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2221
2222 // buffer the above/left context information of the block in search.
2223 for (p = 0; p < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++p) {
2224 memcpy(a + num_4x4_blocks_wide * p,
2225 xd->above_context[p] + (mi_col * 2 >> xd->plane[p].subsampling_x),
2226 (sizeof(ENTROPY_CONTEXT) * num_4x4_blocks_wide) >>
2227 xd->plane[p].subsampling_x);
2228 memcpy(l + num_4x4_blocks_high * p,
2229 xd->left_context[p] +
2230 ((mi_row & MI_MASK) * 2 >> xd->plane[p].subsampling_y),
2231 (sizeof(ENTROPY_CONTEXT) * num_4x4_blocks_high) >>
2232 xd->plane[p].subsampling_y);
2233 }
2234 memcpy(sa, xd->above_seg_context + mi_col,
2235 sizeof(*xd->above_seg_context) * mi_width);
2236 memcpy(sl, xd->left_seg_context + (mi_row & MI_MASK),
2237 sizeof(xd->left_seg_context[0]) * mi_height);
2238}

2240static void encode_b(VP9_COMP *cpi, const TileInfo *const tile, ThreadData *td,
2241 TOKENEXTRA **tp, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2242 int output_enabled, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
2243 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx) {
2244 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2245 set_offsets(cpi, tile, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2246
2247 if (cpi->sf.enable_tpl_model &&
2248 (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == NO_AQ || cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == PERCEPTUAL_AQ)) {
2249 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2250 x->rdmult = x->cb_rdmult;
2251 if (oxcf->tuning == VP8_TUNE_SSIM) {
2252 set_ssim_rdmult(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, &x->rdmult);
2253 }
2254 }
2255
2256 update_state(cpi, td, ctx, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, output_enabled);
2257 encode_superblock(cpi, td, tp, output_enabled, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, ctx);
2258
2259 if (output_enabled) {
2260 update_stats(&cpi->common, td);
2261
2262 (*tp)->token = EOSB_TOKEN;
2263 (*tp)++;
2264 }
2265}
2266
2267static void encode_sb(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td, const TileInfo *const tile,
2268 TOKENEXTRA **tp, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2269 int output_enabled, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, PC_TREE *pc_tree) {
2270 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2271 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2272 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2273
2274 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize], hbs = (1 << bsl) / 4;
2275 int ctx;
2276 PARTITION_TYPE partition;
2277 BLOCK_SIZE subsize = bsize;
2278
2279 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
2280
2281 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) {
2282 ctx = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2283 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, pc_tree->partitioning);
2284 } else {
2285 ctx = 0;
2286 subsize = BLOCK_4X4;
2287 }
2288
2289 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][subsize];
2290 if (output_enabled && bsize != BLOCK_4X4)
2291 td->counts->partition[ctx][partition]++;
2292
2293 switch (partition) {
2294 case PARTITION_NONE:
2295 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2296 &pc_tree->none);
2297 break;
2298 case PARTITION_VERT:
2299 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2300 &pc_tree->vertical[0]);
2301 if (mi_col + hbs < cm->mi_cols && bsize > BLOCK_8X8) {
2302 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row, mi_col + hbs, output_enabled,
2303 subsize, &pc_tree->vertical[1]);
2304 }
2305 break;
2306 case PARTITION_HORZ:
2307 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2308 &pc_tree->horizontal[0]);
2309 if (mi_row + hbs < cm->mi_rows && bsize > BLOCK_8X8) {
2310 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col, output_enabled,
2311 subsize, &pc_tree->horizontal[1]);
2312 }
2313 break;
2314 default:
2315 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
2316 if (bsize == BLOCK_8X8) {
2317 encode_b(cpi, tile, td, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2318 pc_tree->leaf_split[0]);
2319 } else {
2320 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2321 pc_tree->split[0]);
2322 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col + hbs, output_enabled,
2323 subsize, pc_tree->split[1]);
2324 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col, output_enabled,
2325 subsize, pc_tree->split[2]);
2326 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col + hbs, output_enabled,
2327 subsize, pc_tree->split[3]);
2328 }
2329 break;
2330 }
2331
2332 if (partition != PARTITION_SPLIT || bsize == BLOCK_8X8)
2333 update_partition_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, bsize);
2334}
2335#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
2336
2337// Check to see if the given partition size is allowed for a specified number
2338// of 8x8 block rows and columns remaining in the image.
2339// If not then return the largest allowed partition size
2340static BLOCK_SIZE find_partition_size(BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int rows_left,
2341 int cols_left, int *bh, int *bw) {
2342 if (rows_left <= 0 || cols_left <= 0) {
2343 return VPXMIN(bsize, BLOCK_8X8);
2344 } else {
2345 for (; bsize > 0; bsize -= 3) {
2346 *bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2347 *bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2348 if ((*bh <= rows_left) && (*bw <= cols_left)) {
2349 break;
2350 }
2351 }
2352 }
2353 return bsize;
2354}
2355
2356static void set_partial_b64x64_partition(MODE_INFO *mi, int mis, int bh_in,
2357 int bw_in, int row8x8_remaining,
2358 int col8x8_remaining, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
2359 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8) {
2360 int bh = bh_in;
2361 int r, c;
2362 for (r = 0; r < MI_BLOCK_SIZE; r += bh) {
2363 int bw = bw_in;
2364 for (c = 0; c < MI_BLOCK_SIZE; c += bw) {
2365 const int index = r * mis + c;
2366 mi_8x8[index] = mi + index;
2367 mi_8x8[index]->sb_type = find_partition_size(
2368 bsize, row8x8_remaining - r, col8x8_remaining - c, &bh, &bw);
2369 }
2370 }
2371}
2372
2373// This function attempts to set all mode info entries in a given SB64
2374// to the same block partition size.
2375// However, at the bottom and right borders of the image the requested size
2376// may not be allowed in which case this code attempts to choose the largest
2377// allowable partition.
2378static void set_fixed_partitioning(VP9_COMP *cpi, const TileInfo *const tile,
2379 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2380 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
2381 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2382 const int mis = cm->mi_stride;
2383 const int row8x8_remaining = tile->mi_row_end - mi_row;
2384 const int col8x8_remaining = tile->mi_col_end - mi_col;
2385 int block_row, block_col;
2386 MODE_INFO *mi_upper_left = cm->mi + mi_row * mis + mi_col;
2387 int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
2388 int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
2389
2390 assert((row8x8_remaining > 0) && (col8x8_remaining > 0));
2391
2392 // Apply the requested partition size to the SB64 if it is all "in image"
2393 if ((col8x8_remaining >= MI_BLOCK_SIZE) &&
2394 (row8x8_remaining >= MI_BLOCK_SIZE)) {
2395 for (block_row = 0; block_row < MI_BLOCK_SIZE; block_row += bh) {
2396 for (block_col = 0; block_col < MI_BLOCK_SIZE; block_col += bw) {
2397 int index = block_row * mis + block_col;
2398 mi_8x8[index] = mi_upper_left + index;
2399 mi_8x8[index]->sb_type = bsize;
2400 }
2401 }
2402 } else {
2403 // Else this is a partial SB64.
2404 set_partial_b64x64_partition(mi_upper_left, mis, bh, bw, row8x8_remaining,
2405 col8x8_remaining, bsize, mi_8x8);
2406 }
2407}

2409static const struct {
2410 int row;
2411 int col;
2412} coord_lookup[16] = {
2413 // 32x32 index = 0
2414 { 0, 0 },
2415 { 0, 2 },
2416 { 2, 0 },
2417 { 2, 2 },
2418 // 32x32 index = 1
2419 { 0, 4 },
2420 { 0, 6 },
2421 { 2, 4 },
2422 { 2, 6 },
2423 // 32x32 index = 2
2424 { 4, 0 },
2425 { 4, 2 },
2426 { 6, 0 },
2427 { 6, 2 },
2428 // 32x32 index = 3
2429 { 4, 4 },
2430 { 4, 6 },
2431 { 6, 4 },
2432 { 6, 6 },
2433};
2434
2435static void set_source_var_based_partition(VP9_COMP *cpi,
2436 const TileInfo *const tile,
2437 MACROBLOCK *const x,
2438 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8, int mi_row,
2439 int mi_col) {
2440 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2441 const int mis = cm->mi_stride;
2442 const int row8x8_remaining = tile->mi_row_end - mi_row;
2443 const int col8x8_remaining = tile->mi_col_end - mi_col;
2444 MODE_INFO *mi_upper_left = cm->mi + mi_row * mis + mi_col;
2445
2446 vp9_setup_src_planes(x, cpi->Source, mi_row, mi_col);
2447
2448 assert((row8x8_remaining > 0) && (col8x8_remaining > 0));
2449
2450 // In-image SB64
2451 if ((col8x8_remaining >= MI_BLOCK_SIZE) &&
2452 (row8x8_remaining >= MI_BLOCK_SIZE)) {
2453 int i, j;
2454 int index;
2455 diff d32[4];
2456 const int offset = (mi_row >> 1) * cm->mb_cols + (mi_col >> 1);
2457 int is_larger_better = 0;
2458 int use32x32 = 0;
2459 unsigned int thr = cpi->source_var_thresh;
2460
2461 memset(d32, 0, 4 * sizeof(diff));
2462
2463 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2464 diff *d16[4];
2465
2466 for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
2467 int b_mi_row = coord_lookup[i * 4 + j].row;
2468 int b_mi_col = coord_lookup[i * 4 + j].col;
2469 int boffset = b_mi_row / 2 * cm->mb_cols + b_mi_col / 2;
2470
2471 d16[j] = cpi->source_diff_var + offset + boffset;
2472
2473 index = b_mi_row * mis + b_mi_col;
2474 mi_8x8[index] = mi_upper_left + index;
2475 mi_8x8[index]->sb_type = BLOCK_16X16;
2476
2477 // TODO(yunqingwang): If d16[j].var is very large, use 8x8 partition
2478 // size to further improve quality.
2479 }
2480
2481 is_larger_better = (d16[0]->var < thr) && (d16[1]->var < thr) &&
2482 (d16[2]->var < thr) && (d16[3]->var < thr);
2483
2484 // Use 32x32 partition
2485 if (is_larger_better) {
2486 use32x32 += 1;
2487
2488 for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
2489 d32[i].sse += d16[j]->sse;
2490 d32[i].sum += d16[j]->sum;
2491 }
2492
2493 d32[i].var =
2494 (unsigned int)(d32[i].sse -
2495 (unsigned int)(((int64_t)d32[i].sum * d32[i].sum) >>
2496 10));
2497
2498 index = coord_lookup[i * 4].row * mis + coord_lookup[i * 4].col;
2499 mi_8x8[index] = mi_upper_left + index;
2500 mi_8x8[index]->sb_type = BLOCK_32X32;
2501 }
2502 }
2503
2504 if (use32x32 == 4) {
2505 thr <<= 1;
2506 is_larger_better = (d32[0].var < thr) && (d32[1].var < thr) &&
2507 (d32[2].var < thr) && (d32[3].var < thr);
2508
2509 // Use 64x64 partition
2510 if (is_larger_better) {
2511 mi_8x8[0] = mi_upper_left;
2512 mi_8x8[0]->sb_type = BLOCK_64X64;
2513 }
2514 }
2515 } else { // partial in-image SB64
2516 int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[BLOCK_16X16];
2517 int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[BLOCK_16X16];
2518 set_partial_b64x64_partition(mi_upper_left, mis, bh, bw, row8x8_remaining,
2519 col8x8_remaining, BLOCK_16X16, mi_8x8);
2520 }
2521}
2522
2523static void update_state_rt(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
2524 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2525 int bsize) {
2526 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2527 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2528 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2529 MODE_INFO *const mi = xd->mi[0];
2530 struct macroblock_plane *const p = x->plane;
2531 const struct segmentation *const seg = &cm->seg;
2532 const int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[mi->sb_type];
2533 const int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[mi->sb_type];
2534 const int x_mis = VPXMIN(bw, cm->mi_cols - mi_col);
2535 const int y_mis = VPXMIN(bh, cm->mi_rows - mi_row);
2536
2537 *(xd->mi[0]) = ctx->mic;
2538 *(x->mbmi_ext) = ctx->mbmi_ext;
2539
2540 if (seg->enabled && (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ || cpi->roi.enabled)) {
2541 // Setting segmentation map for cyclic_refresh.
2542 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ) {
2543 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_segment(cpi, mi, mi_row, mi_col, bsize,
2544 ctx->rate, ctx->dist, x->skip, p);
2545 } else {
2546 const uint8_t *const map =
2547 seg->update_map ? cpi->segmentation_map : cm->last_frame_seg_map;
2548 mi->segment_id = get_segment_id(cm, map, bsize, mi_row, mi_col);
2549 }
2550 vp9_init_plane_quantizers(cpi, x);
2551 }
2552
2553 if (is_inter_block(mi)) {
2554 vp9_update_mv_count(td);
2555 if (cm->interp_filter == SWITCHABLE) {
2556 const int pred_ctx = get_pred_context_switchable_interp(xd);
2557 ++td->counts->switchable_interp[pred_ctx][mi->interp_filter];
2558 }
2559
2560 if (mi->sb_type < BLOCK_8X8) {
2561 mi->mv[0].as_int = mi->bmi[3].as_mv[0].as_int;
2562 mi->mv[1].as_int = mi->bmi[3].as_mv[1].as_int;
2563 }
2564 }
2565
2566 if (cm->use_prev_frame_mvs || !cm->error_resilient_mode ||
2567 (cpi->svc.use_base_mv && cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers > 1 &&
2568 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id != cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 1)) {
2569 MV_REF *const frame_mvs =
2570 cm->cur_frame->mvs + mi_row * cm->mi_cols + mi_col;
2571 int w, h;
2572
2573 for (h = 0; h < y_mis; ++h) {
2574 MV_REF *const frame_mv = frame_mvs + h * cm->mi_cols;
2575 for (w = 0; w < x_mis; ++w) {
2576 MV_REF *const mv = frame_mv + w;
2577 mv->ref_frame[0] = mi->ref_frame[0];
2578 mv->ref_frame[1] = mi->ref_frame[1];
2579 mv->mv[0].as_int = mi->mv[0].as_int;
2580 mv->mv[1].as_int = mi->mv[1].as_int;
2581 }
2582 }
2583 }
2584
2585 x->skip = ctx->skip;
2586 x->skip_txfm[0] = (mi->segment_id || xd->lossless) ? 0 : ctx->skip_txfm[0];
2587}
2588
2589static void encode_b_rt(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
2590 const TileInfo *const tile, TOKENEXTRA **tp, int mi_row,
2591 int mi_col, int output_enabled, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
2592 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx) {
2593 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2594 set_offsets(cpi, tile, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2595 update_state_rt(cpi, td, ctx, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2596
2597 encode_superblock(cpi, td, tp, output_enabled, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, ctx);
2598 update_stats(&cpi->common, td);
2599
2600 (*tp)->token = EOSB_TOKEN;
2601 (*tp)++;
2602}
2603
2604static void encode_sb_rt(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
2605 const TileInfo *const tile, TOKENEXTRA **tp,
2606 int mi_row, int mi_col, int output_enabled,
2607 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, PC_TREE *pc_tree) {
2608 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2609 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2610 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2611
2612 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize], hbs = (1 << bsl) / 4;
2613 int ctx;
2614 PARTITION_TYPE partition;
2615 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
2616
2617 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
2618
2619 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) {
2620 const int idx_str = xd->mi_stride * mi_row + mi_col;
2621 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8 = cm->mi_grid_visible + idx_str;
2622 ctx = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2623 subsize = mi_8x8[0]->sb_type;
2624 } else {
2625 ctx = 0;
2626 subsize = BLOCK_4X4;
2627 }
2628
2629 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][subsize];
2630 if (output_enabled && bsize != BLOCK_4X4)
2631 td->counts->partition[ctx][partition]++;
2632
2633 switch (partition) {
2634 case PARTITION_NONE:
2635 encode_b_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2636 &pc_tree->none);
2637 break;
2638 case PARTITION_VERT:
2639 encode_b_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2640 &pc_tree->vertical[0]);
2641 if (mi_col + hbs < cm->mi_cols && bsize > BLOCK_8X8) {
2642 encode_b_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col + hbs, output_enabled,
2643 subsize, &pc_tree->vertical[1]);
2644 }
2645 break;
2646 case PARTITION_HORZ:
2647 encode_b_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2648 &pc_tree->horizontal[0]);
2649 if (mi_row + hbs < cm->mi_rows && bsize > BLOCK_8X8) {
2650 encode_b_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col, output_enabled,
2651 subsize, &pc_tree->horizontal[1]);
2652 }
2653 break;
2654 default:
2655 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
2656 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_SPLIT);
2657 encode_sb_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, subsize,
2658 pc_tree->split[0]);
2659 encode_sb_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row, mi_col + hbs, output_enabled,
2660 subsize, pc_tree->split[1]);
2661 encode_sb_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col, output_enabled,
2662 subsize, pc_tree->split[2]);
2663 encode_sb_rt(cpi, td, tile, tp, mi_row + hbs, mi_col + hbs,
2664 output_enabled, subsize, pc_tree->split[3]);
2665 break;
2666 }
2667
2668 if (partition != PARTITION_SPLIT || bsize == BLOCK_8X8)
2669 update_partition_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, bsize);
2670}
2671
2672#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
2673static void rd_use_partition(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
2674 TileDataEnc *tile_data, MODE_INFO **mi_8x8,
2675 TOKENEXTRA **tp, int mi_row, int mi_col,
2676 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int *rate, int64_t *dist,
2677 int do_recon, PC_TREE *pc_tree) {
2678 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2679 TileInfo *const tile_info = &tile_data->tile_info;
2680 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
2681 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
2682 const int mis = cm->mi_stride;
2683 const int bsl = b_width_log2_lookup[bsize];
2684 const int mi_step = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] / 2;
2685 const int bss = (1 << bsl) / 4;
2686 int i, pl;
2687 PARTITION_TYPE partition = PARTITION_NONE;
2688 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
2689 ENTROPY_CONTEXT l[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE], a[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE];
2690 PARTITION_CONTEXT sl[8], sa[8];
2691 RD_COST last_part_rdc, none_rdc, chosen_rdc;
2692 BLOCK_SIZE sub_subsize = BLOCK_4X4;
2693 int splits_below = 0;
2694 BLOCK_SIZE bs_type = mi_8x8[0]->sb_type;
2695 int do_partition_search = 1;
2696 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx = &pc_tree->none;
2697
2698 if (mi_row >= cm->mi_rows || mi_col >= cm->mi_cols) return;
2699
2700 assert(num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] ==
2701 num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize]);
2702
2703 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&last_part_rdc);
2704 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&none_rdc);
2705 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&chosen_rdc);
2706
2707 partition = partition_lookup[bsl][bs_type];
2708 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, partition);
2709
2710 pc_tree->partitioning = partition;
2711 save_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2712
2713 if (bsize == BLOCK_16X16 && cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ) {
2714 set_offsets(cpi, tile_info, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2715 x->mb_energy = vp9_block_energy(cpi, x, bsize);
2716 }
2717
2718 if (do_partition_search &&
2719 cpi->sf.partition_search_type == SEARCH_PARTITION &&
2720 cpi->sf.adjust_partitioning_from_last_frame) {
2721 // Check if any of the sub blocks are further split.
2722 if (partition == PARTITION_SPLIT && subsize > BLOCK_8X8) {
2723 sub_subsize = get_subsize(subsize, PARTITION_SPLIT);
2724 splits_below = 1;
2725 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2726 int jj = i >> 1, ii = i & 0x01;
2727 MODE_INFO *this_mi = mi_8x8[jj * bss * mis + ii * bss];
2728 if (this_mi && this_mi->sb_type >= sub_subsize) {
2729 splits_below = 0;
2730 }
2731 }
2732 }
2733
2734 // If partition is not none try none unless each of the 4 splits are split
2735 // even further..
2736 if (partition != PARTITION_NONE && !splits_below &&
2737 mi_row + (mi_step >> 1) < cm->mi_rows &&
2738 mi_col + (mi_step >> 1) < cm->mi_cols) {
2739 pc_tree->partitioning = PARTITION_NONE;
2740 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &none_rdc, bsize, ctx,
2741 INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2742
2743 pl = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2744
2745 if (none_rdc.rate < INT_MAX) {
2746 none_rdc.rate += cpi->partition_cost[pl][PARTITION_NONE];
2747 none_rdc.rdcost =
2748 RDCOST(x->rdmult, x->rddiv, none_rdc.rate, none_rdc.dist);
2749 }
2750
2751 restore_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2752 mi_8x8[0]->sb_type = bs_type;
2753 pc_tree->partitioning = partition;
2754 }
2755 }
2756
2757 switch (partition) {
2758 case PARTITION_NONE:
2759 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &last_part_rdc, bsize,
2760 ctx, INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2761 break;
2762 case PARTITION_HORZ:
2763 pc_tree->horizontal[0].skip_ref_frame_mask = 0;
2764 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &last_part_rdc,
2765 subsize, &pc_tree->horizontal[0], INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2766 if (last_part_rdc.rate != INT_MAX && bsize >= BLOCK_8X8 &&
2767 mi_row + (mi_step >> 1) < cm->mi_rows) {
2768 RD_COST tmp_rdc;
2769 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx = &pc_tree->horizontal[0];
2770 vp9_rd_cost_init(&tmp_rdc);
2771 update_state(cpi, td, ctx, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, 0);
2772 encode_superblock(cpi, td, tp, 0, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, ctx);
2773 pc_tree->horizontal[1].skip_ref_frame_mask = 0;
2774 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row + (mi_step >> 1), mi_col,
2775 &tmp_rdc, subsize, &pc_tree->horizontal[1], INT_MAX,
2776 INT64_MAX);
2777 if (tmp_rdc.rate == INT_MAX || tmp_rdc.dist == INT64_MAX) {
2778 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&last_part_rdc);
2779 break;
2780 }
2781 last_part_rdc.rate += tmp_rdc.rate;
2782 last_part_rdc.dist += tmp_rdc.dist;
2783 last_part_rdc.rdcost += tmp_rdc.rdcost;
2784 }
2785 break;
2786 case PARTITION_VERT:
2787 pc_tree->vertical[0].skip_ref_frame_mask = 0;
2788 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &last_part_rdc,
2789 subsize, &pc_tree->vertical[0], INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2790 if (last_part_rdc.rate != INT_MAX && bsize >= BLOCK_8X8 &&
2791 mi_col + (mi_step >> 1) < cm->mi_cols) {
2792 RD_COST tmp_rdc;
2793 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx = &pc_tree->vertical[0];
2794 vp9_rd_cost_init(&tmp_rdc);
2795 update_state(cpi, td, ctx, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, 0);
2796 encode_superblock(cpi, td, tp, 0, mi_row, mi_col, subsize, ctx);
2797 pc_tree->vertical[bsize > BLOCK_8X8].skip_ref_frame_mask = 0;
2798 rd_pick_sb_modes(
2799 cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col + (mi_step >> 1), &tmp_rdc,
2800 subsize, &pc_tree->vertical[bsize > BLOCK_8X8], INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2801 if (tmp_rdc.rate == INT_MAX || tmp_rdc.dist == INT64_MAX) {
2802 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&last_part_rdc);
2803 break;
2804 }
2805 last_part_rdc.rate += tmp_rdc.rate;
2806 last_part_rdc.dist += tmp_rdc.dist;
2807 last_part_rdc.rdcost += tmp_rdc.rdcost;
2808 }
2809 break;
2810 default:
2811 assert(partition == PARTITION_SPLIT);
2812 if (bsize == BLOCK_8X8) {
2813 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &last_part_rdc,
2814 subsize, pc_tree->leaf_split[0], INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2815 break;
2816 }
2817 last_part_rdc.rate = 0;
2818 last_part_rdc.dist = 0;
2819 last_part_rdc.rdcost = 0;
2820 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2821 int x_idx = (i & 1) * (mi_step >> 1);
2822 int y_idx = (i >> 1) * (mi_step >> 1);
2823 int jj = i >> 1, ii = i & 0x01;
2824 RD_COST tmp_rdc;
2825 if ((mi_row + y_idx >= cm->mi_rows) || (mi_col + x_idx >= cm->mi_cols))
2826 continue;
2827
2828 vp9_rd_cost_init(&tmp_rdc);
2829 rd_use_partition(cpi, td, tile_data, mi_8x8 + jj * bss * mis + ii * bss,
2830 tp, mi_row + y_idx, mi_col + x_idx, subsize,
2831 &tmp_rdc.rate, &tmp_rdc.dist, i != 3,
2832 pc_tree->split[i]);
2833 if (tmp_rdc.rate == INT_MAX || tmp_rdc.dist == INT64_MAX) {
2834 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&last_part_rdc);
2835 break;
2836 }
2837 last_part_rdc.rate += tmp_rdc.rate;
2838 last_part_rdc.dist += tmp_rdc.dist;
2839 }
2840 break;
2841 }
2842
2843 pl = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2844 if (last_part_rdc.rate < INT_MAX) {
2845 last_part_rdc.rate += cpi->partition_cost[pl][partition];
2846 last_part_rdc.rdcost =
2847 RDCOST(x->rdmult, x->rddiv, last_part_rdc.rate, last_part_rdc.dist);
2848 }
2849
2850 if (do_partition_search && cpi->sf.adjust_partitioning_from_last_frame &&
2851 cpi->sf.partition_search_type == SEARCH_PARTITION &&
2852 partition != PARTITION_SPLIT && bsize > BLOCK_8X8 &&
2853 (mi_row + mi_step < cm->mi_rows ||
2854 mi_row + (mi_step >> 1) == cm->mi_rows) &&
2855 (mi_col + mi_step < cm->mi_cols ||
2856 mi_col + (mi_step >> 1) == cm->mi_cols)) {
2857 BLOCK_SIZE split_subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_SPLIT);
2858 chosen_rdc.rate = 0;
2859 chosen_rdc.dist = 0;
2860 restore_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2861 pc_tree->partitioning = PARTITION_SPLIT;
2862
2863 // Split partition.
2864 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2865 int x_idx = (i & 1) * (mi_step >> 1);
2866 int y_idx = (i >> 1) * (mi_step >> 1);
2867 RD_COST tmp_rdc;
2868 ENTROPY_CONTEXT l[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE], a[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE];
2869 PARTITION_CONTEXT sl[8], sa[8];
2870
2871 if ((mi_row + y_idx >= cm->mi_rows) || (mi_col + x_idx >= cm->mi_cols))
2872 continue;
2873
2874 save_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2875 pc_tree->split[i]->partitioning = PARTITION_NONE;
2876 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row + y_idx, mi_col + x_idx,
2877 &tmp_rdc, split_subsize, &pc_tree->split[i]->none,
2878 INT_MAX, INT64_MAX);
2879
2880 restore_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2881
2882 if (tmp_rdc.rate == INT_MAX || tmp_rdc.dist == INT64_MAX) {
2883 vp9_rd_cost_reset(&chosen_rdc);
2884 break;
2885 }
2886
2887 chosen_rdc.rate += tmp_rdc.rate;
2888 chosen_rdc.dist += tmp_rdc.dist;
2889
2890 if (i != 3)
2891 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile_info, tp, mi_row + y_idx, mi_col + x_idx, 0,
2892 split_subsize, pc_tree->split[i]);
2893
2894 pl = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row + y_idx, mi_col + x_idx,
2895 split_subsize);
2896 chosen_rdc.rate += cpi->partition_cost[pl][PARTITION_NONE];
2897 }
2898 pl = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
2899 if (chosen_rdc.rate < INT_MAX) {
2900 chosen_rdc.rate += cpi->partition_cost[pl][PARTITION_SPLIT];
2901 chosen_rdc.rdcost =
2902 RDCOST(x->rdmult, x->rddiv, chosen_rdc.rate, chosen_rdc.dist);
2903 }
2904 }
2905
2906 // If last_part is better set the partitioning to that.
2907 if (last_part_rdc.rdcost < chosen_rdc.rdcost) {
2908 mi_8x8[0]->sb_type = bsize;
2909 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) pc_tree->partitioning = partition;
2910 chosen_rdc = last_part_rdc;
2911 }
2912 // If none was better set the partitioning to that.
2913 if (none_rdc.rdcost < chosen_rdc.rdcost) {
2914 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) pc_tree->partitioning = PARTITION_NONE;
2915 chosen_rdc = none_rdc;
2916 }
2917
2918 restore_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
2919
2920 // We must have chosen a partitioning and encoding or we'll fail later on.
2921 // No other opportunities for success.
2922 if (bsize == BLOCK_64X64)
2923 assert(chosen_rdc.rate < INT_MAX && chosen_rdc.dist < INT64_MAX);
2924
2925 if (do_recon) {
2926 int output_enabled = (bsize == BLOCK_64X64);
2927 encode_sb(cpi, td, tile_info, tp, mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled, bsize,
2928 pc_tree);
2929 }
2930
2931 *rate = chosen_rdc.rate;
2932 *dist = chosen_rdc.dist;
2933}
2934
2935static const BLOCK_SIZE min_partition_size[BLOCK_SIZES] = {
2936 BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4,
2937 BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_16X16,
2938 BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16
2939};
2940
2941static const BLOCK_SIZE max_partition_size[BLOCK_SIZES] = {
2942 BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_32X32,
2943 BLOCK_32X32, BLOCK_32X32, BLOCK_64X64, BLOCK_64X64, BLOCK_64X64,
2944 BLOCK_64X64, BLOCK_64X64, BLOCK_64X64
2945};
2946
2947// Look at all the mode_info entries for blocks that are part of this
2948// partition and find the min and max values for sb_type.
2949// At the moment this is designed to work on a 64x64 SB but could be
2950// adjusted to use a size parameter.
2951//
2952// The min and max are assumed to have been initialized prior to calling this
2953// function so repeat calls can accumulate a min and max of more than one sb64.
2954static void get_sb_partition_size_range(MACROBLOCKD *xd, MODE_INFO **mi_8x8,
2955 BLOCK_SIZE *min_block_size,
2956 BLOCK_SIZE *max_block_size,
2957 int bs_hist[BLOCK_SIZES]) {
2958 int sb_width_in_blocks = MI_BLOCK_SIZE;
2959 int sb_height_in_blocks = MI_BLOCK_SIZE;
2960 int i, j;
2961 int index = 0;
2962
2963 // Check the sb_type for each block that belongs to this region.
2964 for (i = 0; i < sb_height_in_blocks; ++i) {
2965 for (j = 0; j < sb_width_in_blocks; ++j) {
2966 MODE_INFO *mi = mi_8x8[index + j];
2967 BLOCK_SIZE sb_type = mi ? mi->sb_type : 0;
2968 bs_hist[sb_type]++;
2969 *min_block_size = VPXMIN(*min_block_size, sb_type);
2970 *max_block_size = VPXMAX(*max_block_size, sb_type);
2971 }
2972 index += xd->mi_stride;
2973 }
2974}
2975
2976// Next square block size less or equal than current block size.
2977static const BLOCK_SIZE next_square_size[BLOCK_SIZES] = {
2978 BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_4X4, BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_8X8,
2979 BLOCK_8X8, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_16X16, BLOCK_32X32,
2980 BLOCK_32X32, BLOCK_32X32, BLOCK_64X64
2981};
2982
2983// Look at neighboring blocks and set a min and max partition size based on
2984// what they chose.
2985static void rd_auto_partition_range(VP9_COMP *cpi, const TileInfo *const tile,
2986 MACROBLOCKD *const xd, int mi_row,
2987 int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE *min_block_size,
2988 BLOCK_SIZE *max_block_size) {
2989 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2990 MODE_INFO **mi = xd->mi;
2991 const int left_in_image = !!xd->left_mi;
2992 const int above_in_image = !!xd->above_mi;
2993 const int row8x8_remaining = tile->mi_row_end - mi_row;
2994 const int col8x8_remaining = tile->mi_col_end - mi_col;
2995 int bh, bw;
2996 BLOCK_SIZE min_size = BLOCK_4X4;
2997 BLOCK_SIZE max_size = BLOCK_64X64;
2998 int bs_hist[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 0 };
2999
3000 // Trap case where we do not have a prediction.
3001 if (left_in_image || above_in_image || cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME) {
3002 // Default "min to max" and "max to min"
3003 min_size = BLOCK_64X64;
3004 max_size = BLOCK_4X4;
3005
3006 // NOTE: each call to get_sb_partition_size_range() uses the previous
3007 // passed in values for min and max as a starting point.
3008 // Find the min and max partition used in previous frame at this location
3009 if (cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME) {
3010 MODE_INFO **prev_mi =
3011 &cm->prev_mi_grid_visible[mi_row * xd->mi_stride + mi_col];
3012 get_sb_partition_size_range(xd, prev_mi, &min_size, &max_size, bs_hist);
3013 }
3014 // Find the min and max partition sizes used in the left SB64
3015 if (left_in_image) {
3016 MODE_INFO **left_sb64_mi = &mi[-MI_BLOCK_SIZE];
3017 get_sb_partition_size_range(xd, left_sb64_mi, &min_size, &max_size,
3018 bs_hist);
3019 }
3020 // Find the min and max partition sizes used in the above SB64.
3021 if (above_in_image) {
3022 MODE_INFO **above_sb64_mi = &mi[-xd->mi_stride * MI_BLOCK_SIZE];
3023 get_sb_partition_size_range(xd, above_sb64_mi, &min_size, &max_size,
3024 bs_hist);
3025 }
3026
3027 // Adjust observed min and max for "relaxed" auto partition case.
3028 if (cpi->sf.auto_min_max_partition_size == RELAXED_NEIGHBORING_MIN_MAX) {
3029 min_size = min_partition_size[min_size];
3030 max_size = max_partition_size[max_size];
3031 }
3032 }
3033
3034 // Check border cases where max and min from neighbors may not be legal.
3035 max_size = find_partition_size(max_size, row8x8_remaining, col8x8_remaining,
3036 &bh, &bw);
3037 // Test for blocks at the edge of the active image.
3038 // This may be the actual edge of the image or where there are formatting
3039 // bars.
3040 if (vp9_active_edge_sb(cpi, mi_row, mi_col)) {
3041 min_size = BLOCK_4X4;
3042 } else {
3043 min_size =
3044 VPXMIN(cpi->sf.rd_auto_partition_min_limit, VPXMIN(min_size, max_size));
3045 }
3046
3047 // When use_square_partition_only is true, make sure at least one square
3048 // partition is allowed by selecting the next smaller square size as
3049 // *min_block_size.
3050 if (cpi->sf.use_square_partition_only &&
3051 next_square_size[max_size] < min_size) {
3052 min_size = next_square_size[max_size];
3053 }
3054
3055 *min_block_size = min_size;
3056 *max_block_size = max_size;
3057}
3058
3059// TODO(jingning) refactor functions setting partition search range
3060static void set_partition_range(VP9_COMMON *cm, MACROBLOCKD *xd, int mi_row,
3061 int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
3062 BLOCK_SIZE *min_bs, BLOCK_SIZE *max_bs) {
3063 int mi_width = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
3064 int mi_height = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
3065 int idx, idy;
3066
3067 MODE_INFO *mi;
3068 const int idx_str = cm->mi_stride * mi_row + mi_col;
3069 MODE_INFO **prev_mi = &cm->prev_mi_grid_visible[idx_str];
3070 BLOCK_SIZE bs, min_size, max_size;
3071
3072 min_size = BLOCK_64X64;
3073 max_size = BLOCK_4X4;
3074
3075 if (prev_mi) {
3076 for (idy = 0; idy < mi_height; ++idy) {
3077 for (idx = 0; idx < mi_width; ++idx) {
3078 mi = prev_mi[idy * cm->mi_stride + idx];
3079 bs = mi ? mi->sb_type : bsize;
3080 min_size = VPXMIN(min_size, bs);
3081 max_size = VPXMAX(max_size, bs);
3082 }
3083 }
3084 }
3085
3086 if (xd->left_mi) {
3087 for (idy = 0; idy < mi_height; ++idy) {
3088 mi = xd->mi[idy * cm->mi_stride - 1];
3089 bs = mi ? mi->sb_type : bsize;
3090 min_size = VPXMIN(min_size, bs);
3091 max_size = VPXMAX(max_size, bs);
3092 }
3093 }
3094
3095 if (xd->above_mi) {
3096 for (idx = 0; idx < mi_width; ++idx) {
3097 mi = xd->mi[idx - cm->mi_stride];
3098 bs = mi ? mi->sb_type : bsize;
3099 min_size = VPXMIN(min_size, bs);
3100 max_size = VPXMAX(max_size, bs);
3101 }
3102 }
3103
3104 if (min_size == max_size) {
3105 min_size = min_partition_size[min_size];
3106 max_size = max_partition_size[max_size];
3107 }
3108
3109 *min_bs = min_size;
3110 *max_bs = max_size;
3111}
3112#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY

3119 memcpy(x->pred_mv, ctx->pred_mv, sizeof(x->pred_mv));
3120}

3122#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
3123const int num_16x16_blocks_wide_lookup[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1,
3124 1, 2, 2, 2, 4, 4 };
3125const int num_16x16_blocks_high_lookup[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1,
3126 2, 1, 2, 4, 2, 4 };
3127const int qindex_skip_threshold_lookup[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 0, 10, 10, 30, 40,
3128 40, 60, 80, 80, 90,
3129 100, 100, 120 };
3130const int qindex_split_threshold_lookup[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 0, 3, 3, 7, 15,
3131 15, 30, 40, 40, 60,
3132 80, 80, 120 };
3133const int complexity_16x16_blocks_threshold[BLOCK_SIZES] = { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1,
3134 1, 1, 1, 1, 1,
3135 4, 4, 6 };
3136
3137typedef enum {
3138 MV_ZERO = 0,
3139 MV_LEFT = 1,
3140 MV_UP = 2,
3141 MV_RIGHT = 3,
3142 MV_DOWN = 4,
3143 MV_INVALID
3144} MOTION_DIRECTION;
3145
3146static INLINE MOTION_DIRECTION get_motion_direction_fp(uint8_t fp_byte) {
3147 if (fp_byte & FPMB_MOTION_ZERO_MASK) {
3148 return MV_ZERO;
3149 } else if (fp_byte & FPMB_MOTION_LEFT_MASK) {
3150 return MV_LEFT;
3151 } else if (fp_byte & FPMB_MOTION_RIGHT_MASK) {
3152 return MV_RIGHT;
3153 } else if (fp_byte & FPMB_MOTION_UP_MASK) {
3154 return MV_UP;
3155 } else {
3156 return MV_DOWN;
3157 }
3158}
3159
3160static INLINE int get_motion_inconsistency(MOTION_DIRECTION this_mv,
3161 MOTION_DIRECTION that_mv) {
3162 if (this_mv == that_mv) {
3163 return 0;
3164 } else {
3165 return abs(this_mv - that_mv) == 2 ? 2 : 1;
3166 }
3167}
3168#endif
3169
3170// Calculate prediction based on the given input features and neural net config.
3171// Assume there are no more than NN_MAX_NODES_PER_LAYER nodes in each hidden
3172// layer.
3173static void nn_predict(const float *features, const NN_CONFIG *nn_config,
3174 float *output) {
3175 int num_input_nodes = nn_config->num_inputs;
3176 int buf_index = 0;
3177 float buf[2][NN_MAX_NODES_PER_LAYER];
3178 const float *input_nodes = features;
3179
3180 // Propagate hidden layers.
3181 const int num_layers = nn_config->num_hidden_layers;
3182 int layer, node, i;
3183 assert(num_layers <= NN_MAX_HIDDEN_LAYERS);
3184 for (layer = 0; layer < num_layers; ++layer) {
3185 const float *weights = nn_config->weights[layer];
3186 const float *bias = nn_config->bias[layer];
3187 float *output_nodes = buf[buf_index];
3188 const int num_output_nodes = nn_config->num_hidden_nodes[layer];
3189 assert(num_output_nodes < NN_MAX_NODES_PER_LAYER);
3190 for (node = 0; node < num_output_nodes; ++node) {
3191 float val = 0.0f;
3192 for (i = 0; i < num_input_nodes; ++i) val += weights[i] * input_nodes[i];
3193 val += bias[node];
3194 // ReLU as activation function.
3195 val = VPXMAX(val, 0.0f);
3196 output_nodes[node] = val;
3197 weights += num_input_nodes;
3198 }
3199 num_input_nodes = num_output_nodes;
3200 input_nodes = output_nodes;
3201 buf_index = 1 - buf_index;
3202 }
3203
3204 // Final output layer.
3205 {
3206 const float *weights = nn_config->weights[num_layers];
3207 for (node = 0; node < nn_config->num_outputs; ++node) {
3208 const float *bias = nn_config->bias[num_layers];
3209 float val = 0.0f;
3210 for (i = 0; i < num_input_nodes; ++i) val += weights[i] * input_nodes[i];
3211 output[node] = val + bias[node];
3212 weights += num_input_nodes;
3213 }
3214 }
3215}
3216
3217#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
3218#define FEATURES 7
3219// Machine-learning based partition search early termination.
3220// Return 1 to skip split and rect partitions.
3221static int ml_pruning_partition(VP9_COMMON *const cm, MACROBLOCKD *const xd,
3222 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx, int mi_row, int mi_col,
3223 BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
3224 const int mag_mv =
3225 abs(ctx->mic.mv[0].as_mv.col) + abs(ctx->mic.mv[0].as_mv.row);
3226 const int left_in_image = !!xd->left_mi;
3227 const int above_in_image = !!xd->above_mi;
3228 MODE_INFO **prev_mi =
3229 &cm->prev_mi_grid_visible[mi_col + cm->mi_stride * mi_row];
3230 int above_par = 0; // above_partitioning
3231 int left_par = 0; // left_partitioning
3232 int last_par = 0; // last_partitioning
3233 int offset = 0;
3234 int i;
3235 BLOCK_SIZE context_size;
3236 const NN_CONFIG *nn_config = NULL;
3237 const float *mean, *sd, *linear_weights;
3238 float nn_score, linear_score;
3239 float features[FEATURES];
3240
3241 assert(b_width_log2_lookup[bsize] == b_height_log2_lookup[bsize]);
3242 vpx_clear_system_state();
3243
3244 switch (bsize) {
3245 case BLOCK_64X64:
3246 offset = 0;
3247 nn_config = &vp9_partition_nnconfig_64x64;
3248 break;
3249 case BLOCK_32X32:
3250 offset = 8;
3251 nn_config = &vp9_partition_nnconfig_32x32;
3252 break;
3253 case BLOCK_16X16:
3254 offset = 16;
3255 nn_config = &vp9_partition_nnconfig_16x16;
3256 break;
3257 default: assert(0 && "Unexpected block size."); return 0;
3258 }
3259
3260 if (above_in_image) {
3261 context_size = xd->above_mi->sb_type;
3262 if (context_size < bsize)
3263 above_par = 2;
3264 else if (context_size == bsize)
3265 above_par = 1;
3266 }
3267
3268 if (left_in_image) {
3269 context_size = xd->left_mi->sb_type;
3270 if (context_size < bsize)
3271 left_par = 2;
3272 else if (context_size == bsize)
3273 left_par = 1;
3274 }
3275
3276 if (prev_mi) {
3277 context_size = prev_mi[0]->sb_type;
3278 if (context_size < bsize)
3279 last_par = 2;
3280 else if (context_size == bsize)
3281 last_par = 1;
3282 }
3283
3284 mean = &vp9_partition_feature_mean[offset];
3285 sd = &vp9_partition_feature_std[offset];
3286 features[0] = ((float)ctx->rate - mean[0]) / sd[0];
3287 features[1] = ((float)ctx->dist - mean[1]) / sd[1];
3288 features[2] = ((float)mag_mv / 2 - mean[2]) * sd[2];
3289 features[3] = ((float)(left_par + above_par) / 2 - mean[3]) * sd[3];
3290 features[4] = ((float)ctx->sum_y_eobs - mean[4]) / sd[4];
3291 features[5] = ((float)cm->base_qindex - mean[5]) * sd[5];
3292 features[6] = ((float)last_par - mean[6]) * sd[6];
3293
3294 // Predict using linear model.
3295 linear_weights = &vp9_partition_linear_weights[offset];
3296 linear_score = linear_weights[FEATURES];
3297 for (i = 0; i < FEATURES; ++i)
3298 linear_score += linear_weights[i] * features[i];
3299 if (linear_score > 0.1f) return 0;
3300
3301 // Predict using neural net model.
3302 nn_predict(features, nn_config, &nn_score);
3303
3304 if (linear_score < -0.0f && nn_score < 0.1f) return 1;
3305 if (nn_score < -0.0f && linear_score < 0.1f) return 1;
3306 return 0;
3307}
3308#undef FEATURES
3309
3310#define FEATURES 4
3311// ML-based partition search breakout.
3312static int ml_predict_breakout(VP9_COMP *const cpi, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
3313 const MACROBLOCK *const x,
3314 const RD_COST *const rd_cost) {
3315 DECLARE_ALIGNED(16, static const uint8_t, vp9_64_zeros[64]) = { 0 };
3316 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3317 float features[FEATURES];
3318 const float *linear_weights = NULL; // Linear model weights.
3319 float linear_score = 0.0f;
3320 const int qindex = cm->base_qindex;
3321 const int q_ctx = qindex >= 200 ? 0 : (qindex >= 150 ? 1 : 2);
3322 const int is_720p_or_larger = VPXMIN(cm->width, cm->height) >= 720;
3323 const int resolution_ctx = is_720p_or_larger ? 1 : 0;
3324
3325 switch (bsize) {
3326 case BLOCK_64X64:
3327 linear_weights = vp9_partition_breakout_weights_64[resolution_ctx][q_ctx];
3328 break;
3329 case BLOCK_32X32:
3330 linear_weights = vp9_partition_breakout_weights_32[resolution_ctx][q_ctx];
3331 break;
3332 case BLOCK_16X16:
3333 linear_weights = vp9_partition_breakout_weights_16[resolution_ctx][q_ctx];
3334 break;
3335 case BLOCK_8X8:
3336 linear_weights = vp9_partition_breakout_weights_8[resolution_ctx][q_ctx];
3337 break;
3338 default: assert(0 && "Unexpected block size."); return 0;
3339 }
3340 if (!linear_weights) return 0;
3341
3342 { // Generate feature values.
3343#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3344 const int ac_q =
3345 vp9_ac_quant(cm->base_qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth) >> (x->e_mbd.bd - 8);
3346#else
3347 const int ac_q = vp9_ac_quant(qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth);
3348#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3349 const int num_pels_log2 = num_pels_log2_lookup[bsize];
3350 int feature_index = 0;
3351 unsigned int var, sse;
3352 float rate_f, dist_f;
3353
3354#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3355 if (x->e_mbd.cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
3356 var =
3357 vp9_high_get_sby_variance(cpi, &x->plane[0].src, bsize, x->e_mbd.bd);
3358 } else {
3359 var = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].vf(x->plane[0].src.buf, x->plane[0].src.stride,
3360 vp9_64_zeros, 0, &sse);
3361 }
3362#else
3363 var = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].vf(x->plane[0].src.buf, x->plane[0].src.stride,
3364 vp9_64_zeros, 0, &sse);
3365#endif
3366 var = var >> num_pels_log2;
3367
3368 vpx_clear_system_state();
3369
3370 rate_f = (float)VPXMIN(rd_cost->rate, INT_MAX);
3371 dist_f = (float)(VPXMIN(rd_cost->dist, INT_MAX) >> num_pels_log2);
3372 rate_f =
3373 ((float)x->rdmult / 128.0f / 512.0f / (float)(1 << num_pels_log2)) *
3374 rate_f;
3375
3376 features[feature_index++] = rate_f;
3377 features[feature_index++] = dist_f;
3378 features[feature_index++] = (float)var;
3379 features[feature_index++] = (float)ac_q;
3380 assert(feature_index == FEATURES);
3381 }
3382
3383 { // Calculate the output score.
3384 int i;
3385 linear_score = linear_weights[FEATURES];
3386 for (i = 0; i < FEATURES; ++i)
3387 linear_score += linear_weights[i] * features[i];
3388 }
3389
3390 return linear_score >= cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.search_breakout_thresh[q_ctx];
3391}
3392#undef FEATURES
3393
3394#define FEATURES 8
3395#define LABELS 4
3396static void ml_prune_rect_partition(VP9_COMP *const cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
3397 BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
3398 const PC_TREE *const pc_tree,
3399 int *allow_horz, int *allow_vert,
3400 int64_t ref_rd) {
3401 const NN_CONFIG *nn_config = NULL;
3402 float score[LABELS] = {
3403 0.0f,
3404 };
3405 int thresh = -1;
3406 int i;
3407 (void)x;
3408
3409 if (ref_rd <= 0 || ref_rd > 1000000000) return;
3410
3411 switch (bsize) {
3412 case BLOCK_8X8: break;
3413 case BLOCK_16X16:
3414 nn_config = &vp9_rect_part_nnconfig_16;
3415 thresh = cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.prune_rect_thresh[1];
3416 break;
3417 case BLOCK_32X32:
3418 nn_config = &vp9_rect_part_nnconfig_32;
3419 thresh = cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.prune_rect_thresh[2];
3420 break;
3421 case BLOCK_64X64:
3422 nn_config = &vp9_rect_part_nnconfig_64;
3423 thresh = cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.prune_rect_thresh[3];
3424 break;
3425 default: assert(0 && "Unexpected block size."); return;
3426 }
3427 if (!nn_config || thresh < 0) return;
3428
3429 // Feature extraction and model score calculation.
3430 {
3431 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3432#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3433 const int dc_q =
3434 vp9_dc_quant(cm->base_qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth) >> (x->e_mbd.bd - 8);
3435#else
3436 const int dc_q = vp9_dc_quant(cm->base_qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth);
3437#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3438 const int bs = 4 * num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
3439 int feature_index = 0;
3440 float features[FEATURES];
3441
3442 features[feature_index++] = logf((float)dc_q + 1.0f);
3443 features[feature_index++] =
3444 (float)(pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_NONE);
3445 features[feature_index++] = logf((float)ref_rd / bs / bs + 1.0f);
3446
3447 {
3448 const float norm_factor = 1.0f / ((float)ref_rd + 1.0f);
3449 const int64_t none_rdcost = pc_tree->none.rdcost;
3450 float rd_ratio = 2.0f;
3451 if (none_rdcost > 0 && none_rdcost < 1000000000)
3452 rd_ratio = (float)none_rdcost * norm_factor;
3453 features[feature_index++] = VPXMIN(rd_ratio, 2.0f);
3454
3455 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
3456 const int64_t this_rd = pc_tree->split[i]->none.rdcost;
3457 const int rd_valid = this_rd > 0 && this_rd < 1000000000;
3458 // Ratio between sub-block RD and whole block RD.
3459 features[feature_index++] =
3460 rd_valid ? (float)this_rd * norm_factor : 1.0f;
3461 }
3462 }
3463
3464 assert(feature_index == FEATURES);
3465 nn_predict(features, nn_config, score);
3466 }
3467
3468 // Make decisions based on the model score.
3469 {
3470 int max_score = -1000;
3471 int horz = 0, vert = 0;
3472 int int_score[LABELS];
3473 for (i = 0; i < LABELS; ++i) {
3474 int_score[i] = (int)(100 * score[i]);
3475 max_score = VPXMAX(int_score[i], max_score);
3476 }
3477 thresh = max_score - thresh;
3478 for (i = 0; i < LABELS; ++i) {
3479 if (int_score[i] >= thresh) {
3480 if ((i >> 0) & 1) horz = 1;
3481 if ((i >> 1) & 1) vert = 1;
3482 }
3483 }
3484 *allow_horz = *allow_horz && horz;
3485 *allow_vert = *allow_vert && vert;
3486 }
3487}
3488#undef FEATURES
3489#undef LABELS
3490
3491// Perform fast and coarse motion search for the given block. This is a
3492// pre-processing step for the ML based partition search speedup.
3493static void simple_motion_search(const VP9_COMP *const cpi, MACROBLOCK *const x,
3494 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row, int mi_col,
3495 MV ref_mv, MV_REFERENCE_FRAME ref,
3496 uint8_t *const pred_buf) {
3497 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3498 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
3499 MODE_INFO *const mi = xd->mi[0];
3500 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, ref);
3501 const int step_param = 1;
3502 const MvLimits tmp_mv_limits = x->mv_limits;
3503 const SEARCH_METHODS search_method = NSTEP;
3504 const int sadpb = x->sadperbit16;
3505 MV ref_mv_full = { ref_mv.row >> 3, ref_mv.col >> 3 };
3506 MV best_mv = { 0, 0 };
3507 int cost_list[5];
3508
3509 assert(yv12 != NULL);
3510 if (!yv12) return;
3511 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, yv12, mi_row, mi_col,
3512 &cm->frame_refs[ref - 1].sf);
3513 mi->ref_frame[0] = ref;
3514 mi->ref_frame[1] = NONE;
3515 mi->sb_type = bsize;
3516 vp9_set_mv_search_range(&x->mv_limits, &ref_mv);
3517 vp9_full_pixel_search(cpi, x, bsize, &ref_mv_full, step_param, search_method,
3518 sadpb, cond_cost_list(cpi, cost_list), &ref_mv,
3519 &best_mv, 0, 0);
3520 best_mv.row *= 8;
3521 best_mv.col *= 8;
3522 x->mv_limits = tmp_mv_limits;
3523 mi->mv[0].as_mv = best_mv;
3524
3525 set_ref_ptrs(cm, xd, mi->ref_frame[0], mi->ref_frame[1]);
3526 xd->plane[0].dst.buf = pred_buf;
3527 xd->plane[0].dst.stride = 64;
3528 vp9_build_inter_predictors_sby(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
3529}
3530
3531// Use a neural net model to prune partition-none and partition-split search.
3532// Features used: QP; spatial block size contexts; variance of prediction
3533// residue after simple_motion_search.
3534#define FEATURES 12
3535static void ml_predict_var_rd_paritioning(const VP9_COMP *const cpi,
3536 MACROBLOCK *const x,
3537 PC_TREE *const pc_tree,
3538 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row,
3539 int mi_col, int *none, int *split) {
3540 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3541 const NN_CONFIG *nn_config = NULL;
3542#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3543 MACROBLOCKD *xd = &x->e_mbd;
3544 DECLARE_ALIGNED(16, uint8_t, pred_buffer[64 * 64 * 2]);
3545 uint8_t *const pred_buf = (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH)
3546 ? (CONVERT_TO_BYTEPTR(pred_buffer))
3547 : pred_buffer;
3548#else
3549 DECLARE_ALIGNED(16, uint8_t, pred_buffer[64 * 64]);
3550 uint8_t *const pred_buf = pred_buffer;
3551#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3552 const int speed = cpi->oxcf.speed;
3553 float thresh = 0.0f;
3554
3555 switch (bsize) {
3556 case BLOCK_64X64:
3557 nn_config = &vp9_part_split_nnconfig_64;
3558 thresh = speed > 0 ? 2.8f : 3.0f;
3559 break;
3560 case BLOCK_32X32:
3561 nn_config = &vp9_part_split_nnconfig_32;
3562 thresh = speed > 0 ? 3.5f : 3.0f;
3563 break;
3564 case BLOCK_16X16:
3565 nn_config = &vp9_part_split_nnconfig_16;
3566 thresh = speed > 0 ? 3.8f : 4.0f;
3567 break;
3568 case BLOCK_8X8:
3569 nn_config = &vp9_part_split_nnconfig_8;
3570 if (cm->width >= 720 && cm->height >= 720)
3571 thresh = speed > 0 ? 2.5f : 2.0f;
3572 else
3573 thresh = speed > 0 ? 3.8f : 2.0f;
3574 break;
3575 default: assert(0 && "Unexpected block size."); return;
3576 }
3577
3578 if (!nn_config) return;
3579
3580 // Do a simple single motion search to find a prediction for current block.
3581 // The variance of the residue will be used as input features.
3582 {
3583 MV ref_mv;
3584 const MV_REFERENCE_FRAME ref =
3585 cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref ? ALTREF_FRAME : LAST_FRAME;
3586 // If bsize is 64x64, use zero MV as reference; otherwise, use MV result
3587 // of previous(larger) block as reference.
3588 if (bsize == BLOCK_64X64)
3589 ref_mv.row = ref_mv.col = 0;
3590 else
3591 ref_mv = pc_tree->mv;
3592 vp9_setup_src_planes(x, cpi->Source, mi_row, mi_col);
3593 simple_motion_search(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, ref_mv, ref, pred_buf);
3594 pc_tree->mv = x->e_mbd.mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3595 }
3596
3597 vpx_clear_system_state();
3598
3599 {
3600 float features[FEATURES] = { 0.0f };
3601#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3602 const int dc_q =
3603 vp9_dc_quant(cm->base_qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth) >> (xd->bd - 8);
3604#else
3605 const int dc_q = vp9_dc_quant(cm->base_qindex, 0, cm->bit_depth);
3606#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
3607 int feature_idx = 0;
3608 float score;
3609
3610 // Generate model input features.
3611 features[feature_idx++] = logf((float)dc_q + 1.0f);
3612
3613 // Get the variance of the residue as input features.
3614 {
3615 const int bs = 4 * num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
3616 const BLOCK_SIZE subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_SPLIT);
3617 const uint8_t *pred = pred_buf;
3618 const uint8_t *src = x->plane[0].src.buf;
3619 const int src_stride = x->plane[0].src.stride;
3620 const int pred_stride = 64;
3621 unsigned int sse;
3622 // Variance of whole block.
3623 const unsigned int var =
3624 cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].vf(src, src_stride, pred, pred_stride, &sse);
3625 const float factor = (var == 0) ? 1.0f : (1.0f / (float)var);
3626 const MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
3627 const int has_above = !!xd->above_mi;
3628 const int has_left = !!xd->left_mi;
3629 const BLOCK_SIZE above_bsize = has_above ? xd->above_mi->sb_type : bsize;
3630 const BLOCK_SIZE left_bsize = has_left ? xd->left_mi->sb_type : bsize;
3631 int i;
3632
3633 features[feature_idx++] = (float)has_above;
3634 features[feature_idx++] = (float)b_width_log2_lookup[above_bsize];
3635 features[feature_idx++] = (float)b_height_log2_lookup[above_bsize];
3636 features[feature_idx++] = (float)has_left;
3637 features[feature_idx++] = (float)b_width_log2_lookup[left_bsize];
3638 features[feature_idx++] = (float)b_height_log2_lookup[left_bsize];
3639 features[feature_idx++] = logf((float)var + 1.0f);
3640 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
3641 const int x_idx = (i & 1) * bs / 2;
3642 const int y_idx = (i >> 1) * bs / 2;
3643 const int src_offset = y_idx * src_stride + x_idx;
3644 const int pred_offset = y_idx * pred_stride + x_idx;
3645 // Variance of quarter block.
3646 const unsigned int sub_var =
3647 cpi->fn_ptr[subsize].vf(src + src_offset, src_stride,
3648 pred + pred_offset, pred_stride, &sse);
3649 const float var_ratio = (var == 0) ? 1.0f : factor * (float)sub_var;
3650 features[feature_idx++] = var_ratio;
3651 }
3652 }
3653 assert(feature_idx == FEATURES);
3654
3655 // Feed the features into the model to get the confidence score.
3656 nn_predict(features, nn_config, &score);
3657
3658 // Higher score means that the model has higher confidence that the split
3659 // partition is better than the non-split partition. So if the score is
3660 // high enough, we skip the none-split partition search; if the score is
3661 // low enough, we skip the split partition search.
3662 if (score > thresh) *none = 0;
3663 if (score < -thresh) *split = 0;
3664 }
3665}
3666#undef FEATURES
3667#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
3668
3669static double log_wiener_var(int64_t wiener_variance) {
3670 return log(1.0 + wiener_variance) / log(2.0);
3671}
3672
3673static void build_kmeans_segmentation(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
3674 VP9_COMMON *cm = &cpi->common;
3675 BLOCK_SIZE bsize = BLOCK_64X64;
3676 KMEANS_DATA *kmeans_data;
3677
3678 vp9_disable_segmentation(&cm->seg);
3679 if (cm->show_frame) {
3680 int mi_row, mi_col;
3681 cpi->kmeans_data_size = 0;
3682 cpi->kmeans_ctr_num = 8;
3683
3684 for (mi_row = 0; mi_row < cm->mi_rows; mi_row += MI_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3685 for (mi_col = 0; mi_col < cm->mi_cols; mi_col += MI_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3686 int mb_row_start = mi_row >> 1;
3687 int mb_col_start = mi_col >> 1;
3688 int mb_row_end = VPXMIN(
3689 (mi_row + num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize]) >> 1, cm->mb_rows);
3690 int mb_col_end = VPXMIN(
3691 (mi_col + num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize]) >> 1, cm->mb_cols);
3692 int row, col;
3693 int64_t wiener_variance = 0;
3694
3695 for (row = mb_row_start; row < mb_row_end; ++row)
3696 for (col = mb_col_start; col < mb_col_end; ++col)
3697 wiener_variance += cpi->mb_wiener_variance[row * cm->mb_cols + col];
3698
3699 wiener_variance /=
3700 (mb_row_end - mb_row_start) * (mb_col_end - mb_col_start);
3701
3702#if CONFIG_MULTITHREAD
3703 pthread_mutex_lock(&cpi->kmeans_mutex);
3704#endif // CONFIG_MULTITHREAD
3705
3706 kmeans_data = &cpi->kmeans_data_arr[cpi->kmeans_data_size++];
3707 kmeans_data->value = log_wiener_var(wiener_variance);
3708 kmeans_data->pos = mi_row * cpi->kmeans_data_stride + mi_col;
3709#if CONFIG_MULTITHREAD
3710 pthread_mutex_unlock(&cpi->kmeans_mutex);
3711#endif // CONFIG_MULTITHREAD
3712 }
3713 }
3714
3715 vp9_kmeans(cpi->kmeans_ctr_ls, cpi->kmeans_boundary_ls,
3716 cpi->kmeans_count_ls, cpi->kmeans_ctr_num, cpi->kmeans_data_arr,
3717 cpi->kmeans_data_size);
3718
3719 vp9_perceptual_aq_mode_setup(cpi, &cm->seg);
3720 }
3721}
3722
3723#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
3724static int wiener_var_segment(VP9_COMP *cpi, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row,
3725 int mi_col) {
3726 VP9_COMMON *cm = &cpi->common;
3727 int mb_row_start = mi_row >> 1;
3728 int mb_col_start = mi_col >> 1;
3729 int mb_row_end =
3730 VPXMIN((mi_row + num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize]) >> 1, cm->mb_rows);
3731 int mb_col_end =
3732 VPXMIN((mi_col + num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize]) >> 1, cm->mb_cols);
3733 int row, col, idx;
3734 int64_t wiener_variance = 0;
3735 int segment_id;
3736 int8_t seg_hist[MAX_SEGMENTS] = { 0 };
3737 int8_t max_count = 0, max_index = -1;
3738
3739 vpx_clear_system_state();
3740
3741 assert(cpi->norm_wiener_variance > 0);
3742
3743 for (row = mb_row_start; row < mb_row_end; ++row) {
3744 for (col = mb_col_start; col < mb_col_end; ++col) {
3745 wiener_variance = cpi->mb_wiener_variance[row * cm->mb_cols + col];
3746 segment_id =
3747 vp9_get_group_idx(log_wiener_var(wiener_variance),
3748 cpi->kmeans_boundary_ls, cpi->kmeans_ctr_num);
3749 ++seg_hist[segment_id];
3750 }
3751 }
3752
3753 for (idx = 0; idx < cpi->kmeans_ctr_num; ++idx) {
3754 if (seg_hist[idx] > max_count) {
3755 max_count = seg_hist[idx];
3756 max_index = idx;
3757 }
3758 }
3759
3760 assert(max_index >= 0);
3761 segment_id = max_index;
3762
3763 return segment_id;
3764}
3765
3766static int get_rdmult_delta(VP9_COMP *cpi, BLOCK_SIZE bsize, int mi_row,
3767 int mi_col, int orig_rdmult) {
3768 const int gf_group_index = cpi->twopass.gf_group.index;
3769 int64_t intra_cost = 0;
3770 int64_t mc_dep_cost = 0;
3771 int mi_wide = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
3772 int mi_high = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
3773 int row, col;
3774
3775 int dr = 0;
3776 int count = 0;
3777 double r0, rk, beta;
3778
3779 TplDepFrame *tpl_frame;
3780 TplDepStats *tpl_stats;
3781 int tpl_stride;
3782
3783 if (gf_group_index >= MAX_ARF_GOP_SIZE) return orig_rdmult;
3784 tpl_frame = &cpi->tpl_stats[gf_group_index];
3785
3786 if (tpl_frame->is_valid == 0) return orig_rdmult;
3787 tpl_stats = tpl_frame->tpl_stats_ptr;
3788 tpl_stride = tpl_frame->stride;
3789
3790 if (cpi->twopass.gf_group.layer_depth[gf_group_index] > 1) return orig_rdmult;
3791
3792 for (row = mi_row; row < mi_row + mi_high; ++row) {
3793 for (col = mi_col; col < mi_col + mi_wide; ++col) {
3794 TplDepStats *this_stats = &tpl_stats[row * tpl_stride + col];
3795
3796 if (row >= cpi->common.mi_rows || col >= cpi->common.mi_cols) continue;
3797
3798 intra_cost += this_stats->intra_cost;
3799 mc_dep_cost += this_stats->mc_dep_cost;
3800
3801 ++count;
3802 }
3803 }
3804
3805 vpx_clear_system_state();
3806
3807 r0 = cpi->rd.r0;
3808 rk = (double)intra_cost / mc_dep_cost;
3809 beta = r0 / rk;
3810 dr = vp9_get_adaptive_rdmult(cpi, beta);
3811
3812 dr = VPXMIN(dr, orig_rdmult * 3 / 2);
3813 dr = VPXMAX(dr, orig_rdmult * 1 / 2);
3814
3815 dr = VPXMAX(1, dr);
3816
3817 return dr;
3818}
3819#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
3820
3821#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
3822static void assign_partition_info(
3823 const int row_start_4x4, const int col_start_4x4, const int block_width_4x4,
3824 const int block_height_4x4, const int num_unit_rows,
3825 const int num_unit_cols, PARTITION_INFO *partition_info) {
3826 int i, j;
3827 for (i = 0; i < block_height_4x4; ++i) {
3828 for (j = 0; j < block_width_4x4; ++j) {
3829 const int row_4x4 = row_start_4x4 + i;
3830 const int col_4x4 = col_start_4x4 + j;
3831 const int unit_index = row_4x4 * num_unit_cols + col_4x4;
3832 if (row_4x4 >= num_unit_rows || col_4x4 >= num_unit_cols) continue;
3833 partition_info[unit_index].row = row_4x4 << 2;
3834 partition_info[unit_index].column = col_4x4 << 2;
3835 partition_info[unit_index].row_start = row_start_4x4 << 2;
3836 partition_info[unit_index].column_start = col_start_4x4 << 2;
3837 partition_info[unit_index].width = block_width_4x4 << 2;
3838 partition_info[unit_index].height = block_height_4x4 << 2;
3839 }
3840 }
3841}
3842
3843static void assign_motion_vector_info(const int block_width_4x4,
3844 const int block_height_4x4,
3845 const int row_start_4x4,
3846 const int col_start_4x4,
3847 const int num_unit_rows,
3848 const int num_unit_cols, MV *source_mv[2],
3849 MV_REFERENCE_FRAME source_ref_frame[2],
3850 MOTION_VECTOR_INFO *motion_vector_info) {
3851 int i, j;
3852 for (i = 0; i < block_height_4x4; ++i) {
3853 for (j = 0; j < block_width_4x4; ++j) {
3854 const int row_4x4 = row_start_4x4 + i;
3855 const int col_4x4 = col_start_4x4 + j;
3856 const int unit_index = row_4x4 * num_unit_cols + col_4x4;
3857 if (row_4x4 >= num_unit_rows || col_4x4 >= num_unit_cols) continue;
3858 if (source_ref_frame[1] == NONE) {
3859 assert(source_mv[1]->row == 0 && source_mv[1]->col == 0);
3860 }
3861 motion_vector_info[unit_index].ref_frame[0] = source_ref_frame[0];
3862 motion_vector_info[unit_index].ref_frame[1] = source_ref_frame[1];
3863 motion_vector_info[unit_index].mv[0].as_mv.row = source_mv[0]->row;
3864 motion_vector_info[unit_index].mv[0].as_mv.col = source_mv[0]->col;
3865 motion_vector_info[unit_index].mv[1].as_mv.row = source_mv[1]->row;
3866 motion_vector_info[unit_index].mv[1].as_mv.col = source_mv[1]->col;
3867 }
3868 }
3869}
3870
3871static void store_superblock_info(
3872 const PC_TREE *const pc_tree, MODE_INFO **mi_grid_visible,
3873 const int mi_stride, const int square_size_4x4, const int num_unit_rows,
3874 const int num_unit_cols, const int row_start_4x4, const int col_start_4x4,
3875 PARTITION_INFO *partition_info, MOTION_VECTOR_INFO *motion_vector_info) {
3876 const int subblock_square_size_4x4 = square_size_4x4 >> 1;
3877 if (row_start_4x4 >= num_unit_rows || col_start_4x4 >= num_unit_cols) return;
3878 assert(pc_tree->partitioning != PARTITION_INVALID);
3879 // End node, no split.
3880 if (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_NONE ||
3881 pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_HORZ ||
3882 pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_VERT || square_size_4x4 == 1) {
3883 const int mi_row = row_start_4x4 >> 1;
3884 const int mi_col = col_start_4x4 >> 1;
3885 const int mi_idx = mi_stride * mi_row + mi_col;
3886 MODE_INFO **mi = mi_grid_visible + mi_idx;
3887 MV *source_mv[2];
3888 MV_REFERENCE_FRAME source_ref_frame[2];
3889
3890 // partition info
3891 const int block_width_4x4 = (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_VERT)
3892 ? square_size_4x4 >> 1
3893 : square_size_4x4;
3894 const int block_height_4x4 = (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_HORZ)
3895 ? square_size_4x4 >> 1
3896 : square_size_4x4;
3897 assign_partition_info(row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4, block_width_4x4,
3898 block_height_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
3899 partition_info);
3900 if (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_VERT) {
3901 assign_partition_info(row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4 + block_width_4x4,
3902 block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4, num_unit_rows,
3903 num_unit_cols, partition_info);
3904 } else if (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_HORZ) {
3905 assign_partition_info(row_start_4x4 + block_height_4x4, col_start_4x4,
3906 block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4, num_unit_rows,
3907 num_unit_cols, partition_info);
3908 }
3909
3910 // motion vector info
3911 if (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_HORZ) {
3912 int is_valid_second_rectangle = 0;
3913 assert(square_size_4x4 > 1);
3914 // First rectangle.
3915 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3916 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3917 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3918 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->mv[1].as_mv;
3919 assign_motion_vector_info(block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4,
3920 row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4, num_unit_rows,
3921 num_unit_cols, source_mv, source_ref_frame,
3922 motion_vector_info);
3923 // Second rectangle.
3924 if (square_size_4x4 == 2) {
3925 is_valid_second_rectangle = 1;
3926 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3927 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3928 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->bmi[2].as_mv[0].as_mv;
3929 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->bmi[2].as_mv[1].as_mv;
3930 } else {
3931 const int mi_row_2 = mi_row + (block_height_4x4 >> 1);
3932 const int mi_col_2 = mi_col;
3933 if (mi_row_2 * 2 < num_unit_rows && mi_col_2 * 2 < num_unit_cols) {
3934 const int mi_idx_2 = mi_stride * mi_row_2 + mi_col_2;
3935 is_valid_second_rectangle = 1;
3936 mi = mi_grid_visible + mi_idx_2;
3937 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3938 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3939 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3940 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->mv[1].as_mv;
3941 }
3942 }
3943 if (is_valid_second_rectangle) {
3944 assign_motion_vector_info(
3945 block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4, row_start_4x4 + block_height_4x4,
3946 col_start_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols, source_mv,
3947 source_ref_frame, motion_vector_info);
3948 }
3949 } else if (pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_VERT) {
3950 int is_valid_second_rectangle = 0;
3951 assert(square_size_4x4 > 1);
3952 // First rectangle.
3953 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3954 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3955 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3956 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->mv[1].as_mv;
3957 assign_motion_vector_info(block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4,
3958 row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4, num_unit_rows,
3959 num_unit_cols, source_mv, source_ref_frame,
3960 motion_vector_info);
3961 // Second rectangle.
3962 if (square_size_4x4 == 2) {
3963 is_valid_second_rectangle = 1;
3964 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3965 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3966 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->bmi[1].as_mv[0].as_mv;
3967 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->bmi[1].as_mv[1].as_mv;
3968 } else {
3969 const int mi_row_2 = mi_row;
3970 const int mi_col_2 = mi_col + (block_width_4x4 >> 1);
3971 if (mi_row_2 * 2 < num_unit_rows && mi_col_2 * 2 < num_unit_cols) {
3972 const int mi_idx_2 = mi_stride * mi_row_2 + mi_col_2;
3973 is_valid_second_rectangle = 1;
3974 mi = mi_grid_visible + mi_idx_2;
3975 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3976 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3977 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3978 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->mv[1].as_mv;
3979 }
3980 }
3981 if (is_valid_second_rectangle) {
3982 assign_motion_vector_info(
3983 block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4, row_start_4x4,
3984 col_start_4x4 + block_width_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
3985 source_mv, source_ref_frame, motion_vector_info);
3986 }
3987 } else {
3988 assert(pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_NONE || square_size_4x4 == 1);
3989 source_ref_frame[0] = mi[0]->ref_frame[0];
3990 source_ref_frame[1] = mi[0]->ref_frame[1];
3991 if (square_size_4x4 == 1) {
3992 const int sub8x8_row = row_start_4x4 % 2;
3993 const int sub8x8_col = col_start_4x4 % 2;
3994 const int sub8x8_idx = sub8x8_row * 2 + sub8x8_col;
3995 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->bmi[sub8x8_idx].as_mv[0].as_mv;
3996 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->bmi[sub8x8_idx].as_mv[1].as_mv;
3997 } else {
3998 source_mv[0] = &mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv;
3999 source_mv[1] = &mi[0]->mv[1].as_mv;
4000 }
4001 assign_motion_vector_info(block_width_4x4, block_height_4x4,
4002 row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4, num_unit_rows,
4003 num_unit_cols, source_mv, source_ref_frame,
4004 motion_vector_info);
4005 }
4006
4007 return;
4008 }
4009 // recursively traverse partition tree when partition is split.
4010 assert(pc_tree->partitioning == PARTITION_SPLIT);
4011 store_superblock_info(pc_tree->split[0], mi_grid_visible, mi_stride,
4012 subblock_square_size_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
4013 row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4, partition_info,
4014 motion_vector_info);
4015 store_superblock_info(pc_tree->split[1], mi_grid_visible, mi_stride,
4016 subblock_square_size_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
4017 row_start_4x4, col_start_4x4 + subblock_square_size_4x4,
4018 partition_info, motion_vector_info);
4019 store_superblock_info(pc_tree->split[2], mi_grid_visible, mi_stride,
4020 subblock_square_size_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
4021 row_start_4x4 + subblock_square_size_4x4, col_start_4x4,
4022 partition_info, motion_vector_info);
4023 store_superblock_info(pc_tree->split[3], mi_grid_visible, mi_stride,
4024 subblock_square_size_4x4, num_unit_rows, num_unit_cols,
4025 row_start_4x4 + subblock_square_size_4x4,
4026 col_start_4x4 + subblock_square_size_4x4,
4027 partition_info, motion_vector_info);
4028}
4029#endif // CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
4030
4031#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
4032// TODO(jingning,jimbankoski,rbultje): properly skip partition types that are
4033// unlikely to be selected depending on previous rate-distortion optimization
4034// results, for encoding speed-up.
4035static int rd_pick_partition(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
4036 TileDataEnc *tile_data, TOKENEXTRA **tp,
4037 int mi_row, int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
4038 RD_COST *rd_cost, RD_COST best_rdc,
4039 PC_TREE *pc_tree) {
4040 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
4041 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
4042 TileInfo *const tile_info = &tile_data->tile_info;
4043 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
4044 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
4045 const int mi_step = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] / 2;
4046 ENTROPY_CONTEXT l[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE], a[16 * MAX_MB_PLANE];
4047 PARTITION_CONTEXT sl[8], sa[8];
4048 TOKENEXTRA *tp_orig = *tp;
4049 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *const ctx = &pc_tree->none;
4050 int i;
4051 const int pl = partition_plane_context(xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
4052 BLOCK_SIZE subsize;
4053 RD_COST this_rdc, sum_rdc;
4054 int do_split = bsize >= BLOCK_8X8;
4055 int do_rect = 1;
4056 INTERP_FILTER pred_interp_filter;
4057
4058 // Override skipping rectangular partition operations for edge blocks
4059 const int force_horz_split = (mi_row + mi_step >= cm->mi_rows);
4060 const int force_vert_split = (mi_col + mi_step >= cm->mi_cols);
4061 const int xss = x->e_mbd.plane[1].subsampling_x;
4062 const int yss = x->e_mbd.plane[1].subsampling_y;
4063
4064 BLOCK_SIZE min_size = x->min_partition_size;
4065 BLOCK_SIZE max_size = x->max_partition_size;
4066
4067#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
4068 unsigned int src_diff_var = UINT_MAX;
4069 int none_complexity = 0;
4070#endif
4071
4072 int partition_none_allowed = !force_horz_split && !force_vert_split;
4073 int partition_horz_allowed =
4074 !force_vert_split && yss <= xss && bsize >= BLOCK_8X8;
4075 int partition_vert_allowed =
4076 !force_horz_split && xss <= yss && bsize >= BLOCK_8X8;
4077
4078 int64_t dist_breakout_thr = cpi->sf.partition_search_breakout_thr.dist;
4079 int rate_breakout_thr = cpi->sf.partition_search_breakout_thr.rate;
4080 int must_split = 0;
4081 int should_encode_sb = 0;
4082
4083 // Ref frames picked in the [i_th] quarter subblock during square partition
4084 // RD search. It may be used to prune ref frame selection of rect partitions.
4085 uint8_t ref_frames_used[4] = { 0, 0, 0, 0 };
4086
4087 int partition_mul = x->cb_rdmult;
4088
4089 (void)*tp_orig;
4090
4091 assert(num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] ==
4092 num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize]);
4093
4094 dist_breakout_thr >>=
4095 8 - (b_width_log2_lookup[bsize] + b_height_log2_lookup[bsize]);
4096
4097 rate_breakout_thr *= num_pels_log2_lookup[bsize];
4098
4099 vp9_rd_cost_init(&this_rdc);
4100 vp9_rd_cost_init(&sum_rdc);
4101
4102 set_offsets(cpi, tile_info, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
4103
4104 if (oxcf->tuning == VP8_TUNE_SSIM) {
4105 set_ssim_rdmult(cpi, x, bsize, mi_row, mi_col, &partition_mul);
4106 }
4107 vp9_rd_cost_update(partition_mul, x->rddiv, &best_rdc);
4108
4109 if (bsize == BLOCK_16X16 && cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ &&
4110 cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != LOOKAHEAD_AQ)
4111 x->mb_energy = vp9_block_energy(cpi, x, bsize);
4112
4113 if (cpi->sf.cb_partition_search && bsize == BLOCK_16X16) {
4114 int cb_partition_search_ctrl =
4115 ((pc_tree->index == 0 || pc_tree->index == 3) +
4116 get_chessboard_index(cm->current_video_frame)) &
4117 0x1;
4118
4119 if (cb_partition_search_ctrl && bsize > min_size && bsize < max_size)
4120 set_partition_range(cm, xd, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, &min_size, &max_size);
4121 }
4122
4123 // Get sub block energy range
4124 if (bsize >= BLOCK_16X16) {
4125 int min_energy, max_energy;
4126 vp9_get_sub_block_energy(cpi, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize, &min_energy,
4127 &max_energy);
4128 must_split = (min_energy < -3) && (max_energy - min_energy > 2);
4129 }
4130
4131 // Determine partition types in search according to the speed features.
4132 // The threshold set here has to be of square block size.
4133 if (cpi->sf.auto_min_max_partition_size) {
4134 partition_none_allowed &= (bsize <= max_size);
4135 partition_horz_allowed &=
4136 ((bsize <= max_size && bsize > min_size) || force_horz_split);
4137 partition_vert_allowed &=
4138 ((bsize <= max_size && bsize > min_size) || force_vert_split);
4139 do_split &= bsize > min_size;
4140 }
4141
4142 if (cpi->sf.use_square_partition_only &&
4143 (bsize > cpi->sf.use_square_only_thresh_high ||
4144 bsize < cpi->sf.use_square_only_thresh_low)) {
4145 if (cpi->use_svc) {
4146 if (!vp9_active_h_edge(cpi, mi_row, mi_step) || x->e_mbd.lossless)
4147 partition_horz_allowed &= force_horz_split;
4148 if (!vp9_active_v_edge(cpi, mi_row, mi_step) || x->e_mbd.lossless)
4149 partition_vert_allowed &= force_vert_split;
4150 } else {
4151 partition_horz_allowed &= force_horz_split;
4152 partition_vert_allowed &= force_vert_split;
4153 }
4154 }
4155
4156 save_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
4157
4158#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
4159 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
4160 set_offsets(cpi, tile_info, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
4161 src_diff_var = get_sby_perpixel_diff_variance(cpi, &x->plane[0].src, mi_row,
4162 mi_col, bsize);
4163 }
4164#endif
4165
4166#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
4167 // Decide whether we shall split directly and skip searching NONE by using
4168 // the first pass block statistics
4169 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats && bsize >= BLOCK_32X32 && do_split &&
4170 partition_none_allowed && src_diff_var > 4 &&
4171 cm->base_qindex < qindex_split_threshold_lookup[bsize]) {
4172 int mb_row = mi_row >> 1;
4173 int mb_col = mi_col >> 1;
4174 int mb_row_end =
4175 VPXMIN(mb_row + num_16x16_blocks_high_lookup[bsize], cm->mb_rows);
4176 int mb_col_end =
4177 VPXMIN(mb_col + num_16x16_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize], cm->mb_cols);
4178 int r, c;
4179
4180 // compute a complexity measure, basically measure inconsistency of motion
4181 // vectors obtained from the first pass in the current block
4182 for (r = mb_row; r < mb_row_end; r++) {
4183 for (c = mb_col; c < mb_col_end; c++) {
4184 const int mb_index = r * cm->mb_cols + c;
4185
4186 MOTION_DIRECTION this_mv;
4187 MOTION_DIRECTION right_mv;
4188 MOTION_DIRECTION bottom_mv;
4189
4190 this_mv =
4191 get_motion_direction_fp(cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats[mb_index]);
4192
4193 // to its right
4194 if (c != mb_col_end - 1) {
4195 right_mv = get_motion_direction_fp(
4196 cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats[mb_index + 1]);
4197 none_complexity += get_motion_inconsistency(this_mv, right_mv);
4198 }
4199
4200 // to its bottom
4201 if (r != mb_row_end - 1) {
4202 bottom_mv = get_motion_direction_fp(
4203 cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats[mb_index + cm->mb_cols]);
4204 none_complexity += get_motion_inconsistency(this_mv, bottom_mv);
4205 }
4206
4207 // do not count its left and top neighbors to avoid double counting
4208 }
4209 }
4210
4211 if (none_complexity > complexity_16x16_blocks_threshold[bsize]) {
4212 partition_none_allowed = 0;
4213 }
4214 }
4215#endif
4216
4217 pc_tree->partitioning = PARTITION_NONE;
4218
4219 if (cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.var_pruning && !frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
4220 const int do_rd_ml_partition_var_pruning =
4221 partition_none_allowed && do_split &&
4222 mi_row + num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize] <= cm->mi_rows &&
4223 mi_col + num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] <= cm->mi_cols;
4224 if (do_rd_ml_partition_var_pruning) {
4225 ml_predict_var_rd_paritioning(cpi, x, pc_tree, bsize, mi_row, mi_col,
4226 &partition_none_allowed, &do_split);
4227 } else {
4228 vp9_zero(pc_tree->mv);
4229 }
4230 if (bsize > BLOCK_8X8) { // Store MV result as reference for subblocks.
4231 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) pc_tree->split[i]->mv = pc_tree->mv;
4232 }
4233 }
4234
4235 // PARTITION_NONE
4236 if (partition_none_allowed) {
4237 rd_pick_sb_modes(cpi, tile_data, x, mi_row, mi_col, &this_rdc, bsize, ctx,
4238 best_rdc.rate, best_rdc.dist);
4239 ctx->rdcost = this_rdc.rdcost;
4240 if (this_rdc.rate != INT_MAX) {
4241 if (cpi->sf.prune_ref_frame_for_rect_partitions) {
4242 const int ref1 = ctx->mic.ref_frame[0];
4243 const int ref2 = ctx->mic.ref_frame[1];
4244 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
4245 ref_frames_used[i] |= (1 << ref1);
4246 if (ref2 > 0) ref_frames_used[i] |= (1 << ref2);
4247 }
4248 }
4249 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) {
4250 this_rdc.rate += cpi->partition_cost[pl][PARTITION_NONE];
4251 vp9_rd_cost_update(partition_mul, x->rddiv, &this_rdc);
4252 }
4253
4254 if (this_rdc.rdcost < best_rdc.rdcost) {
4255 MODE_INFO *mi = xd->mi[0];
4256
4257 best_rdc = this_rdc;
4258 should_encode_sb = 1;
4259 if (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) pc_tree->partitioning = PARTITION_NONE;
4260
4261 if (cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.search_early_termination) {
4262 // Currently, the machine-learning based partition search early
4263 // termination is only used while bsize is 16x16, 32x32 or 64x64,
4264 // VPXMIN(cm->width, cm->height) >= 480, and speed = 0.
4265 if (!x->e_mbd.lossless &&
4266 !segfeature_active(&cm->seg, mi->segment_id, SEG_LVL_SKIP) &&
4267 ctx->mic.mode >= INTRA_MODES && bsize >= BLOCK_16X16) {
4268 if (ml_pruning_partition(cm, xd, ctx, mi_row, mi_col, bsize)) {
4269 do_split = 0;
4270 do_rect = 0;
4271 }
4272 }
4273 }
4274
4275 if ((do_split || do_rect) && !x->e_mbd.lossless && ctx->skippable) {
4276 const int use_ml_based_breakout =
4277 cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.search_breakout && cm->base_qindex >= 100;
4278 if (use_ml_based_breakout) {
4279 if (ml_predict_breakout(cpi, bsize, x, &this_rdc)) {
4280 do_split = 0;
4281 do_rect = 0;
4282 }
4283 } else {
4284 if (!cpi->sf.rd_ml_partition.search_early_termination) {
4285 if ((best_rdc.dist < (dist_breakout_thr >> 2)) ||
4286 (best_rdc.dist < dist_breakout_thr &&
4287 best_rdc.rate < rate_breakout_thr)) {
4288 do_split = 0;
4289 do_rect = 0;
4290 }
4291 }
4292 }
4293 }
4294
4295#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
4296 // Check if every 16x16 first pass block statistics has zero
4297 // motion and the corresponding first pass residue is small enough.
4298 // If that is the case, check the difference variance between the
4299 // current frame and the last frame. If the variance is small enough,
4300 // stop further splitting in RD optimization
4301 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats && do_split != 0 &&
4302 cm->base_qindex > qindex_skip_threshold_lookup[bsize]) {
4303 int mb_row = mi_row >> 1;
4304 int mb_col = mi_col >> 1;
4305 int mb_row_end =
4306 VPXMIN(mb_row + num_16x16_blocks_high_lookup[bsize], cm->mb_rows);
4307 int mb_col_end =
4308 VPXMIN(mb_col + num_16x16_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize], cm->mb_cols);
4309 int r, c;
4310
4311 int skip = 1;
4312 for (r = mb_row; r < mb_row_end; r++) {
4313 for (c = mb_col; c < mb_col_end; c++) {
4314 const int mb_index = r * cm->mb_cols + c;
4315 if (!(cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats[mb_index] &
4316 FPMB_MOTION_ZERO_MASK) ||
4317 !(cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats[mb_index] &
4318 FPMB_ERROR_SMALL_MASK)) {
4319 skip = 0;
4320 break;
4321 }
4322 }
4323 if (skip == 0) {
4324 break;
4325 }
4326 }
4327
4328 if (skip) {
4329 if (src_diff_var == UINT_MAX) {
4330 set_offsets(cpi, tile_info, x, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
4331 src_diff_var = get_sby_perpixel_diff_variance(
4332 cpi, &x->plane[0].src, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
4333 }
4334 if (src_diff_var < 8) {
4335 do_split = 0;
4336 do_rect = 0;
4337 }
4338 }
4339 }
4340#endif
4341 }
4342 }
4343 restore_context(x, mi_row, mi_col, a, l, sa, sl, bsize);
4344 } else {
4345 vp9_zero(ctx->pred_mv);
4346 ctx->mic.interp_filter = EIGHTTAP;
4347 }
4348
4349 // store estimated motion vector
4350 store_pred_mv(x, ctx);
4351
4352 // If the interp_filter is marked as SWITCHABLE_FILTERS, it was for an
4353 // intra block and used for context purposes.
4354 if (ctx->mic.interp_filter == SWITCHABLE_FILTERS) {
4355 pred_interp_filter = EIGHTTAP;
4356 } else {
4357 pred_interp_filter = ctx->mic.interp_filter;
4358 }
4359
4360 // PARTITION_SPLIT
4361 // TODO(jingning): use the motion vectors given by the above search as
4362 // the starting point of motion search in the following partition type check.
4363 pc_tree->split[0]->none.rdcost = 0;
4364 pc_tree->split[1]->none.rdcost = 0;
4365 pc_tree->split[2]->none.rdcost = 0;
4366 pc_tree->split[3]->none.rdcost = 0;
4367 if (do_split || must_split) {
4368 subsize = get_subsize(bsize, PARTITION_SPLIT);
4369 load_pred_mv(x, ctx);
4370 if (bsize == BLOCK_8X8) {
4371 i = 4;
4372 if (cpi->sf.adaptive_pred_interp_filter && partition_none_allowed)
4373 pc_tree->leaf_split[0]->pred_interp_filter = pred_interp_filter;
