6075#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
6076static int input_fpmb_stats(FIRSTPASS_MB_STATS *firstpass_mb_stats,
6077 VP9_COMMON *cm, uint8_t **this_frame_mb_stats) {
6078 uint8_t *mb_stats_in = firstpass_mb_stats->mb_stats_start +
6079 cm->current_video_frame * cm->MBs * sizeof(uint8_t);
6080
6081 if (mb_stats_in > firstpass_mb_stats->mb_stats_end) return EOF;
6082
6083 *this_frame_mb_stats = mb_stats_in;
6084
6085 return 1;
6086}
6087#endif
6088
6089static int compare_kmeans_data(const void *a, const void *b) {
6090 if (((const KMEANS_DATA *)a)->value > ((const KMEANS_DATA *)b)->value) {
6091 return 1;
6092 } else if (((const KMEANS_DATA *)a)->value <
6093 ((const KMEANS_DATA *)b)->value) {
6094 return -1;
6095 } else {
6096 return 0;
6097 }
6098}
6099
6100static void compute_boundary_ls(const double *ctr_ls, int k,
6101 double *boundary_ls) {
6102 // boundary_ls[j] is the upper bound of data centered at ctr_ls[j]
6103 int j;
6104 for (j = 0; j < k - 1; ++j) {
6105 boundary_ls[j] = (ctr_ls[j] + ctr_ls[j + 1]) / 2.;
6106 }
6107 boundary_ls[k - 1] = DBL_MAX;
6108}
6109
6110int vp9_get_group_idx(double value, double *boundary_ls, int k) {
6111 int group_idx = 0;
6112 while (value >= boundary_ls[group_idx]) {
6113 ++group_idx;
6114 if (group_idx == k - 1) {
6115 break;
6116 }
6117 }
6118 return group_idx;
6119}
6120
6121void vp9_kmeans(double *ctr_ls, double *boundary_ls, int *count_ls, int k,
6122 KMEANS_DATA *arr, int size) {
6123 int i, j;
6124 int itr;
6125 int group_idx;
6126 double sum[MAX_KMEANS_GROUPS];
6127 int count[MAX_KMEANS_GROUPS];
6128
6129 vpx_clear_system_state();
6130
6131 assert(k >= 2 && k <= MAX_KMEANS_GROUPS);
6132
6133 qsort(arr, size, sizeof(*arr), compare_kmeans_data);
6134
6135 // initialize the center points
6136 for (j = 0; j < k; ++j) {
6137 ctr_ls[j] = arr[(size * (2 * j + 1)) / (2 * k)].value;
6138 }
6139
6140 for (itr = 0; itr < 10; ++itr) {
6141 compute_boundary_ls(ctr_ls, k, boundary_ls);
6142 for (i = 0; i < MAX_KMEANS_GROUPS; ++i) {
6143 sum[i] = 0;
6144 count[i] = 0;
6145 }
6146
6147 // Both the data and centers are sorted in ascending order.
6148 // As each data point is processed in order, its corresponding group index
6149 // can only increase. So we only need to reset the group index to zero here.
6150 group_idx = 0;
6151 for (i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
6152 while (arr[i].value >= boundary_ls[group_idx]) {
6153 // place samples into clusters
6154 ++group_idx;
6155 if (group_idx == k - 1) {
6156 break;
6157 }
6158 }
6159 sum[group_idx] += arr[i].value;
6160 ++count[group_idx];
6161 }
6162
6163 for (group_idx = 0; group_idx < k; ++group_idx) {
6164 if (count[group_idx] > 0)
6165 ctr_ls[group_idx] = sum[group_idx] / count[group_idx];
6166
6167 sum[group_idx] = 0;
6168 count[group_idx] = 0;
6169 }
6170 }
6171
6172 // compute group_idx, boundary_ls and count_ls
6173 for (j = 0; j < k; ++j) {
6174 count_ls[j] = 0;
6175 }
6176 compute_boundary_ls(ctr_ls, k, boundary_ls);
6177 group_idx = 0;
6178 for (i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
6179 while (arr[i].value >= boundary_ls[group_idx]) {
6180 ++group_idx;
6181 if (group_idx == k - 1) {
6182 break;
6183 }
6184 }
6185 arr[i].group_idx = group_idx;
6186 ++count_ls[group_idx];
6187 }
6188}
6189
6190static void encode_frame_internal(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
6191 SPEED_FEATURES *const sf = &cpi->sf;
6192 ThreadData *const td = &cpi->td;
6193 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
6194 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6195 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
6196 const int gf_group_index = cpi->twopass.gf_group.index;
6197
6198 xd->mi = cm->mi_grid_visible;
6199 xd->mi[0] = cm->mi;
6200 vp9_zero(*td->counts);
6201 vp9_zero(cpi->td.rd_counts);
6202
6203 xd->lossless = cm->base_qindex == 0 && cm->y_dc_delta_q == 0 &&
6204 cm->uv_dc_delta_q == 0 && cm->uv_ac_delta_q == 0;
6205
6206#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
6207 if (cm->use_highbitdepth)
6208 x->fwd_txfm4x4 = xd->lossless ? vp9_highbd_fwht4x4 : vpx_highbd_fdct4x4;
6209 else
6210 x->fwd_txfm4x4 = xd->lossless ? vp9_fwht4x4 : vpx_fdct4x4;
6211 x->highbd_inv_txfm_add =
6212 xd->lossless ? vp9_highbd_iwht4x4_add : vp9_highbd_idct4x4_add;
6213#else
6214 x->fwd_txfm4x4 = xd->lossless ? vp9_fwht4x4 : vpx_fdct4x4;
6215#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
6216 x->inv_txfm_add = xd->lossless ? vp9_iwht4x4_add : vp9_idct4x4_add;
6217#if CONFIG_CONSISTENT_RECODE
6218 x->optimize = sf->optimize_coefficients == 1 && cpi->oxcf.pass != 1;
6219#endif
6220 if (xd->lossless) x->optimize = 0;
6221 x->sharpness = cpi->oxcf.sharpness;
6222 x->adjust_rdmult_by_segment = (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == VARIANCE_AQ);
6223
6224 cm->tx_mode = select_tx_mode(cpi, xd);
6225
6226 vp9_frame_init_quantizer(cpi);
6227
6228 vp9_initialize_rd_consts(cpi);
6229 vp9_initialize_me_consts(cpi, x, cm->base_qindex);
6230 init_encode_frame_mb_context(cpi);
6231 cm->use_prev_frame_mvs =
6232 !cm->error_resilient_mode && cm->width == cm->last_width &&
6233 cm->height == cm->last_height && !cm->intra_only && cm->last_show_frame;
6234 // Special case: set prev_mi to NULL when the previous mode info
6235 // context cannot be used.
6236 cm->prev_mi =
6237 cm->use_prev_frame_mvs ? cm->prev_mip + cm->mi_stride + 1 : NULL;
6238
6239 x->quant_fp = cpi->sf.use_quant_fp;
6240 vp9_zero(x->skip_txfm);
6241 if (sf->use_nonrd_pick_mode) {
6242 // Initialize internal buffer pointers for rtc coding, where non-RD
6243 // mode decision is used and hence no buffer pointer swap needed.
6244 int i;
6245 struct macroblock_plane *const p = x->plane;
6246 struct macroblockd_plane *const pd = xd->plane;
6247 PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx = &cpi->td.pc_root->none;
6248
6249 for (i = 0; i < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++i) {
6250 p[i].coeff = ctx->coeff_pbuf[i][0];
6251 p[i].qcoeff = ctx->qcoeff_pbuf[i][0];
6252 pd[i].dqcoeff = ctx->dqcoeff_pbuf[i][0];
6253 p[i].eobs = ctx->eobs_pbuf[i][0];
6254 }
6255 vp9_zero(x->zcoeff_blk);
6256
6257 if (cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME && cpi->rc.frames_since_golden == 0 &&
6258 !(cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 0 && cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_VBR) &&
6259 !cpi->use_svc)
6260 cpi->ref_frame_flags &= (~VP9_GOLD_FLAG);
6261
6262 if (sf->partition_search_type == SOURCE_VAR_BASED_PARTITION)
6263 source_var_based_partition_search_method(cpi);
6264 } else if (gf_group_index && gf_group_index < MAX_ARF_GOP_SIZE &&
6265 cpi->sf.enable_tpl_model) {
6266 TplDepFrame *tpl_frame = &cpi->tpl_stats[cpi->twopass.gf_group.index];
6267 TplDepStats *tpl_stats = tpl_frame->tpl_stats_ptr;
6268
6269 int tpl_stride = tpl_frame->stride;
6270 int64_t intra_cost_base = 0;
6271 int64_t mc_dep_cost_base = 0;
6272 int row, col;
6273
6274 for (row = 0; row < cm->mi_rows && tpl_frame->is_valid; ++row) {
6275 for (col = 0; col < cm->mi_cols; ++col) {
6276 TplDepStats *this_stats = &tpl_stats[row * tpl_stride + col];
6277 intra_cost_base += this_stats->intra_cost;
6278 mc_dep_cost_base += this_stats->mc_dep_cost;
6279 }
6280 }
6281
6282 vpx_clear_system_state();
6283
6284 if (tpl_frame->is_valid)
6285 cpi->rd.r0 = (double)intra_cost_base / mc_dep_cost_base;
6286 }
6287
6288 // Frame segmentation
6289 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == PERCEPTUAL_AQ) build_kmeans_segmentation(cpi);
6290
6291 {
6292 struct vpx_usec_timer emr_timer;
6293 vpx_usec_timer_start(&emr_timer);
6294
6295#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
6296 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
6297 input_fpmb_stats(&cpi->twopass.firstpass_mb_stats, cm,
6298 &cpi->twopass.this_frame_mb_stats);
6299 }
6300#endif
6301
6302 if (!cpi->row_mt) {
6303 cpi->row_mt_sync_read_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_read_dummy;
6304 cpi->row_mt_sync_write_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_write_dummy;
6305 // If allowed, encoding tiles in parallel with one thread handling one
6306 // tile when row based multi-threading is disabled.
6307 if (VPXMIN(cpi->oxcf.max_threads, 1 << cm->log2_tile_cols) > 1)
6308 vp9_encode_tiles_mt(cpi);
6309 else
6310 encode_tiles(cpi);
6311 } else {
6312 cpi->row_mt_sync_read_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_read;
6313 cpi->row_mt_sync_write_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_write;
6314 vp9_encode_tiles_row_mt(cpi);
6315 }
6316
6317 vpx_usec_timer_mark(&emr_timer);
6318 cpi->time_encode_sb_row += vpx_usec_timer_elapsed(&emr_timer);
6319 }
6320
6321 sf->skip_encode_frame =
6322 sf->skip_encode_sb ? get_skip_encode_frame(cm, td) : 0;
6323
6324#if 0
6325 // Keep record of the total distortion this time around for future use
6326 cpi->last_frame_distortion = cpi->frame_distortion;
6327#endif
6328}
6329
6330static INTERP_FILTER get_interp_filter(
6331 const int64_t threshes[SWITCHABLE_FILTER_CONTEXTS], int is_alt_ref) {
6332 if (!is_alt_ref && threshes[EIGHTTAP_SMOOTH] > threshes[EIGHTTAP] &&
6333 threshes[EIGHTTAP_SMOOTH] > threshes[EIGHTTAP_SHARP] &&
6334 threshes[EIGHTTAP_SMOOTH] > threshes[SWITCHABLE - 1]) {
6335 return EIGHTTAP_SMOOTH;
6336 } else if (threshes[EIGHTTAP_SHARP] > threshes[EIGHTTAP] &&
6337 threshes[EIGHTTAP_SHARP] > threshes[SWITCHABLE - 1]) {
6338 return EIGHTTAP_SHARP;
6339 } else if (threshes[EIGHTTAP] > threshes[SWITCHABLE - 1]) {
6340 return EIGHTTAP;
6341 } else {
6342 return SWITCHABLE;
6343 }
6344}
6345
6346static int compute_frame_aq_offset(struct VP9_COMP *cpi) {
6347 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6348 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8_ptr = cm->mi_grid_visible;
6349 struct segmentation *const seg = &cm->seg;
6350
6351 int mi_row, mi_col;
6352 int sum_delta = 0;
6353 int map_index = 0;
6354 int qdelta_index;
6355 int segment_id;
6356
6357 for (mi_row = 0; mi_row < cm->mi_rows; mi_row++) {
6358 MODE_INFO **mi_8x8 = mi_8x8_ptr;
6359 for (mi_col = 0; mi_col < cm->mi_cols; mi_col++, mi_8x8++) {
6360 segment_id = mi_8x8[0]->segment_id;
6361 qdelta_index = get_segdata(seg, segment_id, SEG_LVL_ALT_Q);
6362 sum_delta += qdelta_index;
6363 map_index++;
6364 }
6365 mi_8x8_ptr += cm->mi_stride;
6366 }
6367
6368 return sum_delta / (cm->mi_rows * cm->mi_cols);
6369}
6370
6371#if CONFIG_CONSISTENT_RECODE || CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
6372static void restore_encode_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
6373 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6374 const int tile_cols = 1 << cm->log2_tile_cols;
6375 const int tile_rows = 1 << cm->log2_tile_rows;
6376 int tile_col, tile_row;
6377 int i, j;
6378 RD_OPT *rd_opt = &cpi->rd;
6379 for (i = 0; i < MAX_REF_FRAMES; i++) {
6380 for (j = 0; j < REFERENCE_MODES; j++)
6381 rd_opt->prediction_type_threshes[i][j] =
6382 rd_opt->prediction_type_threshes_prev[i][j];
6383
6384 for (j = 0; j < SWITCHABLE_FILTER_CONTEXTS; j++)
6385 rd_opt->filter_threshes[i][j] = rd_opt->filter_threshes_prev[i][j];
6386 }
6387
6388 if (cpi->tile_data != NULL) {
6389 for (tile_row = 0; tile_row < tile_rows; ++tile_row)
6390 for (tile_col = 0; tile_col < tile_cols; ++tile_col) {
6391 TileDataEnc *tile_data =
6392 &cpi->tile_data[tile_row * tile_cols + tile_col];
6393 for (i = 0; i < BLOCK_SIZES; ++i) {
6394 for (j = 0; j < MAX_MODES; ++j) {
6395 tile_data->thresh_freq_fact[i][j] =
6396 tile_data->thresh_freq_fact_prev[i][j];
6397 }
6398 }
6399 }
6400 }
6401
6402 cm->interp_filter = cpi->sf.default_interp_filter;
6403}
6404#endif // CONFIG_CONSISTENT_RECODE || CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
6405
6406void vp9_encode_frame(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
6407 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6408
6409#if CONFIG_CONSISTENT_RECODE || CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
6410 restore_encode_params(cpi);
6411#endif
6412
6413#if CONFIG_MISMATCH_DEBUG
6414 mismatch_reset_frame(MAX_MB_PLANE);
6415#endif
6416
6417 // In the longer term the encoder should be generalized to match the
6418 // decoder such that we allow compound where one of the 3 buffers has a
6419 // different sign bias and that buffer is then the fixed ref. However, this
6420 // requires further work in the rd loop. For now the only supported encoder
6421 // side behavior is where the ALT ref buffer has opposite sign bias to
6422 // the other two.
6423 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
6424 if (vp9_compound_reference_allowed(cm)) {
6425 cpi->allow_comp_inter_inter = 1;
6426 vp9_setup_compound_reference_mode(cm);
6427 } else {
6428 cpi->allow_comp_inter_inter = 0;
6429 }
6430 }
6431
6432 if (cpi->sf.frame_parameter_update) {
6433 int i;
6434 RD_OPT *const rd_opt = &cpi->rd;
6435 FRAME_COUNTS *counts = cpi->td.counts;
6436 RD_COUNTS *const rdc = &cpi->td.rd_counts;
6437
6438 // This code does a single RD pass over the whole frame assuming
6439 // either compound, single or hybrid prediction as per whatever has
6440 // worked best for that type of frame in the past.
6441 // It also predicts whether another coding mode would have worked
6442 // better than this coding mode. If that is the case, it remembers
6443 // that for subsequent frames.
6444 // It also does the same analysis for transform size selection.
6445 const MV_REFERENCE_FRAME frame_type = get_frame_type(cpi);
6446 int64_t *const mode_thrs = rd_opt->prediction_type_threshes[frame_type];
6447 int64_t *const filter_thrs = rd_opt->filter_threshes[frame_type];
6448 const int is_alt_ref = frame_type == ALTREF_FRAME;
6449
6450 /* prediction (compound, single or hybrid) mode selection */
6451 if (is_alt_ref || !cpi->allow_comp_inter_inter)
6452 cm->reference_mode = SINGLE_REFERENCE;
6453 else if (mode_thrs[COMPOUND_REFERENCE] > mode_thrs[SINGLE_REFERENCE] &&
6454 mode_thrs[COMPOUND_REFERENCE] > mode_thrs[REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT] &&
6455 check_dual_ref_flags(cpi) && cpi->static_mb_pct == 100)
6456 cm->reference_mode = COMPOUND_REFERENCE;
6457 else if (mode_thrs[SINGLE_REFERENCE] > mode_thrs[REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT])
6458 cm->reference_mode = SINGLE_REFERENCE;
6459 else
6460 cm->reference_mode = REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT;
6461
6462 if (cm->interp_filter == SWITCHABLE)
6463 cm->interp_filter = get_interp_filter(filter_thrs, is_alt_ref);
6464
6465 encode_frame_internal(cpi);
6466
6467 for (i = 0; i < REFERENCE_MODES; ++i)
6468 mode_thrs[i] = (mode_thrs[i] + rdc->comp_pred_diff[i] / cm->MBs) / 2;
6469
6470 for (i = 0; i < SWITCHABLE_FILTER_CONTEXTS; ++i)
6471 filter_thrs[i] = (filter_thrs[i] + rdc->filter_diff[i] / cm->MBs) / 2;
6472
6473 if (cm->reference_mode == REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT) {
6474 int single_count_zero = 0;
6475 int comp_count_zero = 0;
6476
6477 for (i = 0; i < COMP_INTER_CONTEXTS; i++) {
6478 single_count_zero += counts->comp_inter[i][0];
6479 comp_count_zero += counts->comp_inter[i][1];
6480 }
6481
6482 if (comp_count_zero == 0) {
6483 cm->reference_mode = SINGLE_REFERENCE;
6484 vp9_zero(counts->comp_inter);
6485 } else if (single_count_zero == 0) {
6486 cm->reference_mode = COMPOUND_REFERENCE;
6487 vp9_zero(counts->comp_inter);
6488 }
6489 }
6490
6491 if (cm->tx_mode == TX_MODE_SELECT) {
6492 int count4x4 = 0;
6493 int count8x8_lp = 0, count8x8_8x8p = 0;
6494 int count16x16_16x16p = 0, count16x16_lp = 0;
6495 int count32x32 = 0;
6496
6497 for (i = 0; i < TX_SIZE_CONTEXTS; ++i) {
6498 count4x4 += counts->tx.p32x32[i][TX_4X4];
6499 count4x4 += counts->tx.p16x16[i][TX_4X4];
6500 count4x4 += counts->tx.p8x8[i][TX_4X4];
6501
6502 count8x8_lp += counts->tx.p32x32[i][TX_8X8];
6503 count8x8_lp += counts->tx.p16x16[i][TX_8X8];
6504 count8x8_8x8p += counts->tx.p8x8[i][TX_8X8];
6505
6506 count16x16_16x16p += counts->tx.p16x16[i][TX_16X16];
6507 count16x16_lp += counts->tx.p32x32[i][TX_16X16];
6508 count32x32 += counts->tx.p32x32[i][TX_32X32];
6509 }
6510 if (count4x4 == 0 && count16x16_lp == 0 && count16x16_16x16p == 0 &&
6511 count32x32 == 0) {
6512 cm->tx_mode = ALLOW_8X8;
6513 reset_skip_tx_size(cm, TX_8X8);
6514 } else if (count8x8_8x8p == 0 && count16x16_16x16p == 0 &&
6515 count8x8_lp == 0 && count16x16_lp == 0 && count32x32 == 0) {
6516 cm->tx_mode = ONLY_4X4;
6517 reset_skip_tx_size(cm, TX_4X4);
6518 } else if (count8x8_lp == 0 && count16x16_lp == 0 && count4x4 == 0) {
6519 cm->tx_mode = ALLOW_32X32;
6520 } else if (count32x32 == 0 && count8x8_lp == 0 && count4x4 == 0) {
6521 cm->tx_mode = ALLOW_16X16;
6522 reset_skip_tx_size(cm, TX_16X16);
6523 }
6524 }
6525 } else {
6526 FRAME_COUNTS *counts = cpi->td.counts;
6527 cm->reference_mode = SINGLE_REFERENCE;
6528 if (cpi->allow_comp_inter_inter && cpi->sf.use_compound_nonrd_pickmode &&
6529 cpi->rc.alt_ref_gf_group && !cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref &&
6530 cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME)
6531 cm->reference_mode = REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT;
6532
6533 encode_frame_internal(cpi);
6534
6535 if (cm->reference_mode == REFERENCE_MODE_SELECT) {
6536 int single_count_zero = 0;
6537 int comp_count_zero = 0;
6538 int i;
6539 for (i = 0; i < COMP_INTER_CONTEXTS; i++) {
6540 single_count_zero += counts->comp_inter[i][0];
6541 comp_count_zero += counts->comp_inter[i][1];
6542 }
6543 if (comp_count_zero == 0) {
6544 cm->reference_mode = SINGLE_REFERENCE;
6545 vp9_zero(counts->comp_inter);
6546 } else if (single_count_zero == 0) {
6547 cm->reference_mode = COMPOUND_REFERENCE;
6548 vp9_zero(counts->comp_inter);
6549 }
6550 }
6551 }
6552
6553 // If segmented AQ is enabled compute the average AQ weighting.
6554 if (cm->seg.enabled && (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ) &&
6555 (cm->seg.update_map || cm->seg.update_data)) {
6556 cm->seg.aq_av_offset = compute_frame_aq_offset(cpi);
6557 }
6558}
6559
6560static void sum_intra_stats(FRAME_COUNTS *counts, const MODE_INFO *mi) {
6561 const PREDICTION_MODE y_mode = mi->mode;
6562 const PREDICTION_MODE uv_mode = mi->uv_mode;
6563 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = mi->sb_type;
6564
6565 if (bsize < BLOCK_8X8) {
6566 int idx, idy;
6567 const int num_4x4_w = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
6568 const int num_4x4_h = num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
6569 for (idy = 0; idy < 2; idy += num_4x4_h)
6570 for (idx = 0; idx < 2; idx += num_4x4_w)
6571 ++counts->y_mode[0][mi->bmi[idy * 2 + idx].as_mode];
6572 } else {
6573 ++counts->y_mode[size_group_lookup[bsize]][y_mode];
6574 }
6575
6576 ++counts->uv_mode[y_mode][uv_mode];
6577}
6578
6579static void update_zeromv_cnt(VP9_COMP *const cpi, const MODE_INFO *const mi,
6580 int mi_row, int mi_col, BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
6581 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6582 MV mv = mi->mv[0].as_mv;
6583 const int bw = num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize];
6584 const int bh = num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize];
6585 const int xmis = VPXMIN(cm->mi_cols - mi_col, bw);
6586 const int ymis = VPXMIN(cm->mi_rows - mi_row, bh);
6587 const int block_index = mi_row * cm->mi_cols + mi_col;
6588 int x, y;
6589 for (y = 0; y < ymis; y++)
6590 for (x = 0; x < xmis; x++) {
6591 int map_offset = block_index + y * cm->mi_cols + x;
6592 if (mi->ref_frame[0] == LAST_FRAME && is_inter_block(mi) &&
6593 mi->segment_id <= CR_SEGMENT_ID_BOOST2) {
6594 if (abs(mv.row) < 8 && abs(mv.col) < 8) {
6595 if (cpi->consec_zero_mv[map_offset] < 255)
6596 cpi->consec_zero_mv[map_offset]++;
6597 } else {
6598 cpi->consec_zero_mv[map_offset] = 0;
6599 }
6600 }
6601 }
6602}
6603
6604static void encode_superblock(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td, TOKENEXTRA **t,
6605 int output_enabled, int mi_row, int mi_col,
6606 BLOCK_SIZE bsize, PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx) {
6607 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
6608 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
6609 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
6610 MODE_INFO *mi = xd->mi[0];
6611 const int seg_skip =
6612 segfeature_active(&cm->seg, mi->segment_id, SEG_LVL_SKIP);
6613 x->skip_recode = !x->select_tx_size && mi->sb_type >= BLOCK_8X8 &&
6614 cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != COMPLEXITY_AQ &&
6615 cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ &&
6616 cpi->sf.allow_skip_recode;
6617
6618 if (!x->skip_recode && !cpi->sf.use_nonrd_pick_mode)
6619 memset(x->skip_txfm, 0, sizeof(x->skip_txfm));
6620
6621 x->skip_optimize = ctx->is_coded;
6622 ctx->is_coded = 1;
6623 x->use_lp32x32fdct = cpi->sf.use_lp32x32fdct;
6624 x->skip_encode = (!output_enabled && cpi->sf.skip_encode_frame &&
6625 x->q_index < QIDX_SKIP_THRESH);
6626
6627 if (x->skip_encode) return;
6628
6629 if (!is_inter_block(mi)) {
6630 int plane;
6631#if CONFIG_BETTER_HW_COMPATIBILITY && CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
6632 if ((xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) &&
6633 (xd->above_mi == NULL || xd->left_mi == NULL) &&
6634 need_top_left[mi->uv_mode])
6635 assert(0);
6636#endif // CONFIG_BETTER_HW_COMPATIBILITY && CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
6637 mi->skip = 1;
6638 for (plane = 0; plane < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++plane)
6639 vp9_encode_intra_block_plane(x, VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8), plane, 1);
6640 if (output_enabled) sum_intra_stats(td->counts, mi);
6641 vp9_tokenize_sb(cpi, td, t, !output_enabled, seg_skip,
6642 VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8));
6643 } else {
6644 int ref;
6645 const int is_compound = has_second_ref(mi);
6646 set_ref_ptrs(cm, xd, mi->ref_frame[0], mi->ref_frame[1]);
6647 for (ref = 0; ref < 1 + is_compound; ++ref) {
6648 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *cfg = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, mi->ref_frame[ref]);
6649 assert(cfg != NULL);
6650 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, ref, cfg, mi_row, mi_col,
6651 &xd->block_refs[ref]->sf);
6652 }
6653 if (!(cpi->sf.reuse_inter_pred_sby && ctx->pred_pixel_ready) || seg_skip)
6654 vp9_build_inter_predictors_sby(xd, mi_row, mi_col,
6655 VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8));
6656
6657 vp9_build_inter_predictors_sbuv(xd, mi_row, mi_col,
6658 VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8));
6659
6660#if CONFIG_MISMATCH_DEBUG
6661 if (output_enabled) {
6662 int plane;
6663 for (plane = 0; plane < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++plane) {
6664 const struct macroblockd_plane *pd = &xd->plane[plane];
6665 int pixel_c, pixel_r;
6666 const BLOCK_SIZE plane_bsize =
6667 get_plane_block_size(VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8), &xd->plane[plane]);
6668 const int bw = get_block_width(plane_bsize);
6669 const int bh = get_block_height(plane_bsize);
6670 mi_to_pixel_loc(&pixel_c, &pixel_r, mi_col, mi_row, 0, 0,
6671 pd->subsampling_x, pd->subsampling_y);
6672
6673 mismatch_record_block_pre(pd->dst.buf, pd->dst.stride, plane, pixel_c,
6674 pixel_r, bw, bh,
6675 xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH);
6676 }
6677 }
6678#endif
6679
6680 vp9_encode_sb(x, VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8), mi_row, mi_col, output_enabled);
6681 vp9_tokenize_sb(cpi, td, t, !output_enabled, seg_skip,
6682 VPXMAX(bsize, BLOCK_8X8));
6683 }
6684
6685 if (seg_skip) {
6686 assert(mi->skip);
6687 }
6688
6689 if (output_enabled) {
6690 if (cm->tx_mode == TX_MODE_SELECT && mi->sb_type >= BLOCK_8X8 &&
6691 !(is_inter_block(mi) && mi->skip)) {
6692 ++get_tx_counts(max_txsize_lookup[bsize], get_tx_size_context(xd),
6693 &td->counts->tx)[mi->tx_size];
6694 } else {
6695 // The new intra coding scheme requires no change of transform size
6696 if (is_inter_block(mi)) {
6697 mi->tx_size = VPXMIN(tx_mode_to_biggest_tx_size[cm->tx_mode],
6698 max_txsize_lookup[bsize]);
6699 } else {
6700 mi->tx_size = (bsize >= BLOCK_8X8) ? mi->tx_size : TX_4X4;
6701 }
6702 }
6703
6704 ++td->counts->tx.tx_totals[mi->tx_size];
6705 ++td->counts->tx.tx_totals[get_uv_tx_size(mi, &xd->plane[1])];
6706 if (cm->seg.enabled && cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ)
6707 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_sb_postencode(cpi, mi, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
6708 if (cpi->oxcf.pass == 0 && cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id == 0 &&
6709 (!cpi->use_svc ||
6710 (cpi->use_svc &&
6711 !cpi->svc.layer_context[cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame &&
6712 cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 1)))
6713 update_zeromv_cnt(cpi, mi, mi_row, mi_col, bsize);
6714 }
6715}
